.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:5:**Headline finding:** The Lane C verdict enum and report renderer have no slot for **degraded/expected** — the state 012 REQ-004 says a drift-to-legacy fallback must report as. The new `compiledRouting` block (014 spec:113-118) will land as a second boolean gate beside `routeGold.gate.failed` (score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1767); combining the two via OR collapses three observably distinct states — *compiled-serving with route-gold violation*, *drifted legacy-fallback*, *broken resolver* — into one BLOCKED signal. The companion per-hub serving-status readout 012 REQ-004 mandates (line 99) has no implementation target: `compiled-route.cjs` only resolves `(hub, prompt) → decision`, never `(fleet) → status[]`. Every existing observability surface — `advisor_status` (advisor-status.ts:230-338), `spec_kit_skill_advisor_status`, and the bridge's metadata path — never reads the seven activation manifests at `.opencode/specs/.../010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:15:- **014 spec.md:134-136** plans `report.compiledRouting` with `drift rows` and `breakages` but says "routing divergence or breakage produces a distinct blocked verdict" — no distinct slot for drift. The expected degradation path has no rendered verdict.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:21:- **.opencode/bin/** contains `compiled-route.cjs` (per-hub × per-prompt decision), `skill-advisor.cjs`, `mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs` — none ships a `compiled-status.cjs` or `--all-hubs` fleet readout. **verified** by `ls .opencode/bin/`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:28:- **advisor-recommend.ts:41-49** `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` is the compiled-eligibility allowlist (7 hubs). A hypothetical 8th hub with `hub-router.json` but no entry in this set would be hub-type but NOT compiled-eligible — `route-gold: auto` → ENFORCED, `compiledRouting: auto` (014 spec line 242) → off; operators must reason about both flags to know what was scored.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:30:### D. `compiledRouting` telemetry is sibling, not parallel
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:33:- **014 spec.md:107** plans `compiledRouting` as a separate report block, not as additional rows in `routeTelemetry`. An operator reading `report.advisorySignals.routeTelemetry.routeMissRate` for a hub where compiled is *drifted* sees a healthy legacy number while the compiled-serving side is silently failing — the metric vocabulary mixes the two regimes under the same shape, with no `compiled.telemetryMissingRate` parallel.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:44:- **build-report.cjs:178-181** renders `## Funnel` from this dict. New compiledRouting parity rows (one per scenario when 014 lands) have no `firstFailingStage` slot and will either be silently dropped from the funnel or double-counted by scenarioId. `headlineBottleneck` will never name the compiled-parity lane even when it is the dominant failure mode.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:50:1. **Add a `DEGRADED | LEGACY-FALLBACK | COMPILED-SERVING | BROKEN | DRIFTED` lane to the Lane C verdict enum** (score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1765-1773 + build-report.cjs:81-86) before 014's parity lane lands. Without a distinct verdict slot, REQ-004 of 012 cannot be observed — drift looks identical to breakage. The new `compiledRouting.blockedReason` should be a *sub-cause* of an outer verdict, not an OR-combined boolean. (F-10-1, F-10-5)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:51:2. **Ship `compiled-route-status` as a new `.opencode/bin/compiled-route-status.cjs` CLI** with `--hub <id>` and `--all` modes that read the seven activation manifests and emit `{hubId, servingAuthority, shadowOnly, selectedPolicy.generation, effectivePolicyHash, fenceEpoch, manifestFingerprint}`. This is the only way the operator can answer "is hub X currently compiled-serving?" without reading seven files by hand. (F-10-3, F-10-7)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:53:4. **In the planned `compiledRouting` lane, attach a `lane: 'legacy'|'compiled'` field to each row's `firstFailingStage` and extend `reduceRouteTelemetry` with a `compiledTelemetry` parallel block** so the existing `headlineBottleneck` can name "compiled-parity" when that is the dominant failure. (F-10-2, F-10-7)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:54:5. **Add a `compiledEligibility` field to the `routeGold` summary** so a hub-type scenario whose target is not in `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` is reported as `n/a` rather than scored; the gap between hub-type detection (file existence) and compiled-eligibility (manifest + allowlist) must be surfaced, not papered over by `auto`. (F-10-4)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:60:  {"id":"F-10-1","area":"benchmark","finding":"The Lane C verdict enum has no degraded/expected slot for drift-to-legacy fallback, so the new compiledRouting parity gate will collapse three observably distinct states (compiled-serving-with-route-gold-violation, drifted-legacy-fallback, broken-resolver) into one BLOCKED signal — directly violating 012 REQ-004 which mandates drift be scored as degraded/expected.","evidence":"score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1765-1773 (verdict enum); 012 spec.md:99+133 (REQ-004 three-state observability contract); 014 spec.md:134-136 (compiledRouting gate OR-combined with routeGold.gate.failed)","severity":"P0","actionable":"Add a distinct DEGRADED|LEGACY-FALLBACK|DRIFTED sub-verdict to the Lane C enum and have compiledRouting.blockedReason route to it instead of being OR-combined with routeGold.gate.failed; require a regression test asserting the three states produce distinct verdict values.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:61:  {"id":"F-10-2","area":"benchmark","finding":"reduceRouteTelemetry emits telemetryMissingRate/routeMissRate/aliasMissRate/bundleMissRate for the legacy replay only; the planned compiledRouting block is a sibling block, not a parallel compiled.telemetryMissingRate row, so an operator reading report.advisorySignals.routeTelemetry cannot distinguish a hub whose compiled path is silently failing from one whose compiled path is healthy.","evidence":"score-skill-benchmark.cjs:745-791 (reduceRouteTelemetry operates on routerResult.routeTelemetry from line 1541); 014 spec.md:107 (compiledRouting as sibling report block, not additive routeTelemetry row)","severity":"P1","actionable":"Extend reduceRouteTelemetry to a compiledTelemetry parallel block keyed by the compiled front-door output, and surface compiledTelemetry.routeMissRate as an advisory signal so a drift never reads as a healthy legacy number.","novelty":"refines:F-3-6"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:62:  {"id":"F-10-3","area":"activation","finding":"No CLI ships a per-hub serving-status readout. 012 REQ-004 mandates it (compiled-serving | legacy-fallback | drifted) and 012 tasks.md:86 (T007) is open, but no module path exists; the seven activation manifests are only inspectable by cat'ing seven files, and compiled-route.cjs resolves (hub,prompt) -> decision rather than fleet -> status[].","evidence":"012 tasks.md:86 (T007, [ ]); .opencode/bin/ contains no compiled-status.cjs (verified via ls); advisor-status.ts:230-338 never reads activation manifests (verified by read); spec_kit_skill_advisor_status never reads activation manifests (F-8-4 prior iteration)","severity":"P0","actionable":"Ship .opencode/bin/compiled-route-status.cjs with --hub <id> and --all modes reading the seven activation manifests; emit {hubId, servingAuthority, shadowOnly, selectedPolicy.generation, effectivePolicyHash, fenceEpoch, manifestFingerprint} as a stable JSON contract that 014's compiledRouting parity lane can consume as the authoritative status probe referenced at 014 spec.md:103.","novelty":"refines:F-8-4"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:63:  {"id":"F-10-4","area":"benchmark","finding":"isHubTypeSkill (run-skill-benchmark.cjs:68-70) keys route-gold auto-on by hub-router.json file existence, NOT by compiled-eligibility (which requires entry in COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS at advisor-recommend.ts:41-49 AND a manifest at 010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json); a hub-type-but-not-compiled-eligible scenario would route-gold ENFORCED while compiledRouting auto -> off, and operators must reason about both flags to know what was scored.","evidence":"run-skill-benchmark.cjs:68-70 (isHubTypeSkill = fs.existsSync hub-router.json); advisor-recommend.ts:41-49 (COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS = {sk-code, mcp-tooling, system-deep-loop, cli-external-orchestration, sk-prompt, sk-design, sk-doc}); resolve.cjs:42 (servingAuthority derived from manifest, not hub-router.json); 014 spec.md:242 (compiledRouting flag mirrors route-gold)","severity":"P1","actionable":"Add a compiledEligibility field to routeGold.summary that explicitly distinguishes hub-type (file existence) from compiled-eligible (manifest + allowlist) so the verdict block can render 'hub-type-but-not-compiled-eligible' rather than silently scoring under either gate.","novelty":"refines:F-2-5"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:64:  {"id":"F-10-5","area":"unnamed","finding":"routeGold.gate.failed (score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1767) is the only blockable verdict that consumes a per-hub mechanism, but the planned OR-combination with compiledRouting.gate.failed in 014 will collapse three observably distinct states into one BLOCKED signal — an operator triaging a P4 rollout cannot tell route drift from manifest churn from engine throw without opening JSON, which defeats the per-hub observability 012 REQ-004 mandates.","evidence":"score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1764-1773 (verdict switch); 014 spec.md:174 (\"drift is reported, never repaired automatically\" but no distinct verdict); 012 spec.md:198 (\"drifted hub vs broken resolver: both currently read identically; P0 observability must separate degraded/expected (drift) from broken (error)\")","severity":"P0","actionable":"Encode compiledRouting state as a sub-cause of the verdict (compiled-serving | legacy-fallback-drifted | broken-compiled-path | drift-falls-back-to-legacy) and require the verdict switch to inspect compiledRouting.subVerdict BEFORE deciding BLOCKED-vs-CONDITIONAL-vs-DEGRADED; add a vitest asserting the four sub-causes produce four distinct outer verdicts.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/sk-code/manifest.json:1:{"schemaVersion":"V1","selectedPolicy":{"effectivePolicyHash":"1a42e542b2e3d2c544b456b7026de69af8f79b57c92b22945e92aef5aa3dd29c","generation":2},"servingAuthority":"compiled","shadowOnly":false}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/sk-code/manifest.prior.json:1:{"schemaVersion":"V1","selectedPolicy":{"effectivePolicyHash":null,"generation":0},"servingAuthority":"legacy","shadowOnly":true}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:8:**Headline:** Promote compiled-vs-legacy evidence as per-hub Lane C run pairs under `.opencode/skills/<hub>/benchmark/<run-label>/`; do not copy `route-gold.typed.json` or activation artifacts out of the spec tree as standalone “results.” The storage contract allows only `skill-benchmark-report.json`, its rendered `.md`, and an optional per-run `README.md` ([storage guide:120-148](.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:120-148)); the parity result therefore belongs in a report-level `compiledRouting` block, as already planned ([014 spec:132-137](.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:132-137)).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:51:1. **P0:** Add `compiledRouting` to the canonical report JSON and render it from `build-report.cjs`; do not create a separate parity report artifact. Preserve the three frozen scorer files byte-for-byte ([014 spec:89-95](.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:89-95)).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:53:3. **P0:** Record active manifest/policy hash, serving authority, route-gold source digest, topology/input digests, frozen scorer hashes, and first differing field for failures in `compiledRouting`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:59:  {"id":"F-4-1","area":"archiving","finding":"The storage contract permits only a report JSON, its rendered Markdown, and an optional README, so compiled-vs-legacy parity must be embedded in the canonical Lane C report pair rather than archived as a copied spec-tree artifact.","evidence":".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark/skill-benchmark-storage-guide.md:120-148","severity":"P0","actionable":"Add report.compiledRouting to the orchestrator JSON and render that block through build-report.cjs without editing the frozen scorer trio.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:61:  {"id":"F-4-3","area":"activation","finding":"The runtime resolves serving state from 010-live-activation while 006-parent-hub-rollout contains candidate manifests with different authority, so archiving the candidate tree can record non-serving evidence.","evidence":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs:19-20","severity":"P0","actionable":"Generate parity reports through the public front door against the active 010-live-activation manifests and store their hashes/status in compiledRouting; never treat 006 candidates as serving proof.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/sk-code/serving-flip-record.json:1:{"fenceEpoch":{"after":4,"before":3},"gate":{"canaryGreen":true,"effectivePolicyHash":"1a42e542b2e3d2c544b456b7026de69af8f79b57c92b22945e92aef5aa3dd29c","routedScenarios":1,"scorerFrozen":true,"totalScenarios":5},"hubId":"sk-code","rollbackTo":"manifest.serving-prior.json","selectedPolicy":{"effectivePolicyHash":"1a42e542b2e3d2c544b456b7026de69af8f79b57c92b22945e92aef5aa3dd29c","generation":2},"servingAuthority":"compiled","shadowOnly":false}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/sk-code/manifest.candidate.json:1:{"schemaVersion":"V1","selectedPolicy":{"effectivePolicyHash":"1a42e542b2e3d2c544b456b7026de69af8f79b57c92b22945e92aef5aa3dd29c","generation":2},"servingAuthority":"legacy","shadowOnly":true}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-014.md:8:Major potential finding — two different env var names (`n` vs `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`). Let me verify directly.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-014.md:9:Let me reconcile the grep mismatch — the file says `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` at line 362, but my earlier grep showed `process.env.n`. Re-grep precisely.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-014.md:10:The flag name is consistent (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`); my first grep was misleading. Now let me verify the kill-switch fleet-wide: where else does code assume absent=legacy? Check the bridge, launcher, and any other env-strip layers.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-014.md:31:**Kill-switch is bi-state, not tri-state.** Both read sites use exact-string `'1'` match: `resolve.cjs:23` (`process.env[FLAG] === '1'`) and `advisor-recommend.ts:362` (`process.env.SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING !== '1'`). Unset, `'0'`, `'false'`, `'off'`, `''`, `'true'`, `'yes'`, `'on'`, `'2'` ALL collapse to legacy. There is no code path that distinguishes "operator explicitly killed" (`'0'`) from "compiled routing is unset because P4 hasn't shipped" — yet 012's P4 target requires exactly that distinction. Refines F-15-3 (which flagged benchmark coverage of this gap) by naming where the production resolver itself must change.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-014.md:33:**Silent fail-safe on absent spec tree.** `compiled-route.cjs:33-38` wraps the resolver require in `try { ... } catch { route = null; }` and emits only `{ servingAuthority: 'legacy', hubId }`. The resolver path is hardcoded into the spec tree (`compiled-route.cjs:16-21`). If the spec tree is moved/deleted (e.g., during the 019-program cutover the 007 phase gets archived), the front door fails safe to legacy with NO stderr line, NO log, NO telemetry. For P4 default-on, an archived spec tree becomes an invisible fleet-wide rollback.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-014.md:37:**`.env` interaction with the launcher allowlist.** `mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:70-76` loads `.env.local` / `.env` into `process.env` at module top-level, BEFORE any spawn. `createChildEnv()` (line 267-286) then filters through `CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST` (line 99-150), which does NOT contain `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` (confirmed: zero matches). The standard operator guidance "put it in `.env`" therefore silently fails: launcher sees the flag, spawned MCP server child does not. This compounds F-5-1 (launcher allowlist) and F-8-2 (bridge allowlist) with the `.env` interaction that makes it operator-invisible.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-014.md:44:4. **P1 — Emit a stderr breadcrumb when the front door fail-safes.** One line in `compiled-route.cjs:36-38` (`process.stderr.write('compiled-route: resolver unavailable, using legacy\n')`) preserves fail-safe semantics while giving operators a fighting chance.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-014.md:46:6. **P1 — Document the `.env` strip in ENV-REFERENCE.md.** Operators need to know `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` in `.env` is invisible to the spawned advisor child until the allowlist adds it.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-014.md:53:  {"id":"F-14-4","area":"unnamed","finding":"compiled-route.cjs fails safe to a legacy sentinel on ANY resolver error including a moved or archived spec tree, with no stderr, log, or telemetry — an invisible fleet-wide rollback if 007-unified-refactor-implementation is archived during the 019 program cutover","evidence":".opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs:16-21 + 33-39","severity":"P1","actionable":"Emit a single stderr breadcrumb inside the catch block at compiled-route.cjs:36-38 (e.g. 'compiled-route: resolver unavailable for <hub>, using legacy') so operators can grep for silent fail-safes","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-014.md:55:  {"id":"F-14-6","area":"unnamed","finding":"The launcher's .env/.env.local loader (mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:70-76) runs at module top-level and injects into process.env, but createChildEnv() (line 267) filters through CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST (line 99-150) which omits SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING, so the standard 'put it in .env' operator path silently strips the flag from the spawned advisor child","evidence":".opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:70-76 + 99-150 + 267-286","severity":"P1","actionable":"Add SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING to both CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST sets (launcher line 99-150 and bridge mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs:58-87) and document the .env propagation contract in ENV-REFERENCE.md","novelty":"new"}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/sk-code/manifest.serving-prior.json:1:{"schemaVersion":"V1","selectedPolicy":{"effectivePolicyHash":"1a42e542b2e3d2c544b456b7026de69af8f79b57c92b22945e92aef5aa3dd29c","generation":2},"servingAuthority":"legacy","shadowOnly":true}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:7:- `mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs` constructs the daemon environment exclusively from `CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST`, which does not include `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`; both build helpers and the live server receive that filtered environment. A P2 canary set in the parent profile therefore does not reach the live advisor daemon (`.opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:99`, `.opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:267-270`, `.opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:1267-1271`). The environment reference already documents this propagation requirement and fresh-session adoption for another advisor flag, establishing the correct operational pattern (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/ENV-REFERENCE.md:639`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:9:- The two predicates are global checks: the advisor enriches nothing unless the process flag is exactly `1` (`.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:357-373`), while the resolver independently accepts only exact `1` before checking hub authority (`.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs:20-24`, `:40-42`). Because all seven manifests already say `servingAuthority:"compiled"`, changing absent-variable semantics activates the fleet at once, not one hub at a time (`.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/sk-code/manifest.json:1`, `activation/mcp-tooling/manifest.json:1`, `activation/system-deep-loop/manifest.json:1`, `activation/cli-external-orchestration/manifest.json:1`, `activation/sk-prompt/manifest.json:1`, `activation/sk-design/manifest.json:1`, `activation/sk-doc/manifest.json:1`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:13:- P3 must not simply delete `HUB_CHILD`. That object is both an eligibility list and the engine-location map used to load each hub’s compiler harness and router (`.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:23-31`, `:35-50`). Separate eligibility from artifact location, ideally by promoting engines/manifests to durable hub-owned paths and deriving both through one manifest index.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:27:  {"id":"F-5-1","area":"unnamed","finding":"The advisor launcher strips SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING before spawning the daemon, so a parent-profile canary cannot activate the live advisor path.","evidence":".opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:267","severity":"P0","actionable":"Add the flag to CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST and test parent-to-daemon propagation plus fresh-session adoption.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:31:  {"id":"F-5-5","area":"unnamed","finding":"HUB_CHILD is not merely a duplicated eligibility allowlist; it is also the runtime engine-location map, so removing it via manifest eligibility alone would break engine loading.","evidence":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:35","severity":"P0","actionable":"Separate eligibility from artifact location and replace both with a durable manifest index plus stable hub-owned engine paths.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-015.md:11:- The benchmark plan always forces `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`. That proves explicit opt-in, not the P4 contract where an unset variable means compiled and `=0` is the kill-switch. `.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:99-107`; `.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:130-137`; `.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:73-75`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/system-deep-loop/manifest.json:1:{"schemaVersion":"V1","selectedPolicy":{"effectivePolicyHash":"82d7f3af886d3e154da2b0f4ec01302c9266fd24ef89f30244a032d6ff77cc3c","generation":3},"servingAuthority":"compiled","shadowOnly":false}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/system-deep-loop/manifest.prior.json:1:{"schemaVersion":"V1","selectedPolicy":{"effectivePolicyHash":"82d7f3af886d3e154da2b0f4ec01302c9266fd24ef89f30244a032d6ff77cc3c","generation":3},"servingAuthority":"legacy","shadowOnly":true}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:11:- The Spec Kit catalog already has a canonical “Feature flag governance” entry and leaf (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:4480`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/governance/feature-flag-governance.md:25`). Extend those rather than creating another flag feature. Document `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, its current/default state, staged rollout, explicit kill switch, eligibility rule, drift response, and serving-status readout. Because the touched leaf currently uses an unstructured source list (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/governance/feature-flag-governance.md:49`), convert it to the template’s separate implementation and validation tables.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:15:- Durable catalog source tables must not preserve the current resolver’s spec-tree path. The front door currently imports from that mutable location (`.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs:16`), while the catalog template explicitly requires packet-history-free stable anchors (`.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/assets/feature-catalog-template.md:33`). Author the leaves only after the resolver is promoted, or point them to the stable promoted path during the same change.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:29:  {"id":"F-1-3","area":"activation","finding":"The feature-flag governance catalog must document compiled-routing polarity and rollback because the live handler directly gates enrichment on SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:362","severity":"P0","actionable":"Extend the existing system-spec-kit feature-flag-governance root entry and leaf with phased defaults, eligibility, serving status, drift behavior, and the explicit =0 kill switch.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:33:  {"id":"F-1-7","area":"unnamed","finding":"The current compiled-router source anchor is unsuitable for a durable catalog because it imports its resolver from the mutable spec tree.","evidence":".opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs:16","severity":"P0","actionable":"Promote the resolver first and make all new catalog source tables cite the stable runtime path rather than the current spec path.","novelty":"new"}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/system-deep-loop/serving-flip-record.json:1:{"fenceEpoch":{"after":3,"before":2},"gate":{"canaryGreen":true,"effectivePolicyHash":"7b5491c4500f08f14aff75736c72a292d1bd4beeadeb409548fa0dd38a8f4b94","routedScenarios":7,"scorerFrozen":true,"totalScenarios":11},"hubId":"system-deep-loop","rollbackTo":"manifest.serving-prior.json","selectedPolicy":{"effectivePolicyHash":"82d7f3af886d3e154da2b0f4ec01302c9266fd24ef89f30244a032d6ff77cc3c","generation":3},"servingAuthority":"compiled","shadowOnly":false}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/system-deep-loop/manifest.candidate.json:1:{"schemaVersion":"V1","selectedPolicy":{"effectivePolicyHash":"7b5491c4500f08f14aff75736c72a292d1bd4beeadeb409548fa0dd38a8f4b94","generation":4},"servingAuthority":"legacy","shadowOnly":true}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-011.md:9:The live assertion is insufficient for compiled routing: its prompt asks the model to state routing in JSON, then scores parsed model text and tool observations. `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:19`, `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:311` Worse, although `runDispatch` supports child-only environment overrides, `runLiveScenario` does not supply one, so `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` is only inherited opportunistically from the parent process. `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:125`, `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:363`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-011.md:15:1. Add a non-frozen compiled-route observation adapter that invokes `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` with an explicit child-only `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`, then asserts authority, action, and ordered targets against route gold.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-011.md:22:  {"id":"F-11-1","area":"playbooks","finding":"The live playbook executor never explicitly enables SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING for its child process, so a LUNA run cannot deterministically exercise the compiled path.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:363","severity":"P0","actionable":"Add a new non-frozen compiled-route adapter that spawns the public front door with child-only SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 and asserts serving authority, action, and ordered targets against route gold.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/system-deep-loop/manifest.serving-prior.json:1:{"schemaVersion":"V1","selectedPolicy":{"effectivePolicyHash":"82d7f3af886d3e154da2b0f4ec01302c9266fd24ef89f30244a032d6ff77cc3c","generation":3},"servingAuthority":"legacy","shadowOnly":true}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:17:4. The compiled-router emits a different vocabulary than the surface RESOURCE_MAP. The compiled `compiledRoute()` at `.opencode/specs/.../lib/compiled-route.cjs:73-85` returns `{ hubId, action, selectionKind, targets: <normalized qualifiedIds>, effectivePolicyHash, generation }`; the on-disk gold `.opencode/specs/.../006-parent-hub-rollout/001-sk-code/compiled/route-gold.typed.json` uses `targetQualifiedIds` like `sk-code/code-review/code-review/workflow/review-cache`. The code-opencode SKILL.md RESOURCE_MAP (lines 73-156) emits paths like `references/shared/universal-patterns/naming-and-commenting.md`. These two vocabularies share no typed-pair contract — `router-replay.cjs`'s `buildResourceContract` (lines 235-262) converts RESOURCE_MAP strings to `(workflowMode, leafResourceId)` pairs via `leaf-manifest.json` only, never via compiled output.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:19:5. The `code-opencode/benchmark/router-mode-a/skill-benchmark-report.json:342,430,518,606,694,782,870,958` reports `routeTelemetry.reason: "no-hub-router"` for every scenario — because `code-opencode` is a surface packet (no `hub-router.json`), the router-replay loads its inline RESOURCE_MAP directly rather than the hub union. The benchmark measures the surface RESOURCE_MAP in isolation; it does NOT measure the parent-hub-union contract that 015 plans to type, and it has no path to invoke `compiled-route.cjs` because the compiled router resolves at the HUB level (the spec-tree `compiled-route.cjs:23-31` `HUB_CHILD` maps hub ids to `006-parent-hub-rollout/00N-<hub>`, with no entry for surface packets).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:25:8. The advisor hook `advisor-recommend.ts:41-49` `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` Set and the spec-tree `compiled-route.cjs:23-31` `HUB_CHILD` map both enumerate the same 7 hubs (`sk-code, mcp-tooling, system-deep-loop, cli-external-orchestration, sk-prompt, sk-design, sk-doc`), but in different shapes (Set vs path map). The two are NOT cross-checked; a hub added to one but not the other causes silent drift (advisor attaches a `compiledRoute` for a hub whose compiled engine throws "unknown hub", or vice versa).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:39:2. **Cross-check the duplicated compiled-hub allowlists.** `advisor-recommend.ts:41-49` `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` (Set) and the spec-tree `compiled-route.cjs:23-31` `HUB_CHILD` (path map) should be the same set of 7 hubs. Add a Vitest in `system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/tests/handlers/` that loads the spec-tree `compiled-route.cjs` and asserts `Array.from(COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS).sort() === Object.keys(HUB_CHILD).sort()` — otherwise an advisor call can attach a `compiledRoute` field that the resolver cannot compute (or vice versa).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:43:4. **Move the compiled-router resolver from the mutable spec tree.** F-2-4 already flagged this; the recommendation to keep `compiled-route.cjs:16-21` resolving into `.opencode/specs/.../011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs` is the load-bearing risk. Action: either ship a copy of `resolve.cjs` under `.opencode/skills/sk-code/` (or a sibling `.opencode/lib/`) and have `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` resolve there, OR add a Vitest that fails when the resolver path does not begin with `.opencode/skills/` (rejects the spec tree). The 015 spec at line 91-99 needs this stability before its Phase 5 live-mode sample runs.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:51:  {"id":"F-6-3","area":"unnamed","finding":"Two duplicated allowlists for the same 7 compiled-serving hubs (`advisor-recommend.ts:41-49` COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS Set vs spec-tree `compiled-route.cjs:23-31` HUB_CHILD map) have no cross-check; an 8th hub added to one but not the other causes the advisor to attach a `compiledRoute` field the resolver cannot compute, or vice versa.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:41-49 vs .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:23-31","severity":"P1","actionable":"Add a Vitest in `system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/tests/handlers/advisor-recommend.vitest.ts` that requires the spec-tree's `compiled-route.cjs` and asserts `Array.from(COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS).sort().join(',') === Object.keys(require(...).HUB_CHILD).sort().join(',')`. Fail with P0 message naming the diverging hub. Add the same check to the existing 014-benchmark-alignment parity harness.","novelty":"new"},
