.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:6:The advisor-hook machine-enforcement layer named in 011-runtime-engine/implementation-summary.md:23,111,147 as "in progress / NOT done" is structurally prevented from happening by **two separate compiledRoute-strip layers** (bridge `buildNativeBrief` + plugin `brief` consumption) AND by **two separate SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING-strip allowlists** (launcher + bridge), neither of which is documented in `ENV-REFERENCE.md`. None of the 5 non-hub single-skill routers carry a compiled-routing directive or an explicit "ineligible by design" clause, and the 009 Phase Map is incomplete (3 of 4 children unlisted, mcp-code-mode missing entirely). Combined, even a P4 hub-by-hub flip with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` exported through `opencode.json` cannot reach the compiled router from a Claude/Codex/OpenCode runtime that calls the MCP path.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:11:- `system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:357-374` — `enrichCompiledRoutes` attaches `compiledRoute` per recommendation when `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING === '1'`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:16:**SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING-strip, layer 2 — bridge CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST also excludes it.**
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:17:- `.opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:99-150` — launcher's allowlist; F-5-1 confirmed `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is absent.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:19:- `system-spec-kit/mcp-server/ENV-REFERENCE.md` — `grep -n "SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING"` returns zero hits. The flag is **undocumented** in the env reference, so operators have no authoritative list of which variables need forwarding and which get stripped.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:22:- `system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:332-345` — `compiledRouteForRecommendation` uses `execFileSync(process.execPath, [...compiled-route.cjs, --hub, skillId, --prompt, prompt], { timeout: 5_000, maxBuffer: 1_048_576 })`. With topK=3 recommendations and 7 COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS, **up to 3 fresh Node process spawns per `advisor_recommend` call**. Each spawn re-resolves the resolver from the spec tree (per F-2-4), reads the activation manifest, and runs the hub's canary/plain router. No in-process cache, no batching, no concurrency limit.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:26:- `system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-status.ts` — `grep -n "servingAuthority"` returns zero hits. `advisor_status` reports freshness/trustState/generation but never reads `010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:27:- The 7 manifests (`specs/.../010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json`, e.g. `sk-code/manifest.json:1` = `{"servingAuthority":"compiled","shadowOnly":false,...}`) are consumed only by the resolver at hot-path time (`resolve.cjs:26-34`). No observability surface ships a "hub X is currently compiled-serving" read to an operator. ADR-002's data-driven eligibility needs that readout to confirm the derived predicate; today the only way to learn a hub's state is to run `flip-serving.cjs --status` (CLI-only).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:30:- 5 single-skill routers exist (`sk-git/SKILL.md:39` smart-router; `system-spec-kit/SKILL.md:95` registry-less; `mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md:71` standalone single-mode; `system-code-graph/SKILL.md:98` singleton-mode; `system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:87` standalone single-mode). All 5 are absent from `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` (`advisor-recommend.ts:41-49`) and absent from `HUB_CHILD` (`specs/.../011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:23-31`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:35:- The only path from the prompt to the compiled router is: prompt → `mk-skill-advisor.js:824` `appendAdvisorBrief` → bridge subprocess → `mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs:519` `handleAdvisorRecommend` → `advisor-recommend.ts:362` `enrichCompiledRoutes` → `compiledRouteForRecommendation` (line 326-355) → `compiled-route.cjs:39` legacy sentinel on any drift. This 6-hop chain **discards compiledRoute at hop 5** (bridge rebuild), so even if every gate fires, the model sees only the legacy brief text — never the compiled decision. There is no second consumer of `compiledRoute` in the tree (`grep -rn "compiledRoute" .opencode/` returns only the resolver, the engine, the schema, the enricher).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:39:1. **(P0, advisor-hook thread)** Either (a) thread `compiledRoute` through `buildNativeBrief.metadata` as a top-level summary (so the plugin's existing metadata path picks it up — `mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs:97-99` already preserves `metadata`), AND add `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` to both `mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:99-150` and `mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs:58-87` allowlists; or (b) downgrade the implementation-summary claim and treat the compiled router as unreachable from the prompt until both layers are patched. F-3-3's gap is necessary but not sufficient — the bridge strip and the launcher/bridge env strip must both be fixed before the model can observe compiled routing.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:40:2. **(P0, observability)** Add an `advisor_status` field or a dedicated `compiled_routing_status` MCP tool that reads `010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json` for each hub and reports `{hubId, servingAuthority, generation, manifestMtime}`. Without it, ADR-002's data-driven eligibility has no operator-visible readout.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:41:3. **(P0, governance docs)** Add `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` to `system-spec-kit/mcp-server/ENV-REFERENCE.md` with default OFF, daemon-propagation caveat (must reach the MCP-server child — currently stripped by launcher + bridge allowlists), and per-hub override semantics.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:49:  {"id":"F-8-2","area":"activation","finding":"The bridge's `CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST` (mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs:58-87) also lacks `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, so the CLI fallback path (`buildCliBrief` → `runCliRecommend` at line 672-735) spawns a child without the flag even if the parent set it; this is a second env-strip layer beyond the launcher strip already documented in F-5-1.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/plugin-bridges/mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs:58-87,210-214,672-735","severity":"P0","actionable":"Add `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` to the bridge allowlist at line 58-87 alongside the other `SPECKIT_ADVISOR_*` entries so the CLI subprocess can read the flag; verify the in-process native path also reads it (it does at line 459 via `env[DISABLED_ENV]` pattern).","novelty":"refines:F-5-1"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:50:  {"id":"F-8-3","area":"activation","finding":"`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is not documented in `system-spec-kit/mcp-server/ENV-REFERENCE.md` despite being a load-bearing runtime flag with default-OFF/ON semantics and per-hub interaction — operators have no authoritative reference and no propagation guidance.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/ENV-REFERENCE.md (zero hits for SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING)","severity":"P0","actionable":"Add an entry with default=OFF, type=boolean, source `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs:10` and `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:362`, plus a propagation note that both the launcher and bridge allowlists must include it (per F-8-2).","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:51:  {"id":"F-8-4","area":"unnamed","finding":"No observability surface ships a per-hub serving-authority readout: `spec_kit_skill_advisor_status` (mk-skill-advisor.js:826-861) and `advisor_status` (handlers/advisor-status.ts) never read the 7 manifests at `.opencode/specs/.../010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json`, so ADR-002's data-driven eligibility has no operator-visible verification channel.","evidence":".opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js:826-861; .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-status.ts (zero hits for servingAuthority); .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/sk-code/manifest.json:1","severity":"P0","actionable":"Add a `compiled_routing_status` MCP tool (or extend `advisor_status` with a `compiledRouting.hubs: [{hubId, servingAuthority, generation, manifestMtime}]` field) that reads each hub's manifest via the same canonical ACTIVATION_ROOT path resolve.cjs:19 uses.","novelty":"refines:F-3-6"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:52:  {"id":"F-8-5","area":"benchmark","finding":"`enrichCompiledRoutes` invokes `execFileSync` per recommendation (advisor-recommend.ts:332-345) — up to 3 fresh Node process spawns per advisor_recommend call with 5s timeout, no batching, no in-process cache — compounding the F-2-4 spec-tree resolver cost on the hot path.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:326-345","severity":"P1","actionable":"Either add a `--multi --hubs <csv>` mode to compiled-route.cjs that batches per prompt, or import the resolver in-process (after ADR-003 promotion to `.opencode/bin/lib/`), or memoize compiledRoute results per (hubId, prompt) per process with a short TTL.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:3:description: "Design-faithful fenced-CAS activation of all seven hubs: selectedPolicy bound to the compiled generation, byte-exact rollback proven, scorer frozen. P4b cutover complete in 011-runtime-engine (all 7 hubs flipped legacy->compiled, inert behind the default-off SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flag)."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:23:| **Status** | Complete — P4a design-faithful activation + T9 real-model verification (0 wrong-hub routes) complete for all 7 hubs, and the P4b cutover (`011-runtime-engine`) is complete: all 7 hubs flipped `legacy → compiled`, inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, byte-exact rollback retained. Advisor-hook machine-enforcement remains in progress |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:26:| **Serving authority** | `compiled` (committed) — P4a bound the compiled generation as `selectedPolicy` with legacy serving; the sibling P4b flip (`011`) advanced all 7 manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:36:A phase-local **activation layer** with one shared, zero-dependency driver, `lib/activate-hub.cjs`. The driver binds each hub's compiled policy generation as the `selectedPolicy` on a dedicated per-hub activation manifest via a fenced compare-and-swap, advancing a monotonic fence epoch, while `servingAuthority` stays `legacy`. It seeds its manifests byte-for-byte from each hub's shadow rollout child (so the completed canary children are never mutated), refuses to run unless the child's canary is green and the three frozen scorer files match their pinned digests, and proves a byte-exact rollback in a scope-validated temp dir on every run.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:38:This is the design-faithful reading of activation: the compiled contract becomes the *accepted, bound* generation; at P4a bind time legacy kept *serving* because no runtime consumer existed yet. The genuine runtime change — a resolver that reads `selectedPolicy` plus a `servingAuthority` flip — is now complete in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`: all seven hubs are flipped `legacy → compiled`, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag (route-gold ROUTING byte-identical — only hashes changed), with a byte-identical legacy manifest retained per hub for a byte-exact rollback.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:56:Per hub, the driver runs six steps. (1) **Frozen-scorer gate** — re-hash the three shared scorer files (`router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`) and abort on any drift from the pinned digests. (2) **Canary gate** — execute the child's `harness/validate-canary.cjs`; a non-zero exit (route-gold not GREEN, rollback not pass, serving-authority not legacy, or protected-digest drift) aborts. (3) **Seed** — byte-for-byte copy the child's prior + candidate manifests into `activation/<hub>/`, verifying the seeded prior hash equals the accepted `priorManifestHash` and the candidate `selectedPolicy` equals the accepted `candidatePolicy`. (4) **Fenced CAS ship** — assert the serving manifest's `selectedPolicy` equals the expected prior generation at the expected fence epoch (compare), then write the candidate bytes into `manifest.json` and advance the fence epoch (swap), with `servingAuthority` staying `legacy`. (5) **Rollback proof** — in a scope-validated temp dir, restore the prior manifest and assert the restored hash is byte-exact against `priorManifestHash` and `selectedPolicy` reverts to the prior generation, never disturbing the committed activated state. (6) **Record** — emit `activation/<hub>/activation-record.json`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:70:| Bind `selectedPolicy` while `servingAuthority` stays `legacy` | Faithful to the design of record: an activation-pointer CAS never edits a serving policy, and no runtime consumer of the compiled contract exists yet. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:75:| Bound real-model verification (T9) to a sample; then execute the P4b flip behind a flag | T9 ran 2 authentic playbook prompts per hub × 3 models × 2 runs — bounded but real (0 wrong-hub routes). The serving-authority flip is the only stage that changes runtime routing; it was executed in `011` one-hub-at-a-time behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag and stays reversible (per-hub serving-prior or fleet-wide flag off). |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:84:All seven hubs, in activation order, returned `ACTIVATION BOUND … serving=legacy shadowOnly=true fence=0->1 rollback.byteExact=true scorerFrozen=true canaryGreen=true` at P4a bind time; the sibling P4b flip (`011`) then advanced all seven to `servingAuthority: compiled`, `shadowOnly: false` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag (each flip canary-green via the real scorer, route-gold ROUTING byte-identical, byte-exact rollback retained):
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:110:2. **The P4b literal cutover (T16-T17) is complete.** The runtime resolver that consumes `selectedPolicy` and the `servingAuthority` `legacy → compiled` flip — the only stage that changes runtime routing — were delivered in the sibling `011-runtime-engine` (commits engine `d7da0fca43`, sk-code cutover `2fa3357f80`, remaining-6 cutover `337ca43cfa`, pushed on v4). All 7 hubs are flipped, each canary-green via the real scorer with a byte-exact rollback retained; the path is inert by default (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` off) and reversible per-hub or fleet-wide. The advisor-hook machine-enforcement layer that would machine-enforce the wired routing remains in progress.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:119:    current_focus: "P4a complete (7/7 hubs bound + byte-exact rollback + T9 real-model verification, 0 wrong-hub routes); P4b cutover complete in 011-runtime-engine — all 7 hubs flipped legacy->compiled (servingAuthority: compiled), held inert behind the default-off SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flag (route-gold byte-identical), byte-exact rollback retained per hub"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:122:      - "Enablement is operator-gated: set SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 to serve compiled (routing byte-identical); reversible per-hub (flip-serving --rollback) or fleet-wide (flag off)"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/008-fleet-cleanup/plan.md:36:  - **Evidence**: all four committed selectors are `servingAuthority:"legacy"`, `shadowOnly:true`, generation `0`, hash `5485c5a4...`; `system-deep-loop` also reports `shadow-partial` route-gold.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:8:- **Current Reality before P4:** “Compiled routing is additive and opt-in with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`; legacy remains authoritative when disabled or when the compiled front door returns its legacy sentinel.” This matches every current hub directive, including `sk-prompt` and `cli-external-orchestration` (`.opencode/skills/sk-prompt/SKILL.md:36-40`, `.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/SKILL.md:41-45`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:9:- **Current Reality after that hub’s P4 cutover:** “Compiled routing is the default authority for a fresh eligible manifest. `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` is the fleet kill-switch; missing or stale eligibility routes to the classified legacy fallback.” The planned observable states are `compiled-serving`, `legacy-fallback`, and `drifted` (`.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:98-107`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:13:The per-feature file should be `routing-and-activation/compiled-hub-routing.md`, titled `Compiled Hub Routing`, with H1 `# Compiled Hub Routing (compiled-route.cjs)`. Use three short `HOW IT WORKS` paragraphs: core routing outcome, activation/rollback, then status/failure classification. Its required implementation table, validation table, metadata, and root-entry linkage follow `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:274-305`. Use hub-qualified triggers such as `"<hub> compiled hub routing"`, `"<hub> compiled route"`, and `"SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING <hub>"`.
