.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:20:A "compiled skill-router" is BUILT and SHIPPED but held INERT behind the default-OFF env flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`. When ON, the live advisor attaches the compiled decision as ADDITIVE metadata (`system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:371`) to a recommendation the legacy path already computed; it changes ZERO routing decisions (compiled is byte-identical to legacy) and fails safe to a legacy sentinel on any drift (`.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs:36-39`). The runtime front door resolves its resolver from a path INSIDE the spec tree (`compiled-route.cjs:16-21` → `.../007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`). The eligibility allowlist is duplicated (`advisor-recommend.ts` `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` + `compiled-route.cjs` `HUB_CHILD`). This session added decision packet `012-default-on-decision` (ruling: adopt a phased path to default-on) and alignment PLANS `013-create-skill-alignment` + `014-benchmark-alignment` (both authored, not implemented) under `.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:32:- Router runtime: `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs`; `.../011-runtime-engine/lib/`; `system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:70:- F-10-1 [benchmark/P0] The Lane C verdict enum has no degraded/expected slot for drift-to-legacy fallback, so the new compiledRouting parity gate will collapse three observably distinct states (compiled-serving-with-route-gold-violation, drifted-legacy-fallback, broken-resolver) into one BLOCKED signal — directly violating 012 REQ-004 which mandates drift be scored as degraded/expected.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:71:- F-10-2 [benchmark/P1] reduceRouteTelemetry emits telemetryMissingRate/routeMissRate/aliasMissRate/bundleMissRate for the legacy replay only; the planned compiledRouting block is a sibling block, not a parallel compiled.telemetryMissingRate row, so an operator reading report.advisorySignals.routeTelemetry cannot distinguish a hub whose compiled path is silently failing from one whose compiled path is healthy.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:72:- F-10-3 [activation/P0] No CLI ships a per-hub serving-status readout. 012 REQ-004 mandates it (compiled-serving | legacy-fallback | drifted) and 012 tasks.md:86 (T007) is open, but no module path exists; the seven activation manifests are only inspectable by cat'ing seven files, and compiled-route.cjs resolves (hub,prompt) -> decision rather than fleet -> status[].
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:73:- F-10-4 [benchmark/P1] isHubTypeSkill (run-skill-benchmark.cjs:68-70) keys route-gold auto-on by hub-router.json file existence, NOT by compiled-eligibility (which requires entry in COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS at advisor-recommend.ts:41-49 AND a manifest at 010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json); a hub-type-but-not-compiled-eligible scenario would route-gold ENFORCED while compiledRouting auto -> off, and operators must reason about both flags to know what was scored.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:74:- F-10-5 [unnamed/P0] routeGold.gate.failed (score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1767) is the only blockable verdict that consumes a per-hub mechanism, but the planned OR-combination with compiledRouting.gate.failed in 014 will collapse three observably distinct states into one BLOCKED signal — an operator triaging a P4 rollout cannot tell route drift from manifest churn from engine throw without opening JSON, which defeats the per-hub observability 012 REQ-004 mandates.
