.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:2519:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:80:Derive both eligibility consumers from the manifest-freshness rule already owned by `decision-record.md`, then stage the global default one hub at a time while preserving `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:2527:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:3:description: "Three decisions governing whether and how SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING becomes the repo's effective default: defer global default-on to a staged P4 outcome, single-source compiled eligibility to a valid fresh manifest, and remediate the runtime-to-spec-tree resolver coupling."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:2548:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:3:description: "Settle whether SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING should become the repo's effective default and, if so, on what safe path. The compiled router is built, wired, and inert behind a default-off flag: the P4b flip already moved all seven hubs' manifests to servingAuthority: compiled, and the live advisor consumes them only when the flag is 1, only for hubs in a hardcoded allowlist, and even then attaches the compiled decision as ADDITIVE metadata that never changes which skill is recommended. This phase records the decision — default-on is a Phase-4 OUTCOME, not a switch-flip — and specifies the four contracts that make an eventual global default-on safe and reversible: (P0) document the flag in ENV-REFERENCE and make the verify harness distinguish drift-to-legacy from breakage plus a per-hub serving-status readout; (P1) a drift-detection CI that recomputes each hub's live hash against its minted manifest and fails 're-mint required'; (P2) a canary default-on in one env profile with the repo default staying off; (P3) a data-driven eligibility rule (compiled-eligible IFF a valid fresh manifest exists) that single-sources the duplicated allowlist and makes no-manifest skills legacy by construction; (P4) a staged, hub-by-hub global default-on that flips the two code predicates and the seven SKILL.md directives in lockstep while keeping =0 as the documented kill-switch. The frozen benchmark scorer is never touched and every step is byte-exact reversible."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:2552:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:44:The compiled skill-router is built, hardened, wired into the live advisor, and **inert behind a default-off flag**. The sibling P4b work (`011-runtime-engine`) already flipped all seven hubs' activation manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`; what remains gated is whether the runtime *consumes* that state, and that gate is `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`. The parent goal asks to make compiled routing "the effective default."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:2559:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:106:- Actually flipping `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` to a repo default in this phase — [why] this phase decides and contracts; the flip is the P4 execution phase, gated on P0–P3 landing green.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:2567:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:180:- **NFR-R01**: Every step P0→P4 names an explicit rollback; the P4 global default-on keeps `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the documented, load-bearing kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:2568:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:202:- `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` after P4 default-on: must fully restore legacy serving fleet-wide, documented as the kill-switch, not an incidental default.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:2571:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:240:- **Q1 (resolved).** The ruling is settled: adopt the phased path (default-on as a staged P4 outcome after P0–P3), decided on the analysis and reversible. An operator override to flip `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` on now remains available but is not blocking; the steelman for flipping now is recorded in `decision-record.md` ("flip it when compiled does something legacy can't").
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:2587:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:178:- [ ] P4: exercise `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch and retain per-hub manifest rollback.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-019.err:3882:  {"id":"F-19-3","area":"activation","finding":"Catalog current-reality wording cannot claim default-on before P4 because the shipped advisor still enables enrichment only when SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING equals 1.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:362-371","severity":"P0","actionable":"Land opt-in additive wording before cutover and make the default-on plus explicit-zero kill-switch wording a P4 lockstep edit.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/008-fleet-cleanup/compiled/final-manifest.json:1:{"bakeWindow":{"discardAuthorized":false,"minimumSuccessfulDeletions":4},"dualReadSkillIds":[],"generation":8,"legacyInputs":[],"policyPins":[{"activationGeneration":1,"effectivePolicyHash":"663c356a3dc72455a25f391a1d97767ace28de911c91b3b70ab4ef91bb37ce9f","skillId":"mcp-code-mode"},{"activationGeneration":2,"effectivePolicyHash":"1dbf295d4608886358137f2a7541778629982db8583f0023e25dffcb2ee9d476","skillId":"sk-code"},{"activationGeneration":3,"effectivePolicyHash":"82d7f3af886d3e154da2b0f4ec01302c9266fd24ef89f30244a032d6ff77cc3c","skillId":"system-deep-loop"},{"activationGeneration":4,"effectivePolicyHash":"dba007a997945fb54b899a142d49ef158a6f8adefe1bd4b18486e1e0799652b3","skillId":"mcp-tooling"}],"preflightDigest":"837149fc80fdb33399ccc560411643243326680e376b2a18dfaf501f20535d9a","resolver":"EffectivePolicy","retiredSkillIds":["mcp-code-mode","sk-code","system-deep-loop","mcp-tooling"],"schemaVersion":"V1","selectedPolicyHash":"97fb6ad2233cd3ce38c9bd1606996c135871da0b9238994ac5c452ce471bc281","servingAuthority":"compiled","soleResolver":true}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/008-fleet-cleanup/implementation-summary.md:24:| Committed selectors | Four manifests at `servingAuthority:"legacy"`, `shadowOnly:true`, generation `0` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:20:A "compiled skill-router" is BUILT and SHIPPED but held INERT behind the default-OFF env flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`. When ON, the live advisor attaches the compiled decision as ADDITIVE metadata (`system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:371`) to a recommendation the legacy path already computed; it changes ZERO routing decisions (compiled is byte-identical to legacy) and fails safe to a legacy sentinel on any drift (`.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs:36-39`). The runtime front door resolves its resolver from a path INSIDE the spec tree (`compiled-route.cjs:16-21` → `.../007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`). The eligibility allowlist is duplicated (`advisor-recommend.ts` `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` + `compiled-route.cjs` `HUB_CHILD`). This session added decision packet `012-default-on-decision` (ruling: adopt a phased path to default-on) and alignment PLANS `013-create-skill-alignment` + `014-benchmark-alignment` (both authored, not implemented) under `.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:32:- Router runtime: `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs`; `.../011-runtime-engine/lib/`; `system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:62:- F-11-1 [playbooks/P0] The live playbook executor never explicitly enables SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING for its child process, so a LUNA run cannot deterministically exercise the compiled path.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:72:- F-8-2 [activation/P0] The bridge's `CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST` (mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs:58-87) also lacks `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, so the CLI fallback path (`buildCliBrief` → `runCliRecommend` at line 672-735) spawns a child without the flag even if the parent set it; this is a second env-strip layer beyond the launcher strip already documented in F-5-1.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:73:- F-8-3 [activation/P0] `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is not documented in `system-spec-kit/mcp-server/ENV-REFERENCE.md` despite being a load-bearing runtime flag with default-OFF/ON semantics and per-hub interaction — operators have no authoritative reference and no propagation guidance.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:90:- F-10-1 [benchmark/P0] The Lane C verdict enum has no degraded/expected slot for drift-to-legacy fallback, so the new compiledRouting parity gate will collapse three observably distinct states (compiled-serving-with-route-gold-violation, drifted-legacy-fallback, broken-resolver) into one BLOCKED signal — directly violating 012 REQ-004 which mandates drift be scored as degraded/expected.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:91:- F-10-2 [benchmark/P1] reduceRouteTelemetry emits telemetryMissingRate/routeMissRate/aliasMissRate/bundleMissRate for the legacy replay only; the planned compiledRouting block is a sibling block, not a parallel compiled.telemetryMissingRate row, so an operator reading report.advisorySignals.routeTelemetry cannot distinguish a hub whose compiled path is silently failing from one whose compiled path is healthy.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:92:- F-10-3 [activation/P0] No CLI ships a per-hub serving-status readout. 012 REQ-004 mandates it (compiled-serving | legacy-fallback | drifted) and 012 tasks.md:86 (T007) is open, but no module path exists; the seven activation manifests are only inspectable by cat'ing seven files, and compiled-route.cjs resolves (hub,prompt) -> decision rather than fleet -> status[].
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:93:- F-10-4 [benchmark/P1] isHubTypeSkill (run-skill-benchmark.cjs:68-70) keys route-gold auto-on by hub-router.json file existence, NOT by compiled-eligibility (which requires entry in COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS at advisor-recommend.ts:41-49 AND a manifest at 010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json); a hub-type-but-not-compiled-eligible scenario would route-gold ENFORCED while compiledRouting auto -> off, and operators must reason about both flags to know what was scored.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:94:- F-10-5 [unnamed/P0] routeGold.gate.failed (score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1767) is the only blockable verdict that consumes a per-hub mechanism, but the planned OR-combination with compiledRouting.gate.failed in 014 will collapse three observably distinct states into one BLOCKED signal — an operator triaging a P4 rollout cannot tell route drift from manifest churn from engine throw without opening JSON, which defeats the per-hub observability 012 REQ-004 mandates.
