.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:6806:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:221:- **Procedure**: Stop the stage; set `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` for fleet-wide legacy serving; restore the affected hub's retained prior manifest when a per-hub pointer changed; restore the prior resolver location or temporary eligibility constants when those components caused the failure; rerun the status and parity gates before resuming.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:6822:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:285:1. Set `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` and verify fleet-wide legacy serving.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:6876:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/tasks.md:84:- [ ] T005 Document `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` in `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, including default-off behavior, explicit enablement, and `=0` kill-switch semantics. (REQ-005; environment reference) {deps: T002, T004}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:6920:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/plan.md:138:- [ ] Add `report.compiledRouting` and distinct verdict/exit handling without changing the score aggregate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:6961:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:80:Derive both eligibility consumers from the manifest-freshness rule already owned by `decision-record.md`, then stage the global default one hub at a time while preserving `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7049:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:3:description: "Plan the Lane C harness changes that exercise the compiled router with SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1, compare its normalized routing decisions with legacy router replay and the same authored route gold, and classify manifest drift separately from compiled-path breakage without editing the three frozen scorer files."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7054:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:25:Lane C currently benchmarks deterministic routing through `router-replay.cjs`, joins the observed result to authored route gold, and scores it through `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`. The orchestrator never turns on `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, never invokes the compiled front door, and never compares the compiled decision with the legacy replay. A hub can therefore pass the benchmark while the path intended to serve under the compiled flag is stale, falling back, or broken.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7060:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:54:The existing seam is suitable for an additive parity lane: `router-replay.cjs` returns legacy intents/resources and hub telemetry; `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` returns the flag-gated compiled decision or a legacy sentinel; `score-skill-benchmark.cjs` already exports the route-gold evaluator. The missing piece is normalization and comparison around those unchanged modules.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7062:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:73:- Child-process invocation of `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` for eligible hubs so the real public flag-gated path is exercised.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7075:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:115:| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/build-report.cjs` | Modify | Render the `compiledRouting` block from report JSON |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7082:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:133:| REQ-002 | Exercise the real compiled-serving path with the flag on. | Eligible hub scenarios invoke `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` in a child process with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`; the report records `flagForcedOn: true` and the front-door outcome. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7084:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:136:| REQ-005 | Integrate parity as a Lane C gate without changing D1-D5. | `report.compiledRouting` contains mode, eligible rows, parity counts, drift rows, breakages, and frozen hashes; routing divergence or breakage produces a distinct blocked verdict and non-zero exit, while drift remains visibly classified according to the authoritative contract. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7157:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:3:description: "Settle whether SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING should become the repo's effective default and, if so, on what safe path. The compiled router is built, wired, and inert behind a default-off flag: the P4b flip already moved all seven hubs' manifests to servingAuthority: compiled, and the live advisor consumes them only when the flag is 1, only for hubs in a hardcoded allowlist, and even then attaches the compiled decision as ADDITIVE metadata that never changes which skill is recommended. This phase records the decision — default-on is a Phase-4 OUTCOME, not a switch-flip — and specifies the four contracts that make an eventual global default-on safe and reversible: (P0) document the flag in ENV-REFERENCE and make the verify harness distinguish drift-to-legacy from breakage plus a per-hub serving-status readout; (P1) a drift-detection CI that recomputes each hub's live hash against its minted manifest and fails 're-mint required'; (P2) a canary default-on in one env profile with the repo default staying off; (P3) a data-driven eligibility rule (compiled-eligible IFF a valid fresh manifest exists) that single-sources the duplicated allowlist and makes no-manifest skills legacy by construction; (P4) a staged, hub-by-hub global default-on that flips the two code predicates and the seven SKILL.md directives in lockstep while keeping =0 as the documented kill-switch. The frozen benchmark scorer is never touched and every step is byte-exact reversible."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7159:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:6:  - "SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flip default"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7165:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:44:The compiled skill-router is built, hardened, wired into the live advisor, and **inert behind a default-off flag**. The sibling P4b work (`011-runtime-engine`) already flipped all seven hubs' activation manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`; what remains gated is whether the runtime *consumes* that state, and that gate is `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`. The parent goal asks to make compiled routing "the effective default."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7173:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:76:2. **Silent drift is the steady state.** The serve-time shim recomputes the decision from live hub config; on any mismatch, missing resolver, or error it emits a `{ servingAuthority: "legacy" }` sentinel (`compiled-route.cjs:36-39`), which the advisor maps to `undefined` (`advisor-recommend.ts:351`). Any edit to a hub's `SKILL.md`/router config reverts that hub to legacy invisibly until its manifest is re-minted. This repo churns hub config constantly, so "compiled" would spend much of its life silently on legacy.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7175:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:78:4. **Undocumented flag = governance violation.** `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is absent from `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, which the project constitution (CLAUDE.md §6) mandates as the source of truth for flag defaults. Flipping an undocumented flag violates that mandate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7177:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:81:A sixth, structural fragility (found this phase, under-weighted in prior handovers): the runtime front door `bin/compiled-route.cjs` resolves its resolver from a path **inside the spec tree** (`compiled-route.cjs:16-21` → `007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`). A spec renumber/re-nest silently breaks every compiled route to the legacy sentinel — the repo's own reorganization is a drift engine.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7184:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:106:- Actually flipping `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` to a repo default in this phase — [why] this phase decides and contracts; the flip is the P4 execution phase, gated on P0–P3 landing green.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7191:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:131:| REQ-002 | Specify the fallback contract precisely and single-sourced. | The contract defines that a hub is compiled-served IFF a valid, fresh manifest exists AND `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND the hub is eligible; every other state resolves to the legacy sentinel with no behavior change. The eligibility predicate is named as the single source both `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` must derive from (delivered in P3). |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7205:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:167:| Risk | Duplicated allowlist diverges | `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` drift apart, mis-gating hubs | P3 single-sources eligibility to "valid fresh manifest exists"; both predicates derive from it |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7209:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:180:- **NFR-R01**: Every step P0→P4 names an explicit rollback; the P4 global default-on keeps `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the documented, load-bearing kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7216:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:202:- `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` after P4 default-on: must fully restore legacy serving fleet-wide, documented as the kill-switch, not an incidental default.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7226:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:240:- **Q1 (resolved).** The ruling is settled: adopt the phased path (default-on as a staged P4 outcome after P0–P3), decided on the analysis and reversible. An operator override to flip `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` on now remains available but is not blocking; the steelman for flipping now is recorded in `decision-record.md` ("flip it when compiled does something legacy can't").
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7248:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:93:> **Compiled routing (opt-in, flag-gated, additive).** When `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`, resolve the mode via the compiled router contract first:
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7249:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:97:> Follow the returned decision — `route` (use its `targets`), `clarify`/`defer` (disambiguate), `reject` (refuse). On a `{"servingAuthority":"legacy"}` sentinel or any error, use the routing below. The front door self-gates on serving authority, and the flag is **off by default**, so this is inert until compiled routing is activated for `{{HUB_NAME}}`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7273:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:3:description: "Three decisions governing whether and how SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING becomes the repo's effective default: defer global default-on to a staged P4 outcome, single-source compiled eligibility to a valid fresh manifest, and remediate the runtime-to-spec-tree resolver coupling."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7280:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:55:The parent goal asks to make compiled routing the effective default, framing it as flipping `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` from off to on. Reading the live integration point shows that framing buys nothing and costs real surface. The advisor enters compiled routing only through `enrichCompiledRoutes()` at `advisor-recommend.ts:357`. With the flag unset that function returns its input untouched (`:362`). With the flag set it maps over recommendations the legacy path already computed and attaches `compiledRoute` as an additive sibling field, `{ ...recommendation, compiledRoute }` at `:371`, and never recomputes the chosen `skillId` or `workflowMode`. Turning the flag on can only make that extra field appear or, on drift, silently not appear. It cannot change which skill is recommended.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7281:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:57:The sibling `011-runtime-engine` already flipped all seven hubs' manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`, held inert behind the default-off flag. So the destination machinery exists. What does not exist is the reason to flip: today the flip is behavior-neutral by construction.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7283:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:63:- `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is absent from `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, which CLAUDE.md section 6 mandates as the source of truth for flag defaults. Flipping an undocumented flag violates that mandate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7284:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:64:- The serve-time shim recomputes each hub's decision from live config and falls back to a `{ servingAuthority: "legacy" }` sentinel on any mismatch (`compiled-route.cjs:36-39`), which the advisor maps to `undefined` (`advisor-recommend.ts:351`). Editing a hub reverts it to legacy until re-minted, with nothing to observe the reversion.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7301:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:145:**How to roll back**: Nothing in this phase changes runtime behavior, so there is nothing to roll back here. Across the program, `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` restores legacy serving fleet-wide, and each per-hub flip retains a byte-identical prior manifest for a byte-exact per-hub revert.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7303:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:168:Which hubs are compiled-eligible is hardcoded in two places: `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` in `advisor-recommend.ts:41` and `HUB_CHILD` in `compiled-route.cjs:23`. Two hand-maintained lists drift apart. A newly created skill is compiled-invisible with no defined way to opt in, and `create-skill` today has zero compiled-routing awareness (a repo grep for compiled-routing tokens under the create-skill mode returns nothing).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7306:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:247:- P3: a single eligibility predicate keyed on manifest freshness; `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` become derived, then removed as hand-authored constants.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7309:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:273:The runtime front door `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` resolves its resolver from a path inside the spec tree: `compiled-route.cjs:16-21` points at `007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`. This repo renumbers and re-nests spec folders constantly (the memory index records repeated hyphen migrations, renumbers, and re-nests). A single such move silently breaks every compiled route to the legacy sentinel, with no observable signal. The repo's own reorganization is a latent drift engine independent of hub-config edits.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7371:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/tasks.md:55:- [ ] T012 Add `report.compiledRouting`, distinct gate/verdict handling, and process signal behavior. (REQ-005) {deps: T011}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7385:     3	description: "Settle whether SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING should become the repo's effective default and, if so, on what safe path. The compiled router is built, wired, and inert behind a default-off flag: the P4b flip already moved all seven hubs' manifests to servingAuthority: compiled, and the live advisor consumes them only when the flag is 1, only for hubs in a hardcoded allowlist, and even then attaches the compiled decision as ADDITIVE metadata that never changes which skill is recommended. This phase records the decision — default-on is a Phase-4 OUTCOME, not a switch-flip — and specifies the four contracts that make an eventual global default-on safe and reversible: (P0) document the flag in ENV-REFERENCE and make the verify harness distinguish drift-to-legacy from breakage plus a per-hub serving-status readout; (P1) a drift-detection CI that recomputes each hub's live hash against its minted manifest and fails 're-mint required'; (P2) a canary default-on in one env profile with the repo default staying off; (P3) a data-driven eligibility rule (compiled-eligible IFF a valid fresh manifest exists) that single-sources the duplicated allowlist and makes no-manifest skills legacy by construction; (P4) a staged, hub-by-hub global default-on that flips the two code predicates and the seven SKILL.md directives in lockstep while keeping =0 as the documented kill-switch. The frozen benchmark scorer is never touched and every step is byte-exact reversible."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7388:     6	  - "SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flip default"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7426:    44	The compiled skill-router is built, hardened, wired into the live advisor, and **inert behind a default-off flag**. The sibling P4b work (`011-runtime-engine`) already flipped all seven hubs' activation manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`; what remains gated is whether the runtime *consumes* that state, and that gate is `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`. The parent goal asks to make compiled routing "the effective default."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7458:    76	2. **Silent drift is the steady state.** The serve-time shim recomputes the decision from live hub config; on any mismatch, missing resolver, or error it emits a `{ servingAuthority: "legacy" }` sentinel (`compiled-route.cjs:36-39`), which the advisor maps to `undefined` (`advisor-recommend.ts:351`). Any edit to a hub's `SKILL.md`/router config reverts that hub to legacy invisibly until its manifest is re-minted. This repo churns hub config constantly, so "compiled" would spend much of its life silently on legacy.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7460:    78	4. **Undocumented flag = governance violation.** `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is absent from `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, which the project constitution (CLAUDE.md §6) mandates as the source of truth for flag defaults. Flipping an undocumented flag violates that mandate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-018.err:7463:    81	A sixth, structural fragility (found this phase, under-weighted in prior handovers): the runtime front door `bin/compiled-route.cjs` resolves its resolver from a path **inside the spec tree** (`compiled-route.cjs:16-21` → `007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`). A spec renumber/re-nest silently breaks every compiled route to the legacy sentinel — the repo's own reorganization is a drift engine.
