.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-003.err:7177:  {"id":"F-3-4","area":"sk-code-align","finding":"The public compiled front door supplies only prompt text, but sk-code surfaceBundle routing requires risk-slice and certificate context, so code-opencode cannot be proven end-to-end through the current interface.","evidence":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:73","severity":"P0","actionable":"Extend the runtime request contract with safe composite-routing context and add a LUNA-high case requiring a surfaceBundle containing sk-code:code-opencode.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:20:A "compiled skill-router" is BUILT and SHIPPED but held INERT behind the default-OFF env flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`. When ON, the live advisor attaches the compiled decision as ADDITIVE metadata (`system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:371`) to a recommendation the legacy path already computed; it changes ZERO routing decisions (compiled is byte-identical to legacy) and fails safe to a legacy sentinel on any drift (`.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs:36-39`). The runtime front door resolves its resolver from a path INSIDE the spec tree (`compiled-route.cjs:16-21` → `.../007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`). The eligibility allowlist is duplicated (`advisor-recommend.ts` `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` + `compiled-route.cjs` `HUB_CHILD`). This session added decision packet `012-default-on-decision` (ruling: adopt a phased path to default-on) and alignment PLANS `013-create-skill-alignment` + `014-benchmark-alignment` (both authored, not implemented) under `.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:32:- Router runtime: `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs`; `.../011-runtime-engine/lib/`; `system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:71:- F-11-1 [playbooks/P0] The live playbook executor never explicitly enables SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING for its child process, so a LUNA run cannot deterministically exercise the compiled path.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:81:- F-8-2 [activation/P0] The bridge's `CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST` (mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs:58-87) also lacks `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, so the CLI fallback path (`buildCliBrief` → `runCliRecommend` at line 672-735) spawns a child without the flag even if the parent set it; this is a second env-strip layer beyond the launcher strip already documented in F-5-1.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:82:- F-8-3 [activation/P0] `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is not documented in `system-spec-kit/mcp-server/ENV-REFERENCE.md` despite being a load-bearing runtime flag with default-OFF/ON semantics and per-hub interaction — operators have no authoritative reference and no propagation guidance.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:15744:/bin/zsh -lc "rg -n -i 'compiled|SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING|routing_authority|serving|legacy' .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/assets/skill-benchmark .opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-benchmark/references/skill-benchmark .opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark | head -300
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16049:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:3:description: "Three decisions governing whether and how SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING becomes the repo's effective default: defer global default-on to a staged P4 outcome, single-source compiled eligibility to a valid fresh manifest, and remediate the runtime-to-spec-tree resolver coupling."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16058:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:55:The parent goal asks to make compiled routing the effective default, framing it as flipping `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` from off to on. Reading the live integration point shows that framing buys nothing and costs real surface. The advisor enters compiled routing only through `enrichCompiledRoutes()` at `advisor-recommend.ts:357`. With the flag unset that function returns its input untouched (`:362`). With the flag set it maps over recommendations the legacy path already computed and attaches `compiledRoute` as an additive sibling field, `{ ...recommendation, compiledRoute }` at `:371`, and never recomputes the chosen `skillId` or `workflowMode`. Turning the flag on can only make that extra field appear or, on drift, silently not appear. It cannot change which skill is recommended.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16060:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:57:The sibling `011-runtime-engine` already flipped all seven hubs' manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`, held inert behind the default-off flag. So the destination machinery exists. What does not exist is the reason to flip: today the flip is behavior-neutral by construction.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16066:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md-63-- `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is absent from `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, which CLAUDE.md section 6 mandates as the source of truth for flag defaults. Flipping an undocumented flag violates that mandate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16067:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:64:- The serve-time shim recomputes each hub's decision from live config and falls back to a `{ servingAuthority: "legacy" }` sentinel on any mismatch (`compiled-route.cjs:36-39`), which the advisor maps to `undefined` (`advisor-recommend.ts:351`). Editing a hub reverts it to legacy until re-minted, with nothing to observe the reversion.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16100:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:168:Which hubs are compiled-eligible is hardcoded in two places: `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` in `advisor-recommend.ts:41` and `HUB_CHILD` in `compiled-route.cjs:23`. Two hand-maintained lists drift apart. A newly created skill is compiled-invisible with no defined way to opt in, and `create-skill` today has zero compiled-routing awareness (a repo grep for compiled-routing tokens under the create-skill mode returns nothing).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16110:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:182:**We chose**: Define compiled eligibility as a single derived predicate: a hub is compiled-eligible if and only if a valid, fresh manifest exists for it (its minted digest matches its live config hash). Both `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` derive from that one rule.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16124:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:273:The runtime front door `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` resolves its resolver from a path inside the spec tree: `compiled-route.cjs:16-21` points at `007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`. This repo renumbers and re-nests spec folders constantly (the memory index records repeated hyphen migrations, renumbers, and re-nests). A single such move silently breaks every compiled route to the legacy sentinel, with no observable signal. The repo's own reorganization is a latent drift engine independent of hub-config edits.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16136:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:335:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | The coupling exists at `compiled-route.cjs:16-21` and the repo renumbers spec folders routinely |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16199:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:93:> **Compiled routing (opt-in, flag-gated, additive).** When `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`, resolve the mode via the compiled router contract first:
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16201:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:95:> node .opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs --hub {{HUB_NAME}} --prompt "<task>"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16203:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:97:> Follow the returned decision — `route` (use its `targets`), `clarify`/`defer` (disambiguate), `reject` (refuse). On a `{"servingAuthority":"legacy"}` sentinel or any error, use the routing below. The front door self-gates on serving authority, and the flag is **off by default**, so this is inert until compiled routing is activated for `{{HUB_NAME}}`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16282:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:3:description: "Plan the Lane C harness changes that exercise the compiled router with SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1, compare its normalized routing decisions with legacy router replay and the same authored route gold, and classify manifest drift separately from compiled-path breakage without editing the three frozen scorer files."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16292:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:25:Lane C currently benchmarks deterministic routing through `router-replay.cjs`, joins the observed result to authored route gold, and scores it through `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`. The orchestrator never turns on `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, never invokes the compiled front door, and never compares the compiled decision with the legacy replay. A hub can therefore pass the benchmark while the path intended to serve under the compiled flag is stale, falling back, or broken.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16309:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:54:The existing seam is suitable for an additive parity lane: `router-replay.cjs` returns legacy intents/resources and hub telemetry; `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` returns the flag-gated compiled decision or a legacy sentinel; `score-skill-benchmark.cjs` already exports the route-gold evaluator. The missing piece is normalization and comparison around those unchanged modules.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16324:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:73:- Child-process invocation of `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` for eligible hubs so the real public flag-gated path is exercised.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16352:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:102:2. Spawn the public compiled front door with a process-local environment containing `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16357:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:107:7. Record the result under a new `compiledRouting` report block without altering D1-D5 scoring.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16365:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:115:| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/build-report.cjs` | Modify | Render the `compiledRouting` block from report JSON |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16374:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:133:| REQ-002 | Exercise the real compiled-serving path with the flag on. | Eligible hub scenarios invoke `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` in a child process with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`; the report records `flagForcedOn: true` and the front-door outcome. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16377:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:136:| REQ-005 | Integrate parity as a Lane C gate without changing D1-D5. | `report.compiledRouting` contains mode, eligible rows, parity counts, drift rows, breakages, and frozen hashes; routing divergence or breakage produces a distinct blocked verdict and non-zero exit, while drift remains visibly classified according to the authoritative contract. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16442:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:3:description: "Settle whether SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING should become the repo's effective default and, if so, on what safe path. The compiled router is built, wired, and inert behind a default-off flag: the P4b flip already moved all seven hubs' manifests to servingAuthority: compiled, and the live advisor consumes them only when the flag is 1, only for hubs in a hardcoded allowlist, and even then attaches the compiled decision as ADDITIVE metadata that never changes which skill is recommended. This phase records the decision — default-on is a Phase-4 OUTCOME, not a switch-flip — and specifies the four contracts that make an eventual global default-on safe and reversible: (P0) document the flag in ENV-REFERENCE and make the verify harness distinguish drift-to-legacy from breakage plus a per-hub serving-status readout; (P1) a drift-detection CI that recomputes each hub's live hash against its minted manifest and fails 're-mint required'; (P2) a canary default-on in one env profile with the repo default staying off; (P3) a data-driven eligibility rule (compiled-eligible IFF a valid fresh manifest exists) that single-sources the duplicated allowlist and makes no-manifest skills legacy by construction; (P4) a staged, hub-by-hub global default-on that flips the two code predicates and the seven SKILL.md directives in lockstep while keeping =0 as the documented kill-switch. The frozen benchmark scorer is never touched and every step is byte-exact reversible."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16445:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-6-  - "SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flip default"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16452:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:44:The compiled skill-router is built, hardened, wired into the live advisor, and **inert behind a default-off flag**. The sibling P4b work (`011-runtime-engine`) already flipped all seven hubs' activation manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`; what remains gated is whether the runtime *consumes* that state, and that gate is `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`. The parent goal asks to make compiled routing "the effective default."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16463:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:76:2. **Silent drift is the steady state.** The serve-time shim recomputes the decision from live hub config; on any mismatch, missing resolver, or error it emits a `{ servingAuthority: "legacy" }` sentinel (`compiled-route.cjs:36-39`), which the advisor maps to `undefined` (`advisor-recommend.ts:351`). Any edit to a hub's `SKILL.md`/router config reverts that hub to legacy invisibly until its manifest is re-minted. This repo churns hub config constantly, so "compiled" would spend much of its life silently on legacy.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16465:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-78-4. **Undocumented flag = governance violation.** `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is absent from `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, which the project constitution (CLAUDE.md §6) mandates as the source of truth for flag defaults. Flipping an undocumented flag violates that mandate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16468:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:81:A sixth, structural fragility (found this phase, under-weighted in prior handovers): the runtime front door `bin/compiled-route.cjs` resolves its resolver from a path **inside the spec tree** (`compiled-route.cjs:16-21` → `007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`). A spec renumber/re-nest silently breaks every compiled route to the legacy sentinel — the repo's own reorganization is a drift engine.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-017.err:16487:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md-106-- Actually flipping `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` to a repo default in this phase — [why] this phase decides and contracts; the flip is the P4 execution phase, gated on P0–P3 landing green.
