.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6362:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:3:description: "Plan the Lane C harness changes that exercise the compiled router with SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1, compare its normalized routing decisions with legacy router replay and the same authored route gold, and classify manifest drift separately from compiled-path breakage without editing the three frozen scorer files."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6365:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:25:Lane C currently benchmarks deterministic routing through `router-replay.cjs`, joins the observed result to authored route gold, and scores it through `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`. The orchestrator never turns on `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, never invokes the compiled front door, and never compares the compiled decision with the legacy replay. A hub can therefore pass the benchmark while the path intended to serve under the compiled flag is stale, falling back, or broken.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6367:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:73:- Child-process invocation of `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` for eligible hubs so the real public flag-gated path is exercised.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6368:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:102:2. Spawn the public compiled front door with a process-local environment containing `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6369:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:133:| REQ-002 | Exercise the real compiled-serving path with the flag on. | Eligible hub scenarios invoke `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` in a child process with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`; the report records `flagForcedOn: true` and the front-door outcome. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6383:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:93:> **Compiled routing (opt-in, flag-gated, additive).** When `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`, resolve the mode via the compiled router contract first:
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6384:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:97:> Follow the returned decision — `route` (use its `targets`), `clarify`/`defer` (disambiguate), `reject` (refuse). On a `{"servingAuthority":"legacy"}` sentinel or any error, use the routing below. The front door self-gates on serving authority, and the flag is **off by default**, so this is inert until compiled routing is activated for `{{HUB_NAME}}`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6394:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:3:description: "The runtime engine that consumes the compiled router contract at route time, plus the per-hub serving-authority flip that makes it authoritative. Stage P4b — the literal cutover — built on top of P4a (010-live-activation, which bound each hub's compiled generation as selectedPolicy while serving authority stayed legacy). Three zero-dependency modules: an archetype-adaptive compiled-route engine that reuses each rollout child's proven closed-decision-algebra engine (evaluateCanary or evaluateRoute, by archetype — so the runtime path and the shadow-validated path are the same code), a double-gated fail-safe resolver plus CLI front-door that only serves the compiled route when the runtime flag SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 AND the hub's manifest reads servingAuthority: compiled, and a fenced compare-and-swap flip that moves a hub legacy→compiled behind green gates with a byte-exact rollback. The literal cutover is complete: all seven hubs are flipped legacy→compiled (each with a flag-gated compiled-routing directive in its live SKILL.md and archetype-adaptive re-certification), held inert behind the default-off SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flag; the frozen benchmark scorer is pinned throughout."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6395:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:27:Three zero-dependency modules do the work. An archetype-adaptive **compiled-route engine** answers `(hubId, taskText)` by loading the hub's compiled policy and reusing the **same** closed-decision-algebra engine the shadow canary already validates — the export name varies by archetype (`evaluateCanary` for the surfaceBundle canary-router, `evaluateRoute` for the plain router), so the runtime path and the shadow-validated path are literally the same code, with no reimplementation to drift. A double-gated **resolver + CLI front-door** returns the compiled decision only when the runtime flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` is set (default off) **and** the hub's activation manifest reads `servingAuthority: compiled`; otherwise it returns a legacy sentinel and the caller keeps the prose smart-router. A fenced-CAS **serving flip** moves one hub `legacy → compiled` behind green gates, retaining a byte-identical pre-flip manifest for a byte-exact rollback. The mechanism was proven end-to-end on `sk-code`, then the literal cutover was executed across all seven hubs: each hub's live `SKILL.md` gained a flag-gated compiled-routing directive, was recompiled with archetype-adaptive re-certification, and had serving authority flipped `legacy → compiled`. The cutover is inert by default and reversible two ways, and the frozen benchmark scorer is pinned untouched throughout — so live routing is unchanged until `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is enabled (compiled routing is route-gold byte-identical to legacy).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6396:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:38:| **Status** | Complete — the P4b runtime engine (archetype-adaptive compiled-route engine + resolver/CLI front-door + per-hub serving flip) is built, and the literal cutover is executed across all seven hubs: each hub carries a flag-gated compiled-routing directive in its live `SKILL.md`, was recompiled with archetype-adaptive re-certification, and had serving authority flipped `legacy → compiled` (`servingAuthority: compiled` in each `010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json`). Each flip is canary-green via the real scorer, route-gold ROUTING byte-identical (only hashes changed), with a byte-exact rollback retained (`manifest.serving-prior.json`). The runtime path is inert by default (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` off), so live routing is unchanged until the flag is enabled. Advisor-hook machine-enforcement remains in progress. Commits: engine `d7da0fca43`, sk-code cutover `2fa3357f80`, remaining-6 cutover `337ca43cfa` (pushed on v4). |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6397:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:56:Deliver the P4b runtime engine as three small, zero-dependency modules: a pure compiled-route engine that reuses each rollout child's proven canary engine (never a reimplementation), a double-gated fail-safe resolver plus CLI front-door that only serves the compiled route under an explicit runtime flag and a per-hub serving flag, and a fenced compare-and-swap flip that moves a hub `legacy → compiled` behind green gates with a proven byte-exact rollback — then prove the whole path end-to-end on one hub, keep the frozen scorer pinned, and execute the rollout across all seven hubs (wire each live `SKILL.md`, re-certify, and flip serving authority) behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag so live routing is unchanged until it is enabled.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6398:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:68:- The **resolver + CLI front-door** `lib/resolve.cjs` — double-gated (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND manifest `servingAuthority: compiled`), fail-safe (errors → null), with a `--hub/--prompt` CLI that prints the compiled decision or a legacy sentinel.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6399:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:75:- Wiring each hub's live `SKILL.md` routing directive to call the resolver - [note] beyond the initial engine build, but now **complete**: each of the seven hubs carries an additive, flag-gated compiled-routing directive that shells to the resolver front-door and self-gates on serving authority (inert while `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is off).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6401:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:89:> The engine and resolver are pure and read-only. Only the flip mutates state, and it does so on the P4a activation manifest under `010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/` (the serving pointer the resolver reads) — never on a live routing file or the scorer. The runtime path stays inert until `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` is set for a hub that has been flipped.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6403:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:104:| REQ-003 | The resolver serves the compiled route ONLY when both gates hold, and is otherwise inert. | `resolveRoute(hubId, taskText)` returns null unless `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND the hub's `010-live-activation` manifest reads `servingAuthority: compiled`; with the flag off it returns null / the CLI prints a legacy sentinel. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6404:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:113:| REQ-007 | Prove the whole path end-to-end on one hub, then execute the cutover across all seven. | On `sk-code`: flip → `servingAuthority: compiled` with green gates → the front-door returns `action: route` (flag on) and a legacy sentinel (flag off) → byte-exact `--rollback` proven. All seven hubs are then flipped `legacy → compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, each canary-green with a retained byte-identical serving-prior; the frozen scorer digests are unchanged. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6405:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:124:- **SC-002**: The resolver is inert by default and double-gated — no compiled route is served unless `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` and the hub reads `servingAuthority: compiled`; it fails safe to legacy on any error.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6406:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:126:- **SC-004**: The path is proven end-to-end on `sk-code` (flip → compiled-served route → byte-exact rollback), and the cutover is then executed across all seven hubs — each flipped `legacy → compiled` and left compiled-serving but inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, with a byte-identical serving-prior retained for a byte-exact per-hub rollback.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6408:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:141:| Risk | The serving flip is the only stage that changes runtime routing | A wrong or premature flip changes what actually routes | Inert by default (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` off), per-hub gate, fenced CAS, byte-exact rollback, one hub at a time |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6409:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:158:- **NFR-R02**: The cutover is reversible two independent ways — unset `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` fleet-wide (the resolver returns null everywhere) or flip a single hub back to `legacy` (per hub).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6410:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:34:| **Serving gate** | Double gate: runtime flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND manifest `servingAuthority: compiled`; default off = inert |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6411:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:40:P4b adds the runtime consumer P4a left out, as three small modules. `compiled-route.cjs` is an archetype-adaptive pure engine: given `(hubId, taskText)` it loads the hub's compiled snapshot and routes it through the child's own engine — `evaluateCanary` or `evaluateRoute`, by archetype — returning a normalized decision and deferring on off-signal prompts. `resolve.cjs` is the safety gate: it serves the compiled decision only when the runtime flag is set and the hub's manifest reads `servingAuthority: compiled`, fails safe to null on any error, and exposes a `--hub/--prompt` CLI front-door. `flip-serving.cjs` is the operated switch: a fenced CAS that moves a hub `legacy → compiled` behind a P4a-binding check, a green canary, the frozen-scorer pin, and a live-route proof, retaining a byte-identical pre-flip manifest so `--rollback` is byte-exact. The path was proven on `sk-code`, then the cutover was executed across all seven hubs — each live `SKILL.md` wired with an additive flag-gated directive, recompiled with archetype-adaptive re-certification, and flipped `legacy → compiled` — held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag with a byte-exact rollback retained per hub.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6412:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:80:Prompt → `resolveRoute(hubId, taskText)` → gate 1 flag (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`) and gate 2 manifest (`servingAuthority: compiled`) → on pass, `compiledRoute` loads the hub's rollout-child engine and routes via its archetype engine (`evaluateCanary` or `evaluateRoute`) → normalized decision returned; on any miss or error, null → caller keeps the legacy prose smart-router. The flip path is operated out-of-band: `flip-serving.cjs` proves the four gates, retains the pre-flip manifest, swaps `servingAuthority` and advances the fence, and records `serving-flip-record.json`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6413:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:96:| Runtime flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` | Off by default | Read by the resolver | Flag off ⇒ resolver returns null everywhere (inert) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6414:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:97:| Live `SKILL.md` (per hub) | Authoritative serving routing | **Wired — additive, flag-gated compiled-routing directive added** | Each of the 7 hubs' `SKILL.md` shells to the resolver front-door under `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`, self-gating on serving authority; existing prose routing unchanged |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6415:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:137:| Gating | Flag off / manifest legacy ⇒ inert; both on ⇒ served | `resolve.cjs --hub … --prompt …` with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` on and off |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6416:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:154:| Runtime flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` | Internal | Off (default) | The compiled path is inert until explicitly enabled per rollout |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-001.err:6417:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:165:- **Procedure**: Two independent reversals. Fleet-wide — unset `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, and the resolver returns null everywhere (legacy serves) with no manifest change. Per hub — `flip-serving.cjs --hub <id> --rollback` restores the byte-identical `manifest.serving-prior.json` and advances the fence; confirm `servingAuthority` reverts to `legacy` and `shadowOnly` to `true`. Retain the serving-prior for the full bake window before any cleanup.
