.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4032:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:3:description: "Activate the compiled router contract across all seven parent hubs in two ordered stages. Stage P4a (design-faithful): a fenced compare-and-swap binds each hub's compiled policy generation as the SELECTED policy on a dedicated per-hub activation manifest, advancing a monotonic fence epoch, while serving authority stays legacy and no runtime consumer is touched; rollback restores the byte-identical prior manifest. Stage P4b (literal cutover, now complete in the sibling 011-runtime-engine): a runtime resolver consumes the compiled contract and serving authority was flipped hub-by-hub across all seven hubs, re-verified, with the byte-identical legacy manifest retained for rollback and the compiled path held inert behind the default-off SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flag. The shared benchmark scorer is frozen and pinned throughout; every activation proves a byte-exact rollback and rides a green canary."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4033:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:27:Every parent hub already owns a real-green rollout canary: its authored routing (`SKILL.md` + `hub-router.json` + `mode-registry.json`) is projected into a content-addressed `CompiledPolicyV1`, proven route-gold byte-green against the real read-only benchmark scorer, closed-algebra-valid, and reversible by a byte-exact shadow rollback. What did **not** exist was an activation layer: a place where the compiled generation is *bound* as authoritative, distinct from where it is *served*. Stage P4a builds exactly that layer, and it is this phase's shipped work; Stage P4b — the only stage that changes what actually routes — is now complete: executed in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`, which flipped all seven hubs' serving authority `legacy → compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag (route-gold ROUTING byte-identical — only hashes changed), with a byte-identical legacy manifest retained per hub for a byte-exact rollback.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4034:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:38:| **Status** | Complete — P4a design-faithful activation + T9 real-model verification (0 wrong-hub routes) complete for all 7 hubs, and the P4b literal cutover (`011-runtime-engine`) is complete: all 7 hubs flipped `legacy → compiled` (`servingAuthority: compiled`, `shadowOnly: false`), inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, byte-exact rollback retained. Advisor-hook machine-enforcement remains in progress |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4035:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:42:| **Blast radius** | Governance binding (selectedPolicy CAS) — reversible, pre-effect; the P4b runtime flip (`011`) is complete but held inert by default behind `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` and reversible per-hub or fleet-wide |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4036:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:56:Establish a phase-local activation layer that binds each hub's compiled generation as `selectedPolicy` through a fenced compare-and-swap while leaving `servingAuthority` at `legacy`, proves a byte-exact rollback for every activation, and provides the proven, reversible foundation that the subsequent P4b flip (executed in `011-runtime-engine`) built on to move all seven hubs to compiled serving behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4038:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:75:- Stage P4b's runtime resolver build - [why] delivered in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`, not authored in this phase. (P4b has since consumed this phase's binding and flipped these activation manifests `legacy → compiled`; that flip is 011's work, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag.)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4039:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:88:> All activation state is phase-local under `activation/`. Live runtime routing files remain read-only. P4a bound the candidate shadow-only with legacy serving; the sibling P4b flip (`011`) has since advanced these manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`, `shadowOnly: false` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4040:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:113:| REQ-008 | Stage P4b — a runtime resolver that consumes `selectedPolicy`, plus a `servingAuthority` `legacy → compiled` flip, one hub at a time, with post-flip re-verification and proven rollback — delivered in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`. | Complete: the P4b runtime engine (`011`) is built and all 7 hubs are flipped `legacy → compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag; each flip is canary-green via the real scorer, route-gold ROUTING byte-identical (only hashes changed), the 3 frozen scorer digests are unchanged, and the byte-exact rollback is retained (`manifest.serving-prior.json`). Commits: engine `d7da0fca43`, sk-code cutover `2fa3357f80`, remaining-6 cutover `337ca43cfa` (pushed on v4). |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4041:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:126:- **SC-005**: Stage P4b (runtime resolver + serving-authority flip) is complete in the sibling `011-runtime-engine` — all 7 hubs flipped `legacy → compiled`, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag (routing byte-identical, so live routing is unchanged until the flag is enabled) and byte-exact-reversible — and T9 real-model verification is complete (0 wrong-hub routes). Post-flip real-model re-verification is treated as satisfied by the T9 result plus flag-off inertness; the advisor-hook machine-enforcement layer remains in progress — no premature "machine-enforced" claim.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4042:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:139:| Risk | Conflating "bind" with "serve" | The highest-blast change (live routing) becomes inseparable from governance binding | Two-stage split: P4a binds `selectedPolicy` only; P4b (serving flip) is a separate stage, executed in `011` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4043:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:141:| Risk | P4b blast radius | The serving-authority flip is the only stage that changes runtime routing | Executed one-hub-at-a-time behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag; reversible per-hub (retained serving-prior) or fleet-wide (flag off); route-gold ROUTING byte-identical, so live routing is unchanged until the flag is enabled |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4044:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:192:| Risk | 16/25 | Governance binding is pre-effect and reversible; the real blast (P4b serving flip) is split out and executed in `011` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4046:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:39:A single shared driver, `lib/activate-hub.cjs`, performs the design-faithful activation for every hub: it seeds a phase-local activation manifest byte-for-byte from the hub's shadow rollout child, then binds the hub's compiled generation as `selectedPolicy` via a fenced CAS that advances the fence epoch while `servingAuthority` stays `legacy`. Every activation is gated on a frozen-scorer pin and a green canary, and proves a byte-exact rollback. Stage P4b — the runtime resolver plus the `servingAuthority` flip — is complete, delivered in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`: all seven hubs were flipped `legacy → compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, with the byte-identical legacy manifest retained per hub.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4047:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:59:- [x] P4b runtime resolver + serving-authority flip complete in `011-runtime-engine` (all 7 hubs flipped `legacy → compiled`, inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, byte-exact rollback retained).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4048:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:70:Bind-then-serve, split into two stages. Activation is a fenced compare-and-swap that moves `selectedPolicy` from the legacy generation to the compiled generation on a phase-local manifest; it never edits a serving policy. Serving authority stayed legacy through P4a; the separate P4b resolver (`011-runtime-engine`) has since been built and flipped all seven hubs to `compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4051:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/checklist.md:84:  - **Evidence**: Each P4a activation record reported `servingAuthority: "legacy"`, `shadowOnly: true`; the sibling P4b flip (`011`) has since advanced the committed manifests to `servingAuthority: "compiled"`, `shadowOnly: false`, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag (route-gold ROUTING byte-identical).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4052:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/checklist.md:147:**Completion Boundary**: Real-model routing verification (T9) is complete (0 wrong-hub routes across 3 models), and the P4b runtime resolver + serving-authority flip (T16-T17) is complete in `011-runtime-engine` — all 7 hubs flipped `legacy → compiled`, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag and byte-exact-reversible. The advisor-hook machine-enforcement layer is complete (committed, flag-off byte-parity proven). A fresh post-flip real-model sweep was re-run and passed: 0 wrong-hub routes across 3 models × 7 hubs.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4054:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:3:description: "Plan the Lane C harness changes that exercise the compiled router with SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1, compare its normalized routing decisions with legacy router replay and the same authored route gold, and classify manifest drift separately from compiled-path breakage without editing the three frozen scorer files."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4055:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:25:Lane C currently benchmarks deterministic routing through `router-replay.cjs`, joins the observed result to authored route gold, and scores it through `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`. The orchestrator never turns on `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, never invokes the compiled front door, and never compares the compiled decision with the legacy replay. A hub can therefore pass the benchmark while the path intended to serve under the compiled flag is stale, falling back, or broken.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4056:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:73:- Child-process invocation of `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` for eligible hubs so the real public flag-gated path is exercised.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4057:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:102:2. Spawn the public compiled front door with a process-local environment containing `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4058:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:133:| REQ-002 | Exercise the real compiled-serving path with the flag on. | Eligible hub scenarios invoke `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` in a child process with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`; the report records `flagForcedOn: true` and the front-door outcome. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4059:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:3:description: "Design-faithful fenced-CAS activation of all seven hubs: selectedPolicy bound to the compiled generation, byte-exact rollback proven, scorer frozen. P4b cutover complete in 011-runtime-engine (all 7 hubs flipped legacy->compiled, inert behind the default-off SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flag)."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4060:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:23:| **Status** | Complete — P4a design-faithful activation + T9 real-model verification (0 wrong-hub routes) complete for all 7 hubs, and the P4b cutover (`011-runtime-engine`) is complete: all 7 hubs flipped `legacy → compiled`, inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, byte-exact rollback retained. Advisor-hook machine-enforcement remains in progress |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4061:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:26:| **Serving authority** | `compiled` (committed) — P4a bound the compiled generation as `selectedPolicy` with legacy serving; the sibling P4b flip (`011`) advanced all 7 manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4062:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:38:This is the design-faithful reading of activation: the compiled contract becomes the *accepted, bound* generation; at P4a bind time legacy kept *serving* because no runtime consumer existed yet. The genuine runtime change — a resolver that reads `selectedPolicy` plus a `servingAuthority` flip — is now complete in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`: all seven hubs are flipped `legacy → compiled`, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag (route-gold ROUTING byte-identical — only hashes changed), with a byte-identical legacy manifest retained per hub for a byte-exact rollback.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4063:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:75:| Bound real-model verification (T9) to a sample; then execute the P4b flip behind a flag | T9 ran 2 authentic playbook prompts per hub × 3 models × 2 runs — bounded but real (0 wrong-hub routes). The serving-authority flip is the only stage that changes runtime routing; it was executed in `011` one-hub-at-a-time behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag and stays reversible (per-hub serving-prior or fleet-wide flag off). |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4064:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:84:All seven hubs, in activation order, returned `ACTIVATION BOUND … serving=legacy shadowOnly=true fence=0->1 rollback.byteExact=true scorerFrozen=true canaryGreen=true` at P4a bind time; the sibling P4b flip (`011`) then advanced all seven to `servingAuthority: compiled`, `shadowOnly: false` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag (each flip canary-green via the real scorer, route-gold ROUTING byte-identical, byte-exact rollback retained):
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4065:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:110:2. **The P4b literal cutover (T16-T17) is complete.** The runtime resolver that consumes `selectedPolicy` and the `servingAuthority` `legacy → compiled` flip — the only stage that changes runtime routing — were delivered in the sibling `011-runtime-engine` (commits engine `d7da0fca43`, sk-code cutover `2fa3357f80`, remaining-6 cutover `337ca43cfa`, pushed on v4). All 7 hubs are flipped, each canary-green via the real scorer with a byte-exact rollback retained; the path is inert by default (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` off) and reversible per-hub or fleet-wide. The advisor-hook machine-enforcement layer that would machine-enforce the wired routing remains in progress.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4067:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:119:    current_focus: "P4a complete (7/7 hubs bound + byte-exact rollback + T9 real-model verification, 0 wrong-hub routes); P4b cutover complete in 011-runtime-engine — all 7 hubs flipped legacy->compiled (servingAuthority: compiled), held inert behind the default-off SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flag (route-gold byte-identical), byte-exact rollback retained per hub"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4068:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/implementation-summary.md:122:      - "Enablement is operator-gated: set SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 to serve compiled (routing byte-identical); reversible per-hub (flip-serving --rollback) or fleet-wide (flag off)"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4072:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:3:description: "Three decisions governing whether and how SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING becomes the repo's effective default: defer global default-on to a staged P4 outcome, single-source compiled eligibility to a valid fresh manifest, and remediate the runtime-to-spec-tree resolver coupling."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4073:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:55:The parent goal asks to make compiled routing the effective default, framing it as flipping `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` from off to on. Reading the live integration point shows that framing buys nothing and costs real surface. The advisor enters compiled routing only through `enrichCompiledRoutes()` at `advisor-recommend.ts:357`. With the flag unset that function returns its input untouched (`:362`). With the flag set it maps over recommendations the legacy path already computed and attaches `compiledRoute` as an additive sibling field, `{ ...recommendation, compiledRoute }` at `:371`, and never recomputes the chosen `skillId` or `workflowMode`. Turning the flag on can only make that extra field appear or, on drift, silently not appear. It cannot change which skill is recommended.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4074:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:63:- `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is absent from `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, which CLAUDE.md section 6 mandates as the source of truth for flag defaults. Flipping an undocumented flag violates that mandate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4075:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:145:**How to roll back**: Nothing in this phase changes runtime behavior, so there is nothing to roll back here. Across the program, `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` restores legacy serving fleet-wide, and each per-hub flip retains a byte-identical prior manifest for a byte-exact per-hub revert.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4077:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/tasks.md:89:**Evidence**: P4a design-faithful activation, T9 real-model verification (0 wrong-hub routes), and the P4b cutover (T016-T017) are all complete for the 7 hubs — the seven-hub `legacy → compiled` flip landed in `011-runtime-engine` (commits engine `d7da0fca43`, sk-code cutover `2fa3357f80`, remaining-6 cutover `337ca43cfa`, pushed on v4), held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag. The advisor-hook machine-enforcement layer remains in progress and is NOT claimed done.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4078:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:3:description: "Settle whether SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING should become the repo's effective default and, if so, on what safe path. The compiled router is built, wired, and inert behind a default-off flag: the P4b flip already moved all seven hubs' manifests to servingAuthority: compiled, and the live advisor consumes them only when the flag is 1, only for hubs in a hardcoded allowlist, and even then attaches the compiled decision as ADDITIVE metadata that never changes which skill is recommended. This phase records the decision — default-on is a Phase-4 OUTCOME, not a switch-flip — and specifies the four contracts that make an eventual global default-on safe and reversible: (P0) document the flag in ENV-REFERENCE and make the verify harness distinguish drift-to-legacy from breakage plus a per-hub serving-status readout; (P1) a drift-detection CI that recomputes each hub's live hash against its minted manifest and fails 're-mint required'; (P2) a canary default-on in one env profile with the repo default staying off; (P3) a data-driven eligibility rule (compiled-eligible IFF a valid fresh manifest exists) that single-sources the duplicated allowlist and makes no-manifest skills legacy by construction; (P4) a staged, hub-by-hub global default-on that flips the two code predicates and the seven SKILL.md directives in lockstep while keeping =0 as the documented kill-switch. The frozen benchmark scorer is never touched and every step is byte-exact reversible."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4079:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:6:  - "SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flip default"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4080:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:44:The compiled skill-router is built, hardened, wired into the live advisor, and **inert behind a default-off flag**. The sibling P4b work (`011-runtime-engine`) already flipped all seven hubs' activation manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`; what remains gated is whether the runtime *consumes* that state, and that gate is `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`. The parent goal asks to make compiled routing "the effective default."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4081:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:78:4. **Undocumented flag = governance violation.** `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is absent from `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, which the project constitution (CLAUDE.md §6) mandates as the source of truth for flag defaults. Flipping an undocumented flag violates that mandate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4083:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:106:- Actually flipping `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` to a repo default in this phase — [why] this phase decides and contracts; the flip is the P4 execution phase, gated on P0–P3 landing green.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4084:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:131:| REQ-002 | Specify the fallback contract precisely and single-sourced. | The contract defines that a hub is compiled-served IFF a valid, fresh manifest exists AND `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND the hub is eligible; every other state resolves to the legacy sentinel with no behavior change. The eligibility predicate is named as the single source both `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` must derive from (delivered in P3). |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4085:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:180:- **NFR-R01**: Every step P0→P4 names an explicit rollback; the P4 global default-on keeps `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the documented, load-bearing kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4086:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:202:- `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` after P4 default-on: must fully restore legacy serving fleet-wide, documented as the kill-switch, not an incidental default.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4087:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:240:- **Q1 (resolved).** The ruling is settled: adopt the phased path (default-on as a staged P4 outcome after P0–P3), decided on the analysis and reversible. An operator override to flip `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` on now remains available but is not blocking; the steelman for flipping now is recorded in `decision-record.md` ("flip it when compiled does something legacy can't").
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4089:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/tasks.md:84:- [ ] T005 Document `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` in `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, including default-off behavior, explicit enablement, and `=0` kill-switch semantics. (REQ-005; environment reference) {deps: T002, T004}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4090:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/tasks.md:107:- [ ] T019 Exercise `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` fleet-wide and the retained prior-manifest rollback per hub. (REQ-005; rollback drill) {deps: T014}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4091:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:87:- [ ] `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` is exercised as the fleet-wide kill-switch after the staged cutover.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4092:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:143:- Locate every read of `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` and every environment profile that can set it.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4093:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:156:- [ ] Document `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` in the environment reference with default-off semantics and the explicit `=0` kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4094:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:178:- [ ] P4: exercise `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch and retain per-hub manifest rollback.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4095:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:221:- **Procedure**: Stop the stage; set `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` for fleet-wide legacy serving; restore the affected hub's retained prior manifest when a per-hub pointer changed; restore the prior resolver location or temporary eligibility constants when those components caused the failure; rerun the status and parity gates before resuming.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4096:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:281:- [ ] `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` has been exercised in the target environment.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4097:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:285:1. Set `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` and verify fleet-wide legacy serving.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4098:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:395:| Reversibility | Preserve `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` and each stage's rollback evidence |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4102:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:28:`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=<0|1> codex exec --model gpt-5.6-luna -c model_reasoning_effort="high" -c service_tier="fast" -c approval_policy=never --sandbox read-only -o <stdout-evidence> "<route-only prompt>" 2> <stderr-evidence>`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4103:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:7:- `mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs` constructs the daemon environment exclusively from `CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST`, which does not include `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`; both build helpers and the live server receive that filtered environment. A P2 canary set in the parent profile therefore does not reach the live advisor daemon (`.opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:99`, `.opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:267-270`, `.opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:1267-1271`). The environment reference already documents this propagation requirement and fresh-session adoption for another advisor flag, establishing the correct operational pattern (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/ENV-REFERENCE.md:639`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4104:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:27:  {"id":"F-5-1","area":"unnamed","finding":"The advisor launcher strips SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING before spawning the daemon, so a parent-profile canary cannot activate the live advisor path.","evidence":".opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:267","severity":"P0","actionable":"Add the flag to CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST and test parent-to-daemon propagation plus fresh-session adoption.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4106:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:93:> **Compiled routing (opt-in, flag-gated, additive).** When `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`, resolve the mode via the compiled router contract first:
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4107:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:80:Derive both eligibility consumers from the manifest-freshness rule already owned by `decision-record.md`, then stage the global default one hub at a time while preserving `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4111:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:11:- The Spec Kit catalog already has a canonical “Feature flag governance” entry and leaf (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:4480`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/governance/feature-flag-governance.md:25`). Extend those rather than creating another flag feature. Document `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, its current/default state, staged rollout, explicit kill switch, eligibility rule, drift response, and serving-status readout. Because the touched leaf currently uses an unstructured source list (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/governance/feature-flag-governance.md:49`), convert it to the template’s separate implementation and validation tables.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4112:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:29:  {"id":"F-1-3","area":"activation","finding":"The feature-flag governance catalog must document compiled-routing polarity and rollback because the live handler directly gates enrichment on SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:362","severity":"P0","actionable":"Extend the existing system-spec-kit feature-flag-governance root entry and leaf with phased defaults, eligibility, serving status, drift behavior, and the explicit =0 kill switch.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4113:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-011.md:9:The live assertion is insufficient for compiled routing: its prompt asks the model to state routing in JSON, then scores parsed model text and tool observations. `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:19`, `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:311` Worse, although `runDispatch` supports child-only environment overrides, `runLiveScenario` does not supply one, so `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` is only inherited opportunistically from the parent process. `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:125`, `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:363`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4114:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-011.md:15:1. Add a non-frozen compiled-route observation adapter that invokes `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` with an explicit child-only `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`, then asserts authority, action, and ordered targets against route gold.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4115:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-011.md:22:  {"id":"F-11-1","area":"playbooks","finding":"The live playbook executor never explicitly enables SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING for its child process, so a LUNA run cannot deterministically exercise the compiled path.","evidence":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/live-executor.cjs:363","severity":"P0","actionable":"Add a new non-frozen compiled-route adapter that spawns the public front door with child-only SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 and asserts serving authority, action, and ordered targets against route gold.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4116:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:8:- **Current Reality before P4:** “Compiled routing is additive and opt-in with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`; legacy remains authoritative when disabled or when the compiled front door returns its legacy sentinel.” This matches every current hub directive, including `sk-prompt` and `cli-external-orchestration` (`.opencode/skills/sk-prompt/SKILL.md:36-40`, `.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/SKILL.md:41-45`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4117:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:9:- **Current Reality after that hub’s P4 cutover:** “Compiled routing is the default authority for a fresh eligible manifest. `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` is the fleet kill-switch; missing or stale eligibility routes to the classified legacy fallback.” The planned observable states are `compiled-serving`, `legacy-fallback`, and `drifted` (`.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:98-107`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4118:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:13:The per-feature file should be `routing-and-activation/compiled-hub-routing.md`, titled `Compiled Hub Routing`, with H1 `# Compiled Hub Routing (compiled-route.cjs)`. Use three short `HOW IT WORKS` paragraphs: core routing outcome, activation/rollback, then status/failure classification. Its required implementation table, validation table, metadata, and root-entry linkage follow `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-feature-catalog/SKILL.md:274-305`. Use hub-qualified triggers such as `"<hub> compiled hub routing"`, `"<hub> compiled route"`, and `"SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING <hub>"`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4119:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/graph-metadata.json:15:      "SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flip default",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4125:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:17:      "finding": "Vacuous-parity trap: SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 alone is insufficient. resolve.cjs:41-42 requires the per-hub activation manifest to read servingAuthority==='compiled'; otherwise resolveRoute returns null and compiled-route.cjs:39 emits a legacy sentinel that a naive lane reads as 'compiled matches legacy'.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4126:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:83:      "finding": "The feature-flag governance catalog must document compiled-routing polarity and rollback because the live handler directly gates enrichment on SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4127:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:281:      "finding": "The advisor launcher strips SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING before spawning the daemon, so a parent-profile canary cannot activate the live advisor path.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4128:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:534:      "finding": "The live playbook executor never explicitly enables SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING for its child process, so a LUNA run cannot deterministically exercise the compiled path.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4129:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:537:      "actionable": "Add a new non-frozen compiled-route adapter that spawns the public front door with child-only SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 and asserts serving authority, action, and ordered targets against route gold.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4130:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:32:- **F-2-2 Vacuous-parity gate (P0, novel).** `resolve.cjs:41-42` requires *both* `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND `servingAuthority==='compiled'` in the activation manifest. Flag-on with `servingAuthority:'legacy'` → `resolveRoute` returns null → `compiled-route.cjs:39` prints `{servingAuthority:'legacy', hubId}` → a naive lane reads "compiled matches legacy" and passes. The lane MUST assert the manifest's state for the target hub before treating the output as a real compiled decision.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4131:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:46:  {"id":"F-2-2","area":"benchmark","finding":"Vacuous-parity trap: SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 alone is insufficient. resolve.cjs:41-42 requires the per-hub activation manifest to read servingAuthority==='compiled'; otherwise resolveRoute returns null and compiled-route.cjs:39 emits a legacy sentinel that a naive lane reads as 'compiled matches legacy'.","evidence":"resolve.cjs:41-42 (flagEnabled AND servingAuthority!=='compiled'); compiled-route.cjs:36-39 (catch→legacy sentinel); .opencode/specs/.../010-live-activation/activation/sk-code/manifest.json shows servingAuthority:'compiled' (so sk-code is the valid pilot; other hubs may still be 'legacy')","severity":"P0","actionable":"compiled-parity.cjs pre-flight MUST read 010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json and treat servingAuthority!=='compiled' as status 'vacuous' (hard fail), never a pass; document the dual gate in the lane README.","novelty":"new"},
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4132:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:3:description: "The runtime engine that consumes the compiled router contract at route time, plus the per-hub serving-authority flip that makes it authoritative. Stage P4b — the literal cutover — built on top of P4a (010-live-activation, which bound each hub's compiled generation as selectedPolicy while serving authority stayed legacy). Three zero-dependency modules: an archetype-adaptive compiled-route engine that reuses each rollout child's proven closed-decision-algebra engine (evaluateCanary or evaluateRoute, by archetype — so the runtime path and the shadow-validated path are the same code), a double-gated fail-safe resolver plus CLI front-door that only serves the compiled route when the runtime flag SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 AND the hub's manifest reads servingAuthority: compiled, and a fenced compare-and-swap flip that moves a hub legacy→compiled behind green gates with a byte-exact rollback. The literal cutover is complete: all seven hubs are flipped legacy→compiled (each with a flag-gated compiled-routing directive in its live SKILL.md and archetype-adaptive re-certification), held inert behind the default-off SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flag; the frozen benchmark scorer is pinned throughout."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4133:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:27:Three zero-dependency modules do the work. An archetype-adaptive **compiled-route engine** answers `(hubId, taskText)` by loading the hub's compiled policy and reusing the **same** closed-decision-algebra engine the shadow canary already validates — the export name varies by archetype (`evaluateCanary` for the surfaceBundle canary-router, `evaluateRoute` for the plain router), so the runtime path and the shadow-validated path are literally the same code, with no reimplementation to drift. A double-gated **resolver + CLI front-door** returns the compiled decision only when the runtime flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` is set (default off) **and** the hub's activation manifest reads `servingAuthority: compiled`; otherwise it returns a legacy sentinel and the caller keeps the prose smart-router. A fenced-CAS **serving flip** moves one hub `legacy → compiled` behind green gates, retaining a byte-identical pre-flip manifest for a byte-exact rollback. The mechanism was proven end-to-end on `sk-code`, then the literal cutover was executed across all seven hubs: each hub's live `SKILL.md` gained a flag-gated compiled-routing directive, was recompiled with archetype-adaptive re-certification, and had serving authority flipped `legacy → compiled`. The cutover is inert by default and reversible two ways, and the frozen benchmark scorer is pinned untouched throughout — so live routing is unchanged until `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is enabled (compiled routing is route-gold byte-identical to legacy).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4134:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:38:| **Status** | Complete — the P4b runtime engine (archetype-adaptive compiled-route engine + resolver/CLI front-door + per-hub serving flip) is built, and the literal cutover is executed across all seven hubs: each hub carries a flag-gated compiled-routing directive in its live `SKILL.md`, was recompiled with archetype-adaptive re-certification, and had serving authority flipped `legacy → compiled` (`servingAuthority: compiled` in each `010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json`). Each flip is canary-green via the real scorer, route-gold ROUTING byte-identical (only hashes changed), with a byte-exact rollback retained (`manifest.serving-prior.json`). The runtime path is inert by default (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` off), so live routing is unchanged until the flag is enabled. Advisor-hook machine-enforcement remains in progress. Commits: engine `d7da0fca43`, sk-code cutover `2fa3357f80`, remaining-6 cutover `337ca43cfa` (pushed on v4). |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4135:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:56:Deliver the P4b runtime engine as three small, zero-dependency modules: a pure compiled-route engine that reuses each rollout child's proven canary engine (never a reimplementation), a double-gated fail-safe resolver plus CLI front-door that only serves the compiled route under an explicit runtime flag and a per-hub serving flag, and a fenced compare-and-swap flip that moves a hub `legacy → compiled` behind green gates with a proven byte-exact rollback — then prove the whole path end-to-end on one hub, keep the frozen scorer pinned, and execute the rollout across all seven hubs (wire each live `SKILL.md`, re-certify, and flip serving authority) behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag so live routing is unchanged until it is enabled.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4136:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:68:- The **resolver + CLI front-door** `lib/resolve.cjs` — double-gated (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND manifest `servingAuthority: compiled`), fail-safe (errors → null), with a `--hub/--prompt` CLI that prints the compiled decision or a legacy sentinel.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4137:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:75:- Wiring each hub's live `SKILL.md` routing directive to call the resolver - [note] beyond the initial engine build, but now **complete**: each of the seven hubs carries an additive, flag-gated compiled-routing directive that shells to the resolver front-door and self-gates on serving authority (inert while `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is off).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4138:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:89:> The engine and resolver are pure and read-only. Only the flip mutates state, and it does so on the P4a activation manifest under `010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/` (the serving pointer the resolver reads) — never on a live routing file or the scorer. The runtime path stays inert until `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` is set for a hub that has been flipped.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4139:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:104:| REQ-003 | The resolver serves the compiled route ONLY when both gates hold, and is otherwise inert. | `resolveRoute(hubId, taskText)` returns null unless `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND the hub's `010-live-activation` manifest reads `servingAuthority: compiled`; with the flag off it returns null / the CLI prints a legacy sentinel. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4140:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:113:| REQ-007 | Prove the whole path end-to-end on one hub, then execute the cutover across all seven. | On `sk-code`: flip → `servingAuthority: compiled` with green gates → the front-door returns `action: route` (flag on) and a legacy sentinel (flag off) → byte-exact `--rollback` proven. All seven hubs are then flipped `legacy → compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, each canary-green with a retained byte-identical serving-prior; the frozen scorer digests are unchanged. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4141:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:124:- **SC-002**: The resolver is inert by default and double-gated — no compiled route is served unless `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` and the hub reads `servingAuthority: compiled`; it fails safe to legacy on any error.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4142:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:126:- **SC-004**: The path is proven end-to-end on `sk-code` (flip → compiled-served route → byte-exact rollback), and the cutover is then executed across all seven hubs — each flipped `legacy → compiled` and left compiled-serving but inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, with a byte-identical serving-prior retained for a byte-exact per-hub rollback.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4143:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:141:| Risk | The serving flip is the only stage that changes runtime routing | A wrong or premature flip changes what actually routes | Inert by default (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` off), per-hub gate, fenced CAS, byte-exact rollback, one hub at a time |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4144:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/spec.md:158:- **NFR-R02**: The cutover is reversible two independent ways — unset `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` fleet-wide (the resolver returns null everywhere) or flip a single hub back to `legacy` (per hub).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4146:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:34:| **Serving gate** | Double gate: runtime flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND manifest `servingAuthority: compiled`; default off = inert |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4147:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:40:P4b adds the runtime consumer P4a left out, as three small modules. `compiled-route.cjs` is an archetype-adaptive pure engine: given `(hubId, taskText)` it loads the hub's compiled snapshot and routes it through the child's own engine — `evaluateCanary` or `evaluateRoute`, by archetype — returning a normalized decision and deferring on off-signal prompts. `resolve.cjs` is the safety gate: it serves the compiled decision only when the runtime flag is set and the hub's manifest reads `servingAuthority: compiled`, fails safe to null on any error, and exposes a `--hub/--prompt` CLI front-door. `flip-serving.cjs` is the operated switch: a fenced CAS that moves a hub `legacy → compiled` behind a P4a-binding check, a green canary, the frozen-scorer pin, and a live-route proof, retaining a byte-identical pre-flip manifest so `--rollback` is byte-exact. The path was proven on `sk-code`, then the cutover was executed across all seven hubs — each live `SKILL.md` wired with an additive flag-gated directive, recompiled with archetype-adaptive re-certification, and flipped `legacy → compiled` — held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag with a byte-exact rollback retained per hub.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4148:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:80:Prompt → `resolveRoute(hubId, taskText)` → gate 1 flag (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`) and gate 2 manifest (`servingAuthority: compiled`) → on pass, `compiledRoute` loads the hub's rollout-child engine and routes via its archetype engine (`evaluateCanary` or `evaluateRoute`) → normalized decision returned; on any miss or error, null → caller keeps the legacy prose smart-router. The flip path is operated out-of-band: `flip-serving.cjs` proves the four gates, retains the pre-flip manifest, swaps `servingAuthority` and advances the fence, and records `serving-flip-record.json`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4149:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:96:| Runtime flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` | Off by default | Read by the resolver | Flag off ⇒ resolver returns null everywhere (inert) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4150:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:97:| Live `SKILL.md` (per hub) | Authoritative serving routing | **Wired — additive, flag-gated compiled-routing directive added** | Each of the 7 hubs' `SKILL.md` shells to the resolver front-door under `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`, self-gating on serving authority; existing prose routing unchanged |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4151:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:137:| Gating | Flag off / manifest legacy ⇒ inert; both on ⇒ served | `resolve.cjs --hub … --prompt …` with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` on and off |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4152:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:154:| Runtime flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` | Internal | Off (default) | The compiled path is inert until explicitly enabled per rollout |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4153:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:165:- **Procedure**: Two independent reversals. Fleet-wide — unset `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, and the resolver returns null everywhere (legacy serves) with no manifest change. Per hub — `flip-serving.cjs --hub <id> --rollback` restores the byte-identical `manifest.serving-prior.json` and advances the fence; confirm `servingAuthority` reverts to `legacy` and `shadowOnly` to `true`. Retain the serving-prior for the full bake window before any cleanup.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4154:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:211:1. Fleet-wide: unset `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` (resolver returns null everywhere; no manifest change).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4158:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/flip-serving.cjs:16:// runtime only honors the flip when SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 (see resolve.cjs).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4160:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs:7://   1. the runtime flag SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 is set (default off), and
