.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4162:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/checklist.md:64:  - **Evidence**: `resolveRoute` returns null unless `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND the manifest reads `servingAuthority: compiled`; the flag-off CLI prints the legacy sentinel `{servingAuthority: legacy, hubId}`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4163:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/checklist.md:84:  - **Evidence**: Each hub's committed `manifest.json` reads `servingAuthority: compiled`, `shadowOnly: false`; the runtime path is inert by default (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` off), so live routing is unchanged until the flag is enabled (compiled routing is route-gold byte-identical), and each hub is byte-exact-reversible via its retained `manifest.serving-prior.json`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4164:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/checklist.md:147:**Completion Boundary**: The per-hub live-`SKILL.md` routing directive and the seven-hub `legacy → compiled` serving flip are complete, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag and byte-exact-reversible. Post-flip real-model re-verification is treated as satisfied by the P4a T9 result plus flag-off inertness; the one item still in progress is the advisor-hook machine-enforcement layer.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4168:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:39:- [x] T004 Author `lib/resolve.cjs` — the double-gated (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND `servingAuthority: compiled`), fail-safe resolver with a `--hub/--prompt` CLI front-door.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/logs/iter-015.err:4169:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:67:- [x] T012 Prove the front-door: with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` the CLI returns `action: route` to the `code-quality` surface (sk-code/quality mode); with the flag off it returns the legacy sentinel.
