.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/009-non-hub-rollout/004-system-spec-kit/activation/manifest.json:1:{"schemaVersion":"V1","selectedPolicy":{"effectivePolicyHash":null,"generation":0},"servingAuthority":"legacy","shadowOnly":true}
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:17:      "finding": "Vacuous-parity trap: SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 alone is insufficient. resolve.cjs:41-42 requires the per-hub activation manifest to read servingAuthority==='compiled'; otherwise resolveRoute returns null and compiled-route.cjs:39 emits a legacy sentinel that a naive lane reads as 'compiled matches legacy'.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:18:      "evidence": "resolve.cjs:41-42 (flagEnabled AND servingAuthority!=='compiled'); compiled-route.cjs:36-39 (catch→legacy sentinel); .opencode/specs/.../010-live-activation/activation/sk-code/manifest.json shows servingAuthority:'compiled' (so sk-code is the valid pilot; other hubs may still be 'legacy')",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:20:      "actionable": "compiled-parity.cjs pre-flight MUST read 010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json and treat servingAuthority!=='compiled' as status 'vacuous' (hard fail), never a pass; document the dual gate in the lane README.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:39:      "finding": "Spec-tree resolver coupling: compiled-route.cjs:16-21 resolves the resolver from inside .opencode/specs/.../011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs. Specs are mutable planning artifacts; a rename silently breaks the resolver and the catch at compiled-route.cjs:36-39 returns the legacy sentinel, producing vacuous parity. ZERO activation/manifest.json or compiled/route-gold.typed.json live under .opencode/skills/<hub>/ — all 19 + 12 live under specs only.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:40:      "evidence": "compiled-route.cjs:16-21 (path.resolve into specs/); find results: 19 activation/manifest.json + 12 route-gold.typed.json ALL under .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-.../007-unified-refactor-implementation/, ZERO under .opencode/skills/<hub>/",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:50:      "finding": "Hub-type detection (isHubTypeSkill, run-skill-benchmark.cjs:68 keys on hub-router.json) is misaligned with compiled-serving eligibility (keys on activation manifest + advisor-recommend.ts COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS allowlist). A hub can have --route-gold auto-on while compiled-parity is structurally N/A.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:83:      "finding": "The feature-flag governance catalog must document compiled-routing polarity and rollback because the live handler directly gates enrichment on SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:128:      "evidence": ".opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs:16",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:172:      "evidence": ".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:73",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:229:      "actionable": "Add report.compiledRouting to the orchestrator JSON and render that block through build-report.cjs without editing the frozen scorer trio.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:251:      "actionable": "Generate parity reports through the public front door against the active 010-live-activation manifests and store their hashes/status in compiledRouting; never treat 006 candidates as serving proof.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:281:      "finding": "The advisor launcher strips SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING before spawning the daemon, so a parent-profile canary cannot activate the live advisor path.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:326:      "evidence": ".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:35",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:380:      "finding": "Two duplicated allowlists for the same 7 compiled-serving hubs (`advisor-recommend.ts:41-49` COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS Set vs spec-tree `compiled-route.cjs:23-31` HUB_CHILD map) have no cross-check; an 8th hub added to one but not the other causes the advisor to attach a `compiledRoute` field the resolver cannot compute, or vice versa.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:381:      "evidence": ".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:41-49 vs .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:23-31",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:383:      "actionable": "Add a Vitest in `system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/tests/handlers/advisor-recommend.vitest.ts` that requires the spec-tree's `compiled-route.cjs` and asserts `Array.from(COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS).sort().join(',') === Object.keys(require(...).HUB_CHILD).sort().join(',')`. Fail with P0 message naming the diverging hub. Add the same check to the existing 014-benchmark-alignment parity harness.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:471:      "actionable": "Implement the planned compiledRouting JSON-to-Markdown block in build-report.cjs and cover it with a rendered-report fixture test; do not hand-author per-run reports.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:534:      "finding": "The live playbook executor never explicitly enables SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING for its child process, so a LUNA run cannot deterministically exercise the compiled path.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:537:      "actionable": "Add a new non-frozen compiled-route adapter that spawns the public front door with child-only SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1 and asserts serving authority, action, and ordered targets against route gold.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:644:      "finding": "The bridge's `CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST` (mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs:58-87) also lacks `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, so the CLI fallback path (`buildCliBrief` → `runCliRecommend` at line 672-735) spawns a child without the flag even if the parent set it; this is a second env-strip layer beyond the launcher strip already documented in F-5-1.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:647:      "actionable": "Add `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` to the bridge allowlist at line 58-87 alongside the other `SPECKIT_ADVISOR_*` entries so the CLI subprocess can read the flag; verify the in-process native path also reads it (it does at line 459 via `env[DISABLED_ENV]` pattern).",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:655:      "finding": "`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is not documented in `system-spec-kit/mcp-server/ENV-REFERENCE.md` despite being a load-bearing runtime flag with default-OFF/ON semantics and per-hub interaction — operators have no authoritative reference and no propagation guidance.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:656:      "evidence": ".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/ENV-REFERENCE.md (zero hits for SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING)",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:658:      "actionable": "Add an entry with default=OFF, type=boolean, source `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs:10` and `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:362`, plus a propagation note that both the launcher and bridge allowlists must include it (per F-8-2).",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:667:      "evidence": ".opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js:826-861; .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-status.ts (zero hits for servingAuthority); .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/activation/sk-code/manifest.json:1",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:669:      "actionable": "Add a `compiled_routing_status` MCP tool (or extend `advisor_status` with a `compiledRouting.hubs: [{hubId, servingAuthority, generation, manifestMtime}]` field) that reads each hub's manifest via the same canonical ACTIVATION_ROOT path resolve.cjs:19 uses.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:680:      "actionable": "Either add a `--multi --hubs <csv>` mode to compiled-route.cjs that batches per prompt, or import the resolver in-process (after ADR-003 promotion to `.opencode/bin/lib/`), or memoize compiledRoute results per (hubId, prompt) per process with a short TTL.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:788:      "evidence": ".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:35-58",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:832:      "evidence": ".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:33-36",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:842:      "finding": "The Lane C verdict enum has no degraded/expected slot for drift-to-legacy fallback, so the new compiledRouting parity gate will collapse three observably distinct states (compiled-serving-with-route-gold-violation, drifted-legacy-fallback, broken-resolver) into one BLOCKED signal — directly violating 012 REQ-004 which mandates drift be scored as degraded/expected.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:843:      "evidence": "score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1765-1773 (verdict enum); 012 spec.md:99+133 (REQ-004 three-state observability contract); 014 spec.md:134-136 (compiledRouting gate OR-combined with routeGold.gate.failed)",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:845:      "actionable": "Add a distinct DEGRADED|LEGACY-FALLBACK|DRIFTED sub-verdict to the Lane C enum and have compiledRouting.blockedReason route to it instead of being OR-combined with routeGold.gate.failed; require a regression test asserting the three states produce distinct verdict values.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:853:      "finding": "reduceRouteTelemetry emits telemetryMissingRate/routeMissRate/aliasMissRate/bundleMissRate for the legacy replay only; the planned compiledRouting block is a sibling block, not a parallel compiled.telemetryMissingRate row, so an operator reading report.advisorySignals.routeTelemetry cannot distinguish a hub whose compiled path is silently failing from one whose compiled path is healthy.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:854:      "evidence": "score-skill-benchmark.cjs:745-791 (reduceRouteTelemetry operates on routerResult.routeTelemetry from line 1541); 014 spec.md:107 (compiledRouting as sibling report block, not additive routeTelemetry row)",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:864:      "finding": "No CLI ships a per-hub serving-status readout. 012 REQ-004 mandates it (compiled-serving | legacy-fallback | drifted) and 012 tasks.md:86 (T007) is open, but no module path exists; the seven activation manifests are only inspectable by cat'ing seven files, and compiled-route.cjs resolves (hub,prompt) -> decision rather than fleet -> status[].",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:867:      "actionable": "Ship .opencode/bin/compiled-route-status.cjs with --hub <id> and --all modes reading the seven activation manifests; emit {hubId, servingAuthority, shadowOnly, selectedPolicy.generation, effectivePolicyHash, fenceEpoch, manifestFingerprint} as a stable JSON contract that 014's compiledRouting parity lane can consume as the authoritative status probe referenced at 014 spec.md:103.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:875:      "finding": "isHubTypeSkill (run-skill-benchmark.cjs:68-70) keys route-gold auto-on by hub-router.json file existence, NOT by compiled-eligibility (which requires entry in COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS at advisor-recommend.ts:41-49 AND a manifest at 010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json); a hub-type-but-not-compiled-eligible scenario would route-gold ENFORCED while compiledRouting auto -> off, and operators must reason about both flags to know what was scored.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:876:      "evidence": "run-skill-benchmark.cjs:68-70 (isHubTypeSkill = fs.existsSync hub-router.json); advisor-recommend.ts:41-49 (COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS = {sk-code, mcp-tooling, system-deep-loop, cli-external-orchestration, sk-prompt, sk-design, sk-doc}); resolve.cjs:42 (servingAuthority derived from manifest, not hub-router.json); 014 spec.md:242 (compiledRouting flag mirrors route-gold)",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:886:      "finding": "routeGold.gate.failed (score-skill-benchmark.cjs:1767) is the only blockable verdict that consumes a per-hub mechanism, but the planned OR-combination with compiledRouting.gate.failed in 014 will collapse three observably distinct states into one BLOCKED signal — an operator triaging a P4 rollout cannot tell route drift from manifest churn from engine throw without opening JSON, which defeats the per-hub observability 012 REQ-004 mandates.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:889:      "actionable": "Encode compiledRouting state as a sub-cause of the verdict (compiled-serving | legacy-fallback-drifted | broken-compiled-path | drift-falls-back-to-legacy) and require the verdict switch to inspect compiledRouting.subVerdict BEFORE deciding BLOCKED-vs-CONDITIONAL-vs-DEGRADED; add a vitest asserting the four sub-causes produce four distinct outer verdicts.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:933:      "actionable": "Require populated compiledRouting parity metadata in report JSON before archiving the P4 evidence and render that state into the Markdown report and benchmark index.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:944:      "actionable": "Define and ship a serving-snapshot.json schema (hubId, capturedAt, flag, manifest{selectedPolicyHash,generation,fenceEpoch,servingAuthority,shadowOnly}, liveConfigHash, freshness, engineResolverPath, parityBaseline, realModelLast) and emit a renderer for serving-snapshot.md under sk-doc/create-benchmark; reference it from create-benchmark §10 storage guide and create-manual-testing-playbook run-archive convention.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:953:      "evidence": ".opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs:23-40 (resolves only (hub,prompt)->decision; --fleet flag absent); 011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs:22-48 (returns single null/decision, no fleet function); .opencode/plugins/mk-skill-advisor.js:826-861 (status tool emits cache stats, never reads the 7 manifests)",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:955:      "actionable": "Add a compiledRoutingFleetStatus block to spec_kit_skill_advisor_status (~10 lines) that reads each of the 7 manifests, recomputes each live hash via loadHubEngine(), and emits hub_serving[] plus a fleet_summary row count per state; back it by a new .opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs --fleet mode that the plugin can shell out to.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:996:      "finding": "create-skill (013 spec) plans to mint a manifest for --compiled-routing ready hubs but no spec names where the manifest lives; until the spec-tree 010-live-activation path is populated AND COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS (advisor-recommend.ts:41) is updated AND the fleet probe is wired, a freshly-scaffolded compiled-ready hub is invisible to every observability surface.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:997:      "evidence": ".opencode/specs/.../013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:73-79 (--compiled-routing legacy|ready option, mints manifest but location unspecified); system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts:41-49 (COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS hardcoded allowlist); compiled-route.cjs:23-31 (HUB_CHILD dispatch table)",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:1008:      "evidence": ".opencode/plugins/mk-dist-freshness-guard.js (compiled dist drift detection); .opencode/plugins/README.md (no compiled-routing-snapshot plugin listed); 011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:33-62 (loadHubEngine + engineCache are runtime-private, not exported for plugins)",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:1010:      "actionable": "Export loadHubEngine (or a read-only equivalent) from 011-runtime-engine/lib/compiled-route.cjs:87 to enable a session-start plugin; add .opencode/plugins/mk-compiled-routing-snapshot.js that walks the 7 manifests, runs loadHubEngine on each, and writes .opencode/skills/<hub>/benchmark/compiled-routing/latest/serving-snapshot.json with the F-12-1 schema.",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:1051:      "finding": "compiled-route.cjs fails safe to a legacy sentinel on ANY resolver error including a moved or archived spec tree, with no stderr, log, or telemetry — an invisible fleet-wide rollback if 007-unified-refactor-implementation is archived during the 019 program cutover",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:1052:      "evidence": ".opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs:16-21 + 33-39",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:1054:      "actionable": "Emit a single stderr breadcrumb inside the catch block at compiled-route.cjs:36-38 (e.g. 'compiled-route: resolver unavailable for <hub>, using legacy') so operators can grep for silent fail-safes",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:1073:      "finding": "The launcher's .env/.env.local loader (mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:70-76) runs at module top-level and injects into process.env, but createChildEnv() (line 267) filters through CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST (line 99-150) which omits SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING, so the standard 'put it in .env' operator path silently strips the flag from the spawned advisor child",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:1076:      "actionable": "Add SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING to both CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST sets (launcher line 99-150 and bridge mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs:58-87) and document the .env propagation contract in ENV-REFERENCE.md",
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/001-research/research/findings-registry.json:1183:      "finding": "Catalog current-reality wording cannot claim default-on before P4 because the shipped advisor still enables enrichment only when SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING equals 1.",
