t .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite by default; MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR overrides, with SYSTEM_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR as a legacy fallback (both still recognized by the launcher + handlers).\",\n+        \"_NOTE_3_THRESHOLDS\": \"Advisor confidence/uncertainty thresholds are tunable: SPECKIT_ADVISOR_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD (default 0.8), SPECKIT_ADVISOR_UNCERTAINTY_THRESHOLD (default 0.35). Lane weights tunable via SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_WEIGHTS_JSON + SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_SHADOW_WEIGHTS_JSON (partial-merge JSON, post-022/011/4b).\",\n+        \"_NOTE_DOC_TRIGGERS\": \"Opt-in doc-frontmatter harvest: skill_graph_scan ingests references/assets trigger_phrases into skill_docs and advisor_recommend returns matchedDocs pointers (dampened derived-lane signal). Default-off in code; enabled for this repo. Unset/false to roll back.\",\n+        \"_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET\": \"Shared hf-local model-server socket — identical to mk-spec-memory's so both services share ONE resident nomic server. (skill-advisor only spawns it when SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_MODEL_SERVER_ENABLED=1; otherwise it just connects to mk-spec-memory's.)\",\n+        \"_NOTE_TRUST_DEFAULT\": \"Daemon-owner trust grant for mutation tools (advisor_rebuild, skill_graph_scan, skill_graph_propagate_enhances). Callers whose _meta omits transport/trust markers default to UNTRUSTED unless this is 'trusted'. Native MCP clients (e.g. /doctor repair flows) send no _meta, so this grant keeps them working; remove it to fail-closed on every transport-absent caller. Explicit _meta trusted:false / callerAuthority:'untrusted' is always rejected.\"\n       }\n     },\n     \"mk_code_index\": {\n@@ -49,7 +66,10 @@\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-code-index\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n+        \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\",\n+        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Database lives SKILL-LOCAL at .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/database/code-graph.sqlite by default (shared across runtimes via the .opencode/skills symlink); SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR overrides. Former shared location (.opencode/.spec-kit/code-graph/database/) is migrated back on first launcher startup.\",\n+        \"_NOTE_3_INDEX_DEFAULTS\": \"INDEX_* committed defaults are false (end-user safe). Maintainer mode: set SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_MAINTAINER_MODE=true in .env.local (gitignored); the launcher will force all 5 INDEX_* to true at startup. Per-call code_graph_scan args (includeSkills, includeAgents, includeCommands, includeSpecs, includePlugins) still override env for fine-grained control.\",\n+        \"_NOTE_4_RESCAN_THRESHOLD\": \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_SELECTIVE_REINDEX_THRESHOLD (default 50) controls when the launcher switches from selective rescan to full scan. Raise to delay full-scans (faster session-boot, more drift tolerance); lower to keep the DB tighter. Post-commit hook (.opencode/scripts/git-hooks/post-commit) also invalidates the SQLite when commits exceed SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_POST_COMMIT_REBUILD_THRESHOLD (default 100).\"\n       }\n     },\n     \"code_mode\": {\n","exit":0,"description":"Shows requested 645bd69fb2 MCP diff","truncated":false},"title":"Shows requested 645bd69fb2 MCP diff","time":{"start":1781429035666,"end":1781429035669}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f4f28c855ae21c7016a2e732b77088191ac8676f545eff76e"}},"id":"prt_ec571e267001WoXUBj4Zd4iWAc","sessionID":"ses_13a8edfe1ffeH4pzgs6S8Je2He","messageID":"msg_ec5719198001s5dukfkzJifuhc"}}
.opencode/specs/system-code-graph/z_archive/034-code-graph-scatter-from-027/001-code-graph-code-only-indexing/review/deltas/iter-004-raw.json:16:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781429035676,"sessionID":"ses_13a8edfe1ffeH4pzgs6S8Je2He","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_0a9n238sBoo48mu3cVsZKuJQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"git show c67a972b88 -- .claude/mcp.json opencode.json .codex/config.toml","timeout":120000,"workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public","description":"Shows requested c67a972b88 config diff"},"output":"commit c67a972b88265925e07bc2273620fc09c3f9a500\nAuthor: Michel Kerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>\nDate:   Sun Jun 14 09:00:06 2026 +0200\n\n    feat(027): daemon re-election on by default + MCP config 1:1 alignment\n    \n    Flip the launcher code default for SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION from off to on\n    (daemonReelectionEnabled now returns true unless explicitly '0'/'off'), so the\n    shared daemon outlives its owning session by default rather than only when a\n    runtime config opts in. Invert the unit test's default assertion accordingly\n    (5/5 green) and sync the living docs (ENV_REFERENCE, README, feature_catalog,\n    playbook) to \"on by default in launcher code\"; the historical changelog is left\n    as the accurate as-of-release record.\n    \n    Sort + align the four MCP runtime configs 1:1 (.mcp.json -> .claude/mcp.json\n    symlink, opencode.json, .codex/config.toml): fix the invalid-JSON missing comma\n    in the code-index block, strip all _NOTE_* pseudo-comment env keys, drop the now\n    redundant explicit SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION entries (the code default covers\n    them), rename legacy SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED to\n    MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED, align SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS across all\n    four, and alphabetise each server's env block so every block is byte-identical\n    across files.\n    \n    Embeddings unchanged: Ollama stays preferred via EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=auto;\n    HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL is only the shared hf-local fallback socket, not a provider\n    switch.\n    \n    Spec-folder documentation (027/004-shared-infrastructure) is deferred while a\n    concurrent session restructures the 027 spec tree.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\ndiff --git a/.claude/mcp.json b/.claude/mcp.json\nindex 0ff82b6e8f..26c17227a9 100644\n--- a/.claude/mcp.json\n+++ b/.claude/mcp.json\n@@ -13,28 +13,13 @@\n       ],\n       \"env\": {\n         \"EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER\": \"auto\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-spec-memory\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION\": \"1\",\n-        \"_NOTE_DAEMON_REELECTION\": \"Daemon survives its owning session: on disposal the launcher releases the shared daemon for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. An unadopted released daemon is bounded by SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MIN. Set 0 to restore kill-on-disposal. See ENV_REFERENCE.md.\",\n         \"HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL\": \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING\": \"300000\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-spec-memory\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\",\n         \"SPECKIT_RETRY_BATCH_SIZE\": \"100\",\n         \"SPECKIT_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS\": \"5000\",\n         \"SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_AGE_MS\": \"3153600000000\",\n-        \"_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET\": \"Shared hf-local model-server socket. Pinned identically for mk-spec-memory AND mk_skill_advisor so both consume ONE resident nomic server (single-owner via the socket-keyed respawn lock). Short /tmp path stays under the macOS sun_path 104-char limit. Do not diverge the two services.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~7,000–8,000 tokens (largest MCP surface; 37 tools across 8 families). Project-wide MCP context budget: ~16–21K tokens total — see code_mode env block for the rollup.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_RETRY_TUNING\": \"Bulk re-embed retry tuning: raised pending cap + max-age + faster batch/interval so a large embedding backlog drains instead of being parked as failed (defaults park excess/old pending: cap 1000, 24h age, 5-per-5min).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_SOCKET\": \"macOS sun_path limit (104 chars): the default bridge socket path under database/daemon-ipc.sock exceeds the limit and the launcher fails with EINVAL. Pin to a short /tmp path so the multi-client bridge can bind.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_RECOMMENDED_SETUP\": \"New users: install Ollama (https://ollama.com) and run `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5`. The cascade auto-detects Ollama and persists nomic-embed-text-v1.5 (768d) as the active embedder — no API keys, all-local.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Default DB (recommended): context-index__ollama__nomic-embed-text-v1.5__768.sqlite (auto-derived from provider+model+dim). Pull `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5` for the local-first new-user setup; hf-local with nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5 is the zero-install Node fallback (no Python).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_2_TOOLS\": \"Registers 37 tools across families (verified against mcp_server/tool-schemas.ts): memory_save/search/context/match_triggers/index_scan/stats/health/validate/update/delete/bulk_delete/list/drift_why/retention_sweep/get_learning_history/quick_search/embedding_reconcile (17 memory), memory_causal_link/causal_unlink/causal_stats (3 causal), memory_ingest_start/status/cancel (3 async ingest), embedder_list/set/status (3 embedder), session_bootstrap/resume/health (3 session), checkpoint_create/list/restore/delete (4 checkpoint), task_preflight/postflight (2 task), eval_run_ablation/reporting_dashboard (2 eval). MCP namespace: mcp__mk_spec_memory__*. Note: coverage-graph and council graph operations are owned by deep-loop-runtime CLI modules and are NOT exposed as MCP tools.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_3_PROVIDERS\": \"Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama (local) -> hf-local (pure-Node @huggingface/transformers HTTP model server, zero-install) -> OpenAI API -> Voyage API.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_4_EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER\": \"Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama -> hf-local -> OpenAI -> Voyage. Set EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=<provider> (ollama|hf-local|openai|voyage) to force a specific tier.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_5_CLOUD_PROVIDERS\": \"Cloud tiers are explicit opt-in: add VOYAGE_API_KEY or OPENAI_API_KEY only when you want cloud embeddings; otherwise the cascade keeps everything local. Voyage is embeddings-only here; cloud rerankers (voyage/cohere) were removed in 022/013.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_6_GET_VOYAGE_KEY\": \"Get Voyage key: https://dash.voyageai.com/api-keys\",\n-        \"_NOTE_7_GET_OPENAI_KEY\": \"Get OpenAI key: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys\",\n-        \"_NOTE_8_FEATURE_FLAGS\": \"Opt-out flags (default ON): SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION, SPECKIT_SESSION_BOOST, SPECKIT_CAUSAL_BOOST, SPECKIT_HYDE_ACTIVE, SPECKIT_ENTITY_LINKING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_CONCEPT_ROUTING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_REFRESH_MODE=write_local. Tier 3 LLM save routing is always on (fail-open to Tier 2 on timeout).\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n+        \"SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING\": \"300000\"\n       }\n     },\n     \"mk_skill_advisor\": {\n@@ -43,17 +28,12 @@\n         \".opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs\"\n       ],\n       \"env\": {\n-        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-skill-advisor\",\n         \"HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL\": \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\",\n         \"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR\": \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED\": \"0\",\n+        \"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED\": \"0\",\n         \"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_TRUST_DEFAULT\": \"trusted\",\n-        \"_NOTE_TRUST_DEFAULT\": \"Daemon-owner trust grant for mutation tools (advisor_rebuild, skill_graph_scan, skill_graph_propagate_enhances). Callers whose _meta omits transport/trust markers default to UNTRUSTED unless this is 'trusted'. Native MCP clients (e.g. /doctor repair flows) send no _meta, so this grant keeps them working; remove it to fail-closed on every transport-absent caller. Explicit _meta trusted:false / callerAuthority:'untrusted' is always rejected.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET\": \"Shared hf-local model-server socket — identical to mk-spec-memory's so both services share ONE resident nomic server. (skill-advisor only spawns it when SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_MODEL_SERVER_ENABLED=1; otherwise it just connects to mk-spec-memory's.)\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~2,200 tokens (9 tools).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Database lives at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite by default; MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR overrides, with SYSTEM_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR as a legacy fallback (both still recognized by the launcher + handlers).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_2_TOOLS\": \"Registers 9 tools (8 public + 1 internal trusted-caller): advisor_recommend/rebuild/status/validate plus skill_graph_scan/query/status/validate/propagate_enhances. MCP namespace: mcp__mk_skill_advisor__*\",\n-        \"_NOTE_3_THRESHOLDS\": \"Advisor confidence/uncertainty thresholds are tunable: SPECKIT_ADVISOR_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD (default 0.8), SPECKIT_ADVISOR_UNCERTAINTY_THRESHOLD (default 0.35). Lane weights tunable via SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_WEIGHTS_JSON + SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_SHADOW_WEIGHTS_JSON (partial-merge JSON, post-022/011/4b).\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS\": \"true\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-skill-advisor\",\n         \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n       }\n     },\n@@ -63,17 +43,12 @@\n         \".opencode/bin/mk-code-index-launcher.cjs\"\n       ],\n       \"env\": {\n-        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-code-index\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS\": \"false\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS\": \"false\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~2,200 tokens (8 tools).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Database lives SKILL-LOCAL at .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/database/code-graph.sqlite by default (shared across runtimes via the .opencode/skills symlink); SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR overrides. Former shared location (.opencode/.spec-kit/code-graph/database/) is migrated back on first launcher startup.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_2_TOOLS\": \"Registers 8 tools: code_graph_scan/query/classify_query_intent/context/status/verify/apply and detect_changes. MCP namespace: mcp__mk_code_index__*\",\n-        \"_NOTE_3_INDEX_DEFAULTS\": \"INDEX_* committed defaults are false (end-user safe). Maintainer mode: set SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_MAINTAINER_MODE=true in .env.local (gitignored); the launcher will force all 5 INDEX_* to true at startup. Per-call code_graph_scan args (includeSkills, includeAgents, includeCommands, includeSpecs, includePlugins) still override env for fine-grained control.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_4_RESCAN_THRESHOLD\": \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_SELECTIVE_REINDEX_THRESHOLD (default 50) controls when the launcher switches from selective rescan to full scan. Raise to delay full-scans (faster session-boot, more drift tolerance); lower to keep the DB tighter. Post-commit hook (.opencode/scripts/git-hooks/post-commit) also invalidates the SQLite when commits exceed SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_POST_COMMIT_REBUILD_THRESHOLD (default 100).\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS\": \"false\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS\": \"false\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-code-index\",\n         \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n       }\n     },\ndiff --git a/.codex/config.toml b/.codex/config.toml\nindex e349a5372d..3f8b2a1243 100644\n--- a/.codex/config.toml\n+++ b/.codex/config.toml\n@@ -56,74 +56,46 @@ command = \"node\"\n \n [mcp_servers.code_mode.env]\n UTCP_CONFIG_FILE = \".utcp_config.json\"\n-_NOTE_TOTAL_MCP_BUDGET = \"Project-wide MCP context-token rollup (rough, wire-payload estimates at ~3.5 chars/token): mk-spec-memory ~7–8K + mk_code_index ~2.2K + mk_skill_advisor ~2.2K + sequential_thinking ~0.3K + code_mode ~1–3K = ~13–16K tokens total. On a 200K-context model this is ~8–11% of total budget; on 1M-context Opus ~2%. mk-spec-memory remains the dominant single-MCP cost. Methodology: source-byte ÷ 3.5 × wire-compression factor 0.5; full repro in .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/ (or pipe `tools/list` JSON-RPC to each launcher for exact wire bytes).\"\n \n [mcp_servers.mk-spec-memory]\n args = [\".opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs\"]\n command = \"node\"\n \n [mcp_servers.mk-spec-memory.env]\n-SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS = \"64\"\n EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER = \"auto\"\n-SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = \"/tmp/mk-spec-memory\"\n-SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION = \"1\"\n-_NOTE_DAEMON_REELECTION = \"Daemon survives its owning session: on disposal the launcher releases the shared daemon for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. An unadopted released daemon is bounded by SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MIN. Set 0 to restore kill-on-disposal. See ENV_REFERENCE.md.\"\n HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL = \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\"\n-_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET = \"Shared hf-local model-server socket. Pinned identically for mk-spec-memory AND mk_skill_advisor so both consume ONE resident nomic server (single-owner via the socket-keyed respawn lock). Short /tmp path stays under the macOS sun_path 104-char limit. Do not diverge the two services.\"\n-SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING = \"300000\"\n+SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = \"/tmp/mk-spec-memory\"\n+SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS = \"64\"\n SPECKIT_RETRY_BATCH_SIZE = \"100\"\n SPECKIT_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS = \"5000\"\n SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_AGE_MS = \"3153600000000\"\n-_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET = \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~7,000–8,000 tokens (largest MCP surface; 37 tools across 8 families). Project-wide MCP context budget: ~16–21K tokens total — see code_mode env block for the rollup.\"\n-_NOTE_RETRY_TUNING = \"Bulk re-embed retry tuning: raised pending cap + max-age + faster batch/interval so a large embedding backlog drains instead of being parked as failed (defaults park excess/old pending: cap 1000, 24h age, 5-per-5min).\"\n-_NOTE_SOCKET = \"macOS sun_path limit (104 chars): the default bridge socket path under database/daemon-ipc.sock exceeds the limit and the launcher fails with EINVAL. Pin to a short /tmp path so the multi-client bridge can bind.\"\n-_NOTE_RECOMMENDED_SETUP = \"New users: install Ollama (https://ollama.com) and run `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5`. The cascade auto-detects Ollama and persists nomic-embed-text-v1.5 (768d) as the active embedder — no API keys, all-local.\"\n-_NOTE_1_DB = \"Default DB (recommended): context-index__ollama__nomic-embed-text-v1.5__768.sqlite (auto-derived from provider+model+dim). Pull `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5` for the local-first new-user setup; hf-local with nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5 is the Python-side fallback.\"\n-_NOTE_2_TOOLS = \"Registers 37 tools across families (verified against mcp_server/tool-schemas.ts): memory_save/search/context/match_triggers/index_scan/stats/health/validate/update/delete/bulk_delete/list/drift_why/retention_sweep/get_learning_history/quick_search/embedding_reconcile (17 memory), memory_causal_link/causal_unlink/causal_stats (3 causal), memory_ingest_start/status/cancel (3 async ingest), embedder_list/set/status (3 embedder), session_bootstrap/resume/health (3 session), checkpoint_create/list/restore/delete (4 checkpoint), task_preflight/postflight (2 task), eval_run_ablation/reporting_dashboard (2 eval). MCP namespace: mcp__mk_spec_memory__*. Note: coverage-graph and council graph operations are owned by deep-loop-runtime CLI modules and are NOT exposed as MCP tools.\"\n-_NOTE_3_PROVIDERS = \"Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama (local) -> hf-local (Python sentence-transformers) -> OpenAI API -> Voyage API.\"\n-_NOTE_4_EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER = \"Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama -> hf-local -> OpenAI -> Voyage. Set EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=<provider> (ollama|hf-local|openai|voyage) to force a specific tier.\"\n-_NOTE_5_CLOUD_PROVIDERS = \"Cloud tiers are explicit opt-in: add VOYAGE_API_KEY or OPENAI_API_KEY only when you want cloud embeddings; otherwise the cascade keeps everything local. Voyage is embeddings-only here; cloud rerankers (voyage/cohere) were removed in 022/013.\"\n-_NOTE_6_GET_VOYAGE_KEY = \"Get Voyage key: https://dash.voyageai.com/api-keys\"\n-_NOTE_7_GET_OPENAI_KEY = \"Get OpenAI key: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys\"\n-_NOTE_8_FEATURE_FLAGS = \"Opt-out flags (default ON): SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION, SPECKIT_SESSION_BOOST, SPECKIT_CAUSAL_BOOST, SPECKIT_HYDE_ACTIVE, SPECKIT_ENTITY_LINKING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_CONCEPT_ROUTING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_REFRESH_MODE=write_local. Tier 3 LLM save routing is always on (fail-open to Tier 2 on timeout).\"\n+SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING = \"300000\"\n \n [mcp_servers.mk_code_index]\n args = [\".opencode/bin/mk-code-index-launcher.cjs\"]\n command = \"node\"\n \n [mcp_servers.mk_code_index.env]\n-SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS = \"64\"\n-SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = \"/tmp/mk-code-index\"\n-SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS = \"false\"\n SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS = \"false\"\n SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS = \"false\"\n-SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS = \"false\"\n SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS = \"false\"\n-_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET = \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~2,200 tokens (8 tools).\"\n-_NOTE_1_DB = \"Database lives at .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/database/code-graph.sqlite by default (skill-local); SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR overrides. Legacy shared location (.opencode/.spec-kit/code-graph/database/) is auto-migrated to the skill-local default on first launcher startup.\"\n-_NOTE_2_TOOLS = \"Registers 8 tools: code_graph_scan/query/classify_query_intent/context/status/verify/apply and detect_changes. MCP namespace: mcp__mk_code_index__*\"\n-_NOTE_3_INDEX_DEFAULTS = \"INDEX_* committed defaults are false (end-user safe). Maintainer mode: set SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_MAINTAINER_MODE=true in .env.local (gitignored); the launcher will force all 5 INDEX_* to true at startup. Per-call code_graph_scan args (includeSkills, includeAgents, includeCommands, includeSpecs, includePlugins) still override env for fine-grained control.\"\n-_NOTE_4_RESCAN_THRESHOLD = \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_SELECTIVE_REINDEX_THRESHOLD (default 50) controls when the launcher switches from selective rescan to full scan. Raise to delay full-scans (faster session-boot, more drift tolerance); lower to keep the DB tighter. Post-commit hook (.opencode/scripts/git-hooks/post-commit) also invalidates the SQLite when commits exceed SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_POST_COMMIT_REBUILD_THRESHOLD (default 100).\"\n+SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS = \"false\"\n+SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS = \"false\"\n+SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = \"/tmp/mk-code-index\"\n+SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS = \"64\"\n \n [mcp_servers.mk_skill_advisor]\n args = [\".opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs\"]\n command = \"node\"\n \n [mcp_servers.mk_skill_advisor.env]\n-SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS = \"64\"\n-SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = \"/tmp/mk-skill-advisor\"\n HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL = \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\"\n-_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET = \"Shared hf-local model-server socket — identical to mk-spec-memory's so both services share ONE resident nomic server. (skill-advisor only spawns it when SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_MODEL_SERVER_ENABLED=1; otherwise it just connects to mk-spec-memory's.)\"\n MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR = \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database\"\n-SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS = \"true\"\n-_NOTE_DOC_TRIGGERS = \"Opt-in doc-frontmatter harvest: skill_graph_scan ingests references/assets trigger_phrases into skill_docs and advisor_recommend returns matchedDocs pointers (dampened derived-lane signal). Default-off in code; enabled for this repo. Unset/false to roll back.\"\n-SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED = \"0\"\n+MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED = \"0\"\n MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_TRUST_DEFAULT = \"trusted\"\n-_NOTE_TRUST_DEFAULT = \"Daemon-owner trust grant for mutation tools (advisor_rebuild, skill_graph_scan, skill_graph_propagate_enhances). Callers whose _meta omits transport/trust markers default to UNTRUSTED unless this is 'trusted'. Native MCP clients (e.g. /doctor repair flows) send no _meta, so this grant keeps them working; remove it to fail-closed on every transport-absent caller. Explicit _meta trusted:false / callerAuthority:'untrusted' is always rejected.\"\n-_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET = \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~2,200 tokens (9 tools).\"\n-_NOTE_1_DB = \"Database lives at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite by default; MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR overrides, with SYSTEM_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR as a legacy fallback (both still recognized by the launcher + handlers).\"\n-_NOTE_2_TOOLS = \"Registers 9 tools (8 public + 1 internal trusted-caller): advisor_recommend/rebuild/status/validate plus skill_graph_scan/query/status/validate/propagate_enhances. MCP namespace: mcp__mk_skill_advisor__*\"\n-_NOTE_3_THRESHOLDS = \"Advisor confidence/uncertainty thresholds are tunable: SPECKIT_ADVISOR_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD (default 0.8), SPECKIT_ADVISOR_UNCERTAINTY_THRESHOLD (default 0.35). Lane weights tunable via SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_WEIGHTS_JSON + SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_SHADOW_WEIGHTS_JSON (partial-merge JSON, post-022/011/4b).\"\n+SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS = \"true\"\n+SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = \"/tmp/mk-skill-advisor\"\n+SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS = \"64\"\n \n [mcp_servers.sequential_thinking]\n args = [\"@modelcontextprotocol/server-sequential-thinking@2025.12.18\"]\ndiff --git a/opencode.json b/opencode.json\nindex 945767cc32..d2462a1717 100644\n--- a/opencode.json\n+++ b/opencode.json\n@@ -25,26 +25,11 @@\n         \"EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER\": \"auto\",\n         \"HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL\": \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\",\n         \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-spec-memory\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION\": \"1\",\n-        \"_NOTE_DAEMON_REELECTION\": \"Daemon survives its owning session: on disposal the launcher releases the shared daemon for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. An unadopted released daemon is bounded by SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MIN. Set 0 to restore kill-on-disposal. See ENV_REFERENCE.md.\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING\": \"300000\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\",\n         \"SPECKIT_RETRY_BATCH_SIZE\": \"100\",\n         \"SPECKIT_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS\": \"5000\",\n         \"SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_AGE_MS\": \"3153600000000\",\n-        \"_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET\": \"Shared hf-local model-server socket. Pinned identically for mk-spec-memory AND mk_skill_advisor so both consume ONE resident nomic server (single-owner via the socket-keyed respawn lock). Short /tmp path stays under the macOS sun_path 104-char limit. Do not diverge the two services.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~7,000–8,000 tokens (largest MCP surface; 37 tools across 8 families). Project-wide MCP context budget: ~16–21K tokens total — see code_mode env block for the rollup.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_RETRY_TUNING\": \"Bulk re-embed retry tuning: raised pending cap + max-age + faster batch/interval so a large embedding backlog drains instead of being parked as failed (defaults park excess/old pending: cap 1000, 24h age, 5-per-5min).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_SOCKET\": \"macOS sun_path limit (104 chars): the default bridge socket path under database/daemon-ipc.sock exceeds the limit and the launcher fails with EINVAL. Pin to a short /tmp path so the multi-client bridge can bind.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_RECOMMENDED_SETUP\": \"New users: install Ollama (https://ollama.com) and run `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5`. The cascade auto-detects Ollama and persists nomic-embed-text-v1.5 (768d) as the active embedder — no API keys, all-local.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Default DB (recommended): context-index__ollama__nomic-embed-text-v1.5__768.sqlite (auto-derived from provider+model+dim). Pull `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5` for the local-first new-user setup; hf-local with nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5 is the zero-install Node fallback (no Python).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_2_TOOLS\": \"Registers 37 tools across families (verified against mcp_server/tool-schemas.ts): memory_save/search/context/match_triggers/index_scan/stats/health/validate/update/delete/bulk_delete/list/drift_why/retention_sweep/get_learning_history/quick_search/embedding_reconcile (17 memory), memory_causal_link/causal_unlink/causal_stats (3 causal), memory_ingest_start/status/cancel (3 async ingest), embedder_list/set/status (3 embedder), session_bootstrap/resume/health (3 session), checkpoint_create/list/restore/delete (4 checkpoint), task_preflight/postflight (2 task), eval_run_ablation/reporting_dashboard (2 eval). MCP namespace: mcp__mk_spec_memory__*. Note: coverage-graph and council graph operations are owned by deep-loop-runtime CLI modules and are NOT exposed as MCP tools.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_3_PROVIDERS\": \"Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama (local) -> hf-local (pure-Node @huggingface/transformers HTTP model server, zero-install) -> OpenAI API -> Voyage API.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_4_EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER\": \"Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama -> hf-local -> OpenAI -> Voyage. Set EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=<provider> (ollama|hf-local|openai|voyage) to force a specific tier.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_5_CLOUD_PROVIDERS\": \"Cloud tiers are explicit opt-in: add VOYAGE_API_KEY or OPENAI_API_KEY only when you want cloud embeddings; otherwise the cascade keeps everything local. Voyage is embeddings-only here; cloud rerankers (voyage/cohere) were removed in 022/013.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_6_GET_VOYAGE_KEY\": \"Get Voyage key: https://dash.voyageai.com/api-keys\",\n-        \"_NOTE_7_GET_OPENAI_KEY\": \"Get OpenAI key: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys\",\n-        \"_NOTE_8_FEATURE_FLAGS\": \"Opt-out flags (default ON): SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION, SPECKIT_SESSION_BOOST, SPECKIT_CAUSAL_BOOST, SPECKIT_HYDE_ACTIVE, SPECKIT_ENTITY_LINKING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_CONCEPT_ROUTING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_REFRESH_MODE=write_local. Tier 3 LLM save routing is always on (fail-open to Tier 2 on timeout).\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n+        \"SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING\": \"300000\"\n       }\n     },\n     \"mk_skill_advisor\": {\n@@ -54,17 +39,12 @@\n         \".opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs\"\n       ],\n       \"environment\": {\n+        \"HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL\": \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\",\n         \"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR\": \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-skill-advisor\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED\": \"0\",\n+        \"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED\": \"0\",\n         \"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_TRUST_DEFAULT\": \"trusted\",\n-        \"_NOTE_TRUST_DEFAULT\": \"Daemon-owner trust grant for mutation tools (advisor_rebuild, skill_graph_scan, skill_graph_propagate_enhances). Callers whose _meta omits transport/trust markers default to UNTRUSTED unless this is 'trusted'. Native MCP clients (e.g. /doctor repair flows) send no _meta, so this grant keeps them working; remove it to fail-closed on every transport-absent caller. Explicit _meta trusted:false / callerAuthority:'untrusted' is always rejected.\",\n-        \"HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL\": \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\",\n-        \"_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET\": \"Shared hf-local model-server socket — identical to mk-spec-memory's so both services share ONE resident nomic server. (skill-advisor only spawns it when SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_MODEL_SERVER_ENABLED=1; otherwise it just connects to mk-spec-memory's.)\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~2,200 tokens (9 tools).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Database lives at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite by default; MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR overrides, with SYSTEM_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR as a legacy fallback (both still recognized by the launcher + handlers).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_2_TOOLS\": \"Registers 9 tools (8 public + 1 internal trusted-caller): advisor_recommend/rebuild/status/validate plus skill_graph_scan/query/status/validate/propagate_enhances. MCP namespace: mcp__mk_skill_advisor__*\",\n-        \"_NOTE_3_THRESHOLDS\": \"Advisor confidence/uncertainty thresholds are tunable: SPECKIT_ADVISOR_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD (default 0.8), SPECKIT_ADVISOR_UNCERTAINTY_THRESHOLD (default 0.35). Lane weights tunable via SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_WEIGHTS_JSON + SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_SHADOW_WEIGHTS_JSON (partial-merge JSON, post-022/011/4b).\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS\": \"true\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-skill-advisor\",\n         \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n       }\n     },\n@@ -75,17 +55,12 @@\n         \".opencode/bin/mk-code-index-launcher.cjs\"\n       ],\n       \"environment\": {\n-        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-code-index\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS\": \"false\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS\": \"false\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~2,200 tokens (8 tools).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Database lives SKILL-LOCAL at .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/database/code-graph.sqlite by default (shared across runtimes via the .opencode/skills symlink); SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR overrides. Former shared location (.opencode/.spec-kit/code-graph/database/) is migrated back on first launcher startup.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_2_TOOLS\": \"Registers 8 tools: code_graph_scan/query/classify_query_intent/context/status/verify/apply and detect_changes. MCP namespace: mcp__mk_code_index__*\",\n-        \"_NOTE_3_INDEX_DEFAULTS\": \"INDEX_* committed defaults are false (end-user safe). Maintainer mode: set SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_MAINTAINER_MODE=true in .env.local (gitignored); the launcher will force all 5 INDEX_* to true at startup. Per-call code_graph_scan args (includeSkills, includeAgents, includeCommands, includeSpecs, includePlugins) still override env for fine-grained control.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_4_RESCAN_THRESHOLD\": \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_SELECTIVE_REINDEX_THRESHOLD (default 50) controls when the launcher switches from selective rescan to full scan. Raise to delay full-scans (faster session-boot, more drift tolerance); lower to keep the DB tighter. Post-commit hook (.opencode/scripts/git-hooks/post-commit) also invalidates the SQLite when commits exceed SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_POST_COMMIT_REBUILD_THRESHOLD (default 100).\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS\": \"false\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS\": \"false\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-code-index\",\n         \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n       }\n     },\n@@ -96,9 +71,7 @@\n         \".opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/mcp_server/dist/index.js\"\n       ],\n       \"environment\": {\n-        \"UTCP_CONFIG_FILE\": \".utcp_config.json\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~1–3K tokens (varies by .utcp_config.json declared tool surface).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_TOTAL_MCP_BUDGET\": \"Project-wide MCP context-token rollup (rough, wire-payload estimates at ~3.5 chars/token): mk-spec-memory ~7–8K + mk_code_index ~2.2K + mk_skill_advisor ~2.2K + sequential_thinking ~0.3K + code_mode ~1–3K = ~13–16K tokens total. On a 200K-context model this is ~8–11% of total budget; on 1M-context Opus ~2%. mk-spec-memory remains the dominant single-MCP cost. Methodology: source-byte ÷ 3.5 × wire-compression factor 0.5; full repro in .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/ (or pipe `tools/list` JSON-RPC to each launcher for exact wire bytes).\"\n+        \"UTCP_CONFIG_FILE\": \".utcp_config.json\"\n       }\n     }\n   },\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\nK_DISABLED to\n    MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED, align SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS across all\n    four, and alphabetise each server's env block so every block is byte-identical\n    across files.\n    \n    Embeddings unchanged: Ollama stays preferred via EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=auto;\n    HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL is only the shared hf-local fallback socket, not a provider\n    switch.\n    \n    Spec-folder documentation (027/004-shared-infrastructure) is deferred while a\n    concurrent session restructures the 027 spec tree.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\ndiff --git a/.claude/mcp.json b/.claude/mcp.json\nindex 0ff82b6e8f..26c17227a9 100644\n--- a/.claude/mcp.json\n+++ b/.claude/mcp.json\n@@ -13,28 +13,13 @@\n       ],\n       \"env\": {\n         \"EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER\": \"auto\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-spec-memory\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION\": \"1\",\n-        \"_NOTE_DAEMON_REELECTION\": \"Daemon survives its owning session: on disposal the launcher releases the shared daemon for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. An unadopted released daemon is bounded by SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MIN. Set 0 to restore kill-on-disposal. See ENV_REFERENCE.md.\",\n         \"HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL\": \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING\": \"300000\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-spec-memory\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\",\n         \"SPECKIT_RETRY_BATCH_SIZE\": \"100\",\n         \"SPECKIT_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS\": \"5000\",\n         \"SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_AGE_MS\": \"3153600000000\",\n-        \"_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET\": \"Shared hf-local model-server socket. Pinned identically for mk-spec-memory AND mk_skill_advisor so both consume ONE resident nomic server (single-owner via the socket-keyed respawn lock). Short /tmp path stays under the macOS sun_path 104-char limit. Do not diverge the two services.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~7,000–8,000 tokens (largest MCP surface; 37 tools across 8 families). Project-wide MCP context budget: ~16–21K tokens total — see code_mode env block for the rollup.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_RETRY_TUNING\": \"Bulk re-embed retry tuning: raised pending cap + max-age + faster batch/interval so a large embedding backlog drains instead of being parked as failed (defaults park excess/old pending: cap 1000, 24h age, 5-per-5min).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_SOCKET\": \"macOS sun_path limit (104 chars): the default bridge socket path under database/daemon-ipc.sock exceeds the limit and the launcher fails with EINVAL. Pin to a short /tmp path so the multi-client bridge can bind.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_RECOMMENDED_SETUP\": \"New users: install Ollama (https://ollama.com) and run `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5`. The cascade auto-detects Ollama and persists nomic-embed-text-v1.5 (768d) as the active embedder — no API keys, all-local.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Default DB (recommended): context-index__ollama__nomic-embed-text-v1.5__768.sqlite (auto-derived from provider+model+dim). Pull `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5` for the local-first new-user setup; hf-local with nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5 is the zero-install Node fallback (no Python).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_2_TOOLS\": \"Registers 37 tools across families (verified against mcp_server/tool-schemas.ts): memory_save/search/context/match_triggers/index_scan/stats/health/validate/update/delete/bulk_delete/list/drift_why/retention_sweep/get_learning_history/quick_search/embedding_reconcile (17 memory), memory_causal_link/causal_unlink/causal_stats (3 causal), memory_ingest_start/status/cancel (3 async ingest), embedder_list/set/status (3 embedder), session_bootstrap/resume/health (3 session), checkpoint_create/list/restore/delete (4 checkpoint), task_preflight/postflight (2 task), eval_run_ablation/reporting_dashboard (2 eval). MCP namespace: mcp__mk_spec_memory__*. Note: coverage-graph and council graph operations are owned by deep-loop-runtime CLI modules and are NOT exposed as MCP tools.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_3_PROVIDERS\": \"Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama (local) -> hf-local (pure-Node @huggingface/transformers HTTP model server, zero-install) -> OpenAI API -> Voyage API.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_4_EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER\": \"Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama -> hf-local -> OpenAI -> Voyage. Set EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=<provider> (ollama|hf-local|openai|voyage) to force a specific tier.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_5_CLOUD_PROVIDERS\": \"Cloud tiers are explicit opt-in: add VOYAGE_API_KEY or OPENAI_API_KEY only when you want cloud embeddings; otherwise the cascade keeps everything local. Voyage is embeddings-only here; cloud rerankers (voyage/cohere) were removed in 022/013.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_6_GET_VOYAGE_KEY\": \"Get Voyage key: https://dash.voyageai.com/api-keys\",\n-        \"_NOTE_7_GET_OPENAI_KEY\": \"Get OpenAI key: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys\",\n-        \"_NOTE_8_FEATURE_FLAGS\": \"Opt-out flags (default ON): SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION, SPECKIT_SESSION_BOOST, SPECKIT_CAUSAL_BOOST, SPECKIT_HYDE_ACTIVE, SPECKIT_ENTITY_LINKING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_CONCEPT_ROUTING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_REFRESH_MODE=write_local. Tier 3 LLM save routing is always on (fail-open to Tier 2 on timeout).\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n+        \"SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING\": \"300000\"\n       }\n     },\n     \"mk_skill_advisor\": {\n@@ -43,17 +28,12 @@\n         \".opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs\"\n       ],\n       \"env\": {\n-        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-skill-advisor\",\n         \"HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL\": \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\",\n         \"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR\": \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED\": \"0\",\n+        \"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED\": \"0\",\n         \"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_TRUST_DEFAULT\": \"trusted\",\n-        \"_NOTE_TRUST_DEFAULT\": \"Daemon-owner trust grant for mutation tools (advisor_rebuild, skill_graph_scan, skill_graph_propagate_enhances). Callers whose _meta omits transport/trust markers default to UNTRUSTED unless this is 'trusted'. Native MCP clients (e.g. /doctor repair flows) send no _meta, so this grant keeps them working; remove it to fail-closed on every transport-absent caller. Explicit _meta trusted:false / callerAuthority:'untrusted' is always rejected.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET\": \"Shared hf-local model-server socket — identical to mk-spec-memory's so both services share ONE resident nomic server. (skill-advisor only spawns it when SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_MODEL_SERVER_ENABLED=1; otherwise it just connects to mk-spec-memory's.)\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~2,200 tokens (9 tools).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Database lives at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite by default; MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR overrides, with SYSTEM_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR as a legacy fallback (both still recognized by the launcher + handlers).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_2_TOOLS\": \"Registers 9 tools (8 public + 1 internal trusted-caller): advisor_recommend/rebuild/status/validate plus skill_graph_scan/query/status/validate/propagate_enhances. MCP namespace: mcp__mk_skill_advisor__*\",\n-        \"_NOTE_3_THRESHOLDS\": \"Advisor confidence/uncertainty thresholds are tunable: SPECKIT_ADVISOR_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD (default 0.8), SPECKIT_ADVISOR_UNCERTAINTY_THRESHOLD (default 0.35). Lane weights tunable via SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_WEIGHTS_JSON + SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_SHADOW_WEIGHTS_JSON (partial-merge JSON, post-022/011/4b).\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS\": \"true\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-skill-advisor\",\n         \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n       }\n     },\n@@ -63,17 +43,12 @@\n         \".opencode/bin/mk-code-index-launcher.cjs\"\n       ],\n       \"env\": {\n-        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-code-index\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS\": \"false\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS\": \"false\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~2,200 tokens (8 tools).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Database lives SKILL-LOCAL at .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/database/code-graph.sqlite by default (shared across runtimes via the .opencode/skills symlink); SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR overrides. Former shared location (.opencode/.spec-kit/code-graph/database/) is migrated back on first launcher startup.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_2_TOOLS\": \"Registers 8 tools: code_graph_scan/query/classify_query_intent/context/status/verify/apply and detect_changes. MCP namespace: mcp__mk_code_index__*\",\n-        \"_NOTE_3_INDEX_DEFAULTS\": \"INDEX_* committed defaults are false (end-user safe). Maintainer mode: set SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_MAINTAINER_MODE=true in .env.local (gitignored); the launcher will force all 5 INDEX_* to true at startup. Per-call code_graph_scan args (includeSkills, includeAgents, includeCommands, includeSpecs, includePlugins) still override env for fine-grained control.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_4_RESCAN_THRESHOLD\": \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_SELECTIVE_REINDEX_THRESHOLD (default 50) controls when the launcher switches from selective rescan to full scan. Raise to delay full-scans (faster session-boot, more drift tolerance); lower to keep the DB tighter. Post-commit hook (.opencode/scripts/git-hooks/post-commit) also invalidates the SQLite when commits exceed SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_POST_COMMIT_REBUILD_THRESHOLD (default 100).\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS\": \"false\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS\": \"false\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-code-index\",\n         \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n       }\n     },\ndiff --git a/.codex/config.toml b/.codex/config.toml\nindex e349a5372d..3f8b2a1243 100644\n--- a/.codex/config.toml\n+++ b/.codex/config.toml\n@@ -56,74 +56,46 @@ command = \"node\"\n \n [mcp_servers.code_mode.env]\n UTCP_CONFIG_FILE = \".utcp_config.json\"\n-_NOTE_TOTAL_MCP_BUDGET = \"Project-wide MCP context-token rollup (rough, wire-payload estimates at ~3.5 chars/token): mk-spec-memory ~7–8K + mk_code_index ~2.2K + mk_skill_advisor ~2.2K + sequential_thinking ~0.3K + code_mode ~1–3K = ~13–16K tokens total. On a 200K-context model this is ~8–11% of total budget; on 1M-context Opus ~2%. mk-spec-memory remains the dominant single-MCP cost. Methodology: source-byte ÷ 3.5 × wire-compression factor 0.5; full repro in .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/ (or pipe `tools/list` JSON-RPC to each launcher for exact wire bytes).\"\n \n [mcp_servers.mk-spec-memory]\n args = [\".opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs\"]\n command = \"node\"\n \n [mcp_servers.mk-spec-memory.env]\n-SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS = \"64\"\n EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER = \"auto\"\n-SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = \"/tmp/mk-spec-memory\"\n-SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION = \"1\"\n-_NOTE_DAEMON_REELECTION = \"Daemon survives its owning session: on disposal the launcher releases the shared daemon for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. An unadopted released daemon is bounded by SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MIN. Set 0 to restore kill-on-disposal. See ENV_REFERENCE.md.\"\n HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL = \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\"\n-_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET = \"Shared hf-local model-server socket. Pinned identically for mk-spec-memory AND mk_skill_advisor so both consume ONE resident nomic server (single-owner via the socket-keyed respawn lock). Short /tmp path stays under the macOS sun_path 104-char limit. Do not diverge the two services.\"\n-SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING = \"300000\"\n+SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = \"/tmp/mk-spec-memory\"\n+SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS = \"64\"\n SPECKIT_RETRY_BATCH_SIZE = \"100\"\n SPECKIT_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS = \"5000\"\n SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_AGE_MS = \"3153600000000\"\n-_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET = \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~7,000–8,000 tokens (largest MCP surface; 37 tools across 8 families). Project-wide MCP context budget: ~16–21K tokens total — see code_mode env block for the rollup.\"\n-_NOTE_RETRY_TUNING = \"Bulk re-embed retry tuning: raised pending cap + max-age + faster batch/interval so a large embedding backlog drains instead of being parked as failed (defaults park excess/old pending: cap 1000, 24h age, 5-per-5min).\"\n-_NOTE_SOCKET = \"macOS sun_path limit (104 chars): the default bridge socket path under database/daemon-ipc.sock exceeds the limit and the launcher fails with EINVAL. Pin to a short /tmp path so the multi-client bridge can bind.\"\n-_NOTE_RECOMMENDED_SETUP = \"New users: install Ollama (https://ollama.com) and run `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5`. The cascade auto-detects Ollama and persists nomic-embed-text-v1.5 (768d) as the active embedder — no API keys, all-local.\"\n-_NOTE_1_DB = \"Default DB (recommended): context-index__ollama__nomic-embed-text-v1.5__768.sqlite (auto-derived from provider+model+dim). Pull `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5` for the local-first new-user setup; hf-local with nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5 is the Python-side fallback.\"\n-_NOTE_2_TOOLS = \"Registers 37 tools across families (verified against mcp_server/tool-schemas.ts): memory_save/search/context/match_triggers/index_scan/stats/health/validate/update/delete/bulk_delete/list/drift_why/retention_sweep/get_learning_history/quick_search/embedding_reconcile (17 memory), memory_causal_link/causal_unlink/causal_stats (3 causal), memory_ingest_start/status/cancel (3 async ingest), embedder_list/set/status (3 embedder), session_bootstrap/resume/health (3 session), checkpoint_create/list/restore/delete (4 checkpoint), task_preflight/postflight (2 task), eval_run_ablation/reporting_dashboard (2 eval). MCP namespace: mcp__mk_spec_memory__*. Note: coverage-graph and council graph operations are owned by deep-loop-runtime CLI modules and are NOT exposed as MCP tools.\"\n-_NOTE_3_PROVIDERS = \"Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama (local) -> hf-local (Python sentence-transformers) -> OpenAI API -> Voyage API.\"\n-_NOTE_4_EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER = \"Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama -> hf-local -> OpenAI -> Voyage. Set EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=<provider> (ollama|hf-local|openai|voyage) to force a specific tier.\"\n-_NOTE_5_CLOUD_PROVIDERS = \"Cloud tiers are explicit opt-in: add VOYAGE_API_KEY or OPENAI_API_KEY only when you want cloud embeddings; otherwise the cascade keeps everything local. Voyage is embeddings-only here; cloud rerankers (voyage/cohere) were removed in 022/013.\"\n-_NOTE_6_GET_VOYAGE_KEY = \"Get Voyage key: https://dash.voyageai.com/api-keys\"\n-_NOTE_7_GET_OPENAI_KEY = \"Get OpenAI key: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys\"\n-_NOTE_8_FEATURE_FLAGS = \"Opt-out flags (default ON): SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION, SPECKIT_SESSION_BOOST, SPECKIT_CAUSAL_BOOST, SPECKIT_HYDE_ACTIVE, SPECKIT_ENTITY_LINKING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_CONCEPT_ROUTING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_REFRESH_MODE=write_local. Tier 3 LLM save routing is always on (fail-open to Tier 2 on timeout).\"\n+SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING = \"300000\"\n \n [mcp_servers.mk_code_index]\n args = [\".opencode/bin/mk-code-index-launcher.cjs\"]\n command = \"node\"\n \n [mcp_servers.mk_code_index.env]\n-SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS = \"64\"\n-SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = \"/tmp/mk-code-index\"\n-SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS = \"false\"\n SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS = \"false\"\n SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS = \"false\"\n-SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS = \"false\"\n SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS = \"false\"\n-_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET = \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~2,200 tokens (8 tools).\"\n-_NOTE_1_DB = \"Database lives at .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/database/code-graph.sqlite by default (skill-local); SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR overrides. Legacy shared location (.opencode/.spec-kit/code-graph/database/) is auto-migrated to the skill-local default on first launcher startup.\"\n-_NOTE_2_TOOLS = \"Registers 8 tools: code_graph_scan/query/classify_query_intent/context/status/verify/apply and detect_changes. MCP namespace: mcp__mk_code_index__*\"\n-_NOTE_3_INDEX_DEFAULTS = \"INDEX_* committed defaults are false (end-user safe). Maintainer mode: set SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_MAINTAINER_MODE=true in .env.local (gitignored); the launcher will force all 5 INDEX_* to true at startup. Per-call code_graph_scan args (includeSkills, includeAgents, includeCommands, includeSpecs, includePlugins) still override env for fine-grained control.\"\n-_NOTE_4_RESCAN_THRESHOLD = \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_SELECTIVE_REINDEX_THRESHOLD (default 50) controls when the launcher switches from selective rescan to full scan. Raise to delay full-scans (faster session-boot, more drift tolerance); lower to keep the DB tighter. Post-commit hook (.opencode/scripts/git-hooks/post-commit) also invalidates the SQLite when commits exceed SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_POST_COMMIT_REBUILD_THRESHOLD (default 100).\"\n+SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS = \"false\"\n+SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS = \"false\"\n+SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = \"/tmp/mk-code-index\"\n+SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS = \"64\"\n \n [mcp_servers.mk_skill_advisor]\n args = [\".opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs\"]\n command = \"node\"\n \n [mcp_servers.mk_skill_advisor.env]\n-SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS = \"64\"\n-SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = \"/tmp/mk-skill-advisor\"\n HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL = \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\"\n-_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET = \"Shared hf-local model-server socket — identical to mk-spec-memory's so both services share ONE resident nomic server. (skill-advisor only spawns it when SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_MODEL_SERVER_ENABLED=1; otherwise it just connects to mk-spec-memory's.)\"\n MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR = \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database\"\n-SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS = \"true\"\n-_NOTE_DOC_TRIGGERS = \"Opt-in doc-frontmatter harvest: skill_graph_scan ingests references/assets trigger_phrases into skill_docs and advisor_recommend returns matchedDocs pointers (dampened derived-lane signal). Default-off in code; enabled for this repo. Unset/false to roll back.\"\n-SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED = \"0\"\n+MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED = \"0\"\n MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_TRUST_DEFAULT = \"trusted\"\n-_NOTE_TRUST_DEFAULT = \"Daemon-owner trust grant for mutation tools (advisor_rebuild, skill_graph_scan, skill_graph_propagate_enhances). Callers whose _meta omits transport/trust markers default to UNTRUSTED unless this is 'trusted'. Native MCP clients (e.g. /doctor repair flows) send no _meta, so this grant keeps them working; remove it to fail-closed on every transport-absent caller. Explicit _meta trusted:false / callerAuthority:'untrusted' is always rejected.\"\n-_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET = \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~2,200 tokens (9 tools).\"\n-_NOTE_1_DB = \"Database lives at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite by default; MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR overrides, with SYSTEM_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR as a legacy fallback (both still recognized by the launcher + handlers).\"\n-_NOTE_2_TOOLS = \"Registers 9 tools (8 public + 1 internal trusted-caller): advisor_recommend/rebuild/status/validate plus skill_graph_scan/query/status/validate/propagate_enhances. MCP namespace: mcp__mk_skill_advisor__*\"\n-_NOTE_3_THRESHOLDS = \"Advisor confidence/uncertainty thresholds are tunable: SPECKIT_ADVISOR_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD (default 0.8), SPECKIT_ADVISOR_UNCERTAINTY_THRESHOLD (default 0.35). Lane weights tunable via SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_WEIGHTS_JSON + SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_SHADOW_WEIGHTS_JSON (partial-merge JSON, post-022/011/4b).\"\n+SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS = \"true\"\n+SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR = \"/tmp/mk-skill-advisor\"\n+SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS = \"64\"\n \n [mcp_servers.sequential_thinking]\n args = [\"@modelcontextprotocol/server-sequential-thinking@2025.12.18\"]\ndiff --git a/opencode.json b/opencode.json\nindex 945767cc32..d2462a1717 100644\n--- a/opencode.json\n+++ b/opencode.json\n@@ -25,26 +25,11 @@\n         \"EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER\": \"auto\",\n         \"HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL\": \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\",\n         \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-spec-memory\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION\": \"1\",\n-        \"_NOTE_DAEMON_REELECTION\": \"Daemon survives its owning session: on disposal the launcher releases the shared daemon for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. An unadopted released daemon is bounded by SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MIN. Set 0 to restore kill-on-disposal. See ENV_REFERENCE.md.\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING\": \"300000\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\",\n         \"SPECKIT_RETRY_BATCH_SIZE\": \"100\",\n         \"SPECKIT_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS\": \"5000\",\n         \"SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_AGE_MS\": \"3153600000000\",\n-        \"_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET\": \"Shared hf-local model-server socket. Pinned identically for mk-spec-memory AND mk_skill_advisor so both consume ONE resident nomic server (single-owner via the socket-keyed respawn lock). Short /tmp path stays under the macOS sun_path 104-char limit. Do not diverge the two services.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~7,000–8,000 tokens (largest MCP surface; 37 tools across 8 families). Project-wide MCP context budget: ~16–21K tokens total — see code_mode env block for the rollup.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_RETRY_TUNING\": \"Bulk re-embed retry tuning: raised pending cap + max-age + faster batch/interval so a large embedding backlog drains instead of being parked as failed (defaults park excess/old pending: cap 1000, 24h age, 5-per-5min).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_SOCKET\": \"macOS sun_path limit (104 chars): the default bridge socket path under database/daemon-ipc.sock exceeds the limit and the launcher fails with EINVAL. Pin to a short /tmp path so the multi-client bridge can bind.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_RECOMMENDED_SETUP\": \"New users: install Ollama (https://ollama.com) and run `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5`. The cascade auto-detects Ollama and persists nomic-embed-text-v1.5 (768d) as the active embedder — no API keys, all-local.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Default DB (recommended): context-index__ollama__nomic-embed-text-v1.5__768.sqlite (auto-derived from provider+model+dim). Pull `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5` for the local-first new-user setup; hf-local with nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5 is the zero-install Node fallback (no Python).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_2_TOOLS\": \"Registers 37 tools across families (verified against mcp_server/tool-schemas.ts): memory_save/search/context/match_triggers/index_scan/stats/health/validate/update/delete/bulk_delete/list/drift_why/retention_sweep/get_learning_history/quick_search/embedding_reconcile (17 memory), memory_causal_link/causal_unlink/causal_stats (3 causal), memory_ingest_start/status/cancel (3 async ingest), embedder_list/set/status (3 embedder), session_bootstrap/resume/health (3 session), checkpoint_create/list/restore/delete (4 checkpoint), task_preflight/postflight (2 task), eval_run_ablation/reporting_dashboard (2 eval). MCP namespace: mcp__mk_spec_memory__*. Note: coverage-graph and council graph operations are owned by deep-loop-runtime CLI modules and are NOT exposed as MCP tools.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_3_PROVIDERS\": \"Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama (local) -> hf-local (pure-Node @huggingface/transformers HTTP model server, zero-install) -> OpenAI API -> Voyage API.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_4_EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER\": \"Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama -> hf-local -> OpenAI -> Voyage. Set EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=<provider> (ollama|hf-local|openai|voyage) to force a specific tier.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_5_CLOUD_PROVIDERS\": \"Cloud tiers are explicit opt-in: add VOYAGE_API_KEY or OPENAI_API_KEY only when you want cloud embeddings; otherwise the cascade keeps everything local. Voyage is embeddings-only here; cloud rerankers (voyage/cohere) were removed in 022/013.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_6_GET_VOYAGE_KEY\": \"Get Voyage key: https://dash.voyageai.com/api-keys\",\n-        \"_NOTE_7_GET_OPENAI_KEY\": \"Get OpenAI key: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys\",\n-        \"_NOTE_8_FEATURE_FLAGS\": \"Opt-out flags (default ON): SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION, SPECKIT_SESSION_BOOST, SPECKIT_CAUSAL_BOOST, SPECKIT_HYDE_ACTIVE, SPECKIT_ENTITY_LINKING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_CONCEPT_ROUTING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_REFRESH_MODE=write_local. Tier 3 LLM save routing is always on (fail-open to Tier 2 on timeout).\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n+        \"SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING\": \"300000\"\n       }\n     },\n     \"mk_skill_advisor\": {\n@@ -54,17 +39,12 @@\n         \".opencode/bin/mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs\"\n       ],\n       \"environment\": {\n+        \"HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL\": \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\",\n         \"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR\": \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-skill-advisor\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED\": \"0\",\n+        \"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED\": \"0\",\n         \"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_TRUST_DEFAULT\": \"trusted\",\n-        \"_NOTE_TRUST_DEFAULT\": \"Daemon-owner trust grant for mutation tools (advisor_rebuild, skill_graph_scan, skill_graph_propagate_enhances). Callers whose _meta omits transport/trust markers default to UNTRUSTED unless this is 'trusted'. Native MCP clients (e.g. /doctor repair flows) send no _meta, so this grant keeps them working; remove it to fail-closed on every transport-absent caller. Explicit _meta trusted:false / callerAuthority:'untrusted' is always rejected.\",\n-        \"HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL\": \"unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock\",\n-        \"_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET\": \"Shared hf-local model-server socket — identical to mk-spec-memory's so both services share ONE resident nomic server. (skill-advisor only spawns it when SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_MODEL_SERVER_ENABLED=1; otherwise it just connects to mk-spec-memory's.)\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~2,200 tokens (9 tools).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Database lives at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite by default; MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR overrides, with SYSTEM_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR as a legacy fallback (both still recognized by the launcher + handlers).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_2_TOOLS\": \"Registers 9 tools (8 public + 1 internal trusted-caller): advisor_recommend/rebuild/status/validate plus skill_graph_scan/query/status/validate/propagate_enhances. MCP namespace: mcp__mk_skill_advisor__*\",\n-        \"_NOTE_3_THRESHOLDS\": \"Advisor confidence/uncertainty thresholds are tunable: SPECKIT_ADVISOR_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD (default 0.8), SPECKIT_ADVISOR_UNCERTAINTY_THRESHOLD (default 0.35). Lane weights tunable via SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_WEIGHTS_JSON + SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_SHADOW_WEIGHTS_JSON (partial-merge JSON, post-022/011/4b).\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS\": \"true\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-skill-advisor\",\n         \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n       }\n     },\n@@ -75,17 +55,12 @@\n         \".opencode/bin/mk-code-index-launcher.cjs\"\n       ],\n       \"environment\": {\n-        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-code-index\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS\": \"false\",\n-        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS\": \"false\",\n         \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS\": \"false\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~2,200 tokens (8 tools).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_1_DB\": \"Database lives SKILL-LOCAL at .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/database/code-graph.sqlite by default (shared across runtimes via the .opencode/skills symlink); SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR overrides. Former shared location (.opencode/.spec-kit/code-graph/database/) is migrated back on first launcher startup.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_2_TOOLS\": \"Registers 8 tools: code_graph_scan/query/classify_query_intent/context/status/verify/apply and detect_changes. MCP namespace: mcp__mk_code_index__*\",\n-        \"_NOTE_3_INDEX_DEFAULTS\": \"INDEX_* committed defaults are false (end-user safe). Maintainer mode: set SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_MAINTAINER_MODE=true in .env.local (gitignored); the launcher will force all 5 INDEX_* to true at startup. Per-call code_graph_scan args (includeSkills, includeAgents, includeCommands, includeSpecs, includePlugins) still override env for fine-grained control.\",\n-        \"_NOTE_4_RESCAN_THRESHOLD\": \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_SELECTIVE_REINDEX_THRESHOLD (default 50) controls when the launcher switches from selective rescan to full scan. Raise to delay full-scans (faster session-boot, more drift tolerance); lower to keep the DB tighter. Post-commit hook (.opencode/scripts/git-hooks/post-commit) also invalidates the SQLite when commits exceed SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_POST_COMMIT_REBUILD_THRESHOLD (default 100).\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS\": \"false\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS\": \"false\",\n+        \"SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR\": \"/tmp/mk-code-index\",\n         \"SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS\": \"64\"\n       }\n     },\n@@ -96,9 +71,7 @@\n         \".opencode/skills/mcp-code-mode/mcp_server/dist/index.js\"\n       ],\n       \"environment\": {\n-        \"UTCP_CONFIG_FILE\": \".utcp_config.json\",\n-        \"_NOTE_CONTEXT_BUDGET\": \"Tool-schema wire payload: ~1–3K tokens (varies by .utcp_config.json declared tool surface).\",\n-        \"_NOTE_TOTAL_MCP_BUDGET\": \"Project-wide MCP context-token rollup (rough, wire-payload estimates at ~3.5 chars/token): mk-spec-memory ~7–8K + mk_code_index ~2.2K + mk_skill_advisor ~2.2K + sequential_thinking ~0.3K + code_mode ~1–3K = ~13–16K tokens total. On a 200K-context model this is ~8–11% of total budget; on 1M-context Opus ~2%. mk-spec-memory remains the dominant single-MCP cost. Methodology: source-byte ÷ 3.5 × wire-compression factor 0.5; full repro in .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/ (or pipe `tools/list` JSON-RPC to each launcher for exact wire bytes).\"\n+        \"UTCP_CONFIG_FILE\": \".utcp_config.json\"\n       }\n     }\n   },\n","exit":0,"description":"Shows requested c67a972b88 config diff","truncated":false},"title":"Shows requested c67a972b88 config diff","time":{"start":1781429035672,"end":1781429035674}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f4f28c855ae21c7016a2e732b76fc8191a29fb896c2313c30"}},"id":"prt_ec571e261001uH6vCqUqrsrVfL","sessionID":"ses_13a8edfe1ffeH4pzgs6S8Je2He","messageID":"msg_ec5719198001s5dukfkzJifuhc"}}
.opencode/specs/system-code-graph/z_archive/034-code-graph-scatter-from-027/001-code-graph-code-only-indexing/review/deltas/iter-004-raw.json:31:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781429103999,"sessionID":"ses_13a8edfe1ffeH4pzgs6S8Je2He","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_ueD9javjEWFaLHbyJuJqMRqq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"python3 -c 'import json, tomli, os, pathlib; root=pathlib.Path.cwd(); files=[\".mcp.json\",\".claude/mcp.json\",\"opencode.json\",\".codex/config.toml\"]; servers=[\"mk-spec-memory\",\"mk_skill_advisor\",\"mk_code_index\",\"code_mode\"]; data={}; print(\"symlink\", os.path.islink(root/\".mcp.json\"), os.readlink(root/\".mcp.json\") if os.path.islink(root/\".mcp.json\") else \"\");\nfor f in files:\n    p=root/f\n    if f.endswith(\".toml\"):\n        obj=tomli.loads(p.read_text())\n        envs={s: obj[\"mcp_servers\"][s].get(\"env\", {}) for s in servers}\n    else:\n        obj=json.loads(p.read_text())\n        table=obj.get(\"mcpServers\") or obj.get(\"mcp\")\n        envs={s: table[s].get(\"env\") or table[s].get(\"environment\") or {} for s in servers}\n    data[f]=envs\n    print(\"parsed\", f)\n    for s in servers:\n        print(f, s, list(envs[s].items()))\nbase=\".claude/mcp.json\"\nfor s in servers:\n    b=list(data[base][s].items())\n    for f in files:\n        same=list(data[f][s].items())==b\n        print(\"compare\", s, f, same)\nidx_keys=[\"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS\",\"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS\",\"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS\",\"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS\",\"SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS\"]\nfor f in files:\n    vals={k:data[f][\"mk_code_index\"][k] for k in idx_keys}\n    print(\"index_defaults\", f, vals)\nfor f in files:\n    print(\"doc_trigger\", f, data[f][\"mk_skill_advisor\"].get(\"SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS\"))\nfor f in files:\n    print(\"legacy_hook\", f, \"SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED\" in data[f][\"mk_skill_advisor\"], \"mk_hook\", data[f][\"mk_skill_advisor\"].get(\"MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED\"))\nfor f in files:\n    print(\"reelection_key\", f, \"SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION\" in data[f][\"mk-spec-memory\"], \"note\", \"_NOTE_DAEMON_REELECTION\" in data[f][\"mk-spec-memory\"])'","timeout":120000,"workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public","description":"Parses and compares MCP env blocks"},"output":"symlink True .claude/mcp.json\nparsed .mcp.json\n.mcp.json mk-spec-memory [('EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER', 'auto'), ('HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL', 'unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock'), ('SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR', '/tmp/mk-spec-memory'), ('SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS', '64'), ('SPECKIT_RETRY_BATCH_SIZE', '100'), ('SPECKIT_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS', '5000'), ('SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_AGE_MS', '3153600000000'), ('SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING', '300000'), ('_NOTE_1_DB', 'Default DB (recommended): context-index__ollama__nomic-embed-text-v1.5__768.sqlite (auto-derived from provider+model+dim). Pull `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5` for the local-first new-user setup; hf-local with nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5 is the zero-install Node fallback (no Python).'), ('_NOTE_3_PROVIDERS', 'Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama (local) -> hf-local (pure-Node @huggingface/transformers HTTP model server, zero-install) -> OpenAI API -> Voyage API.'), ('_NOTE_4_EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER', 'Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama -> hf-local -> OpenAI -> Voyage. Set EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=<provider> (ollama|hf-local|openai|voyage) to force a specific tier.'), ('_NOTE_5_CLOUD_PROVIDERS', 'Cloud tiers are explicit opt-in: add VOYAGE_API_KEY or OPENAI_API_KEY only when you want cloud embeddings; otherwise the cascade keeps everything local. Voyage is embeddings-only here; cloud rerankers (voyage/cohere) were removed in 022/013.'), ('_NOTE_6_GET_VOYAGE_KEY', 'Get Voyage key: https://dash.voyageai.com/api-keys'), ('_NOTE_7_GET_OPENAI_KEY', 'Get OpenAI key: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys'), ('_NOTE_8_FEATURE_FLAGS', 'Opt-out flags (default ON): SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION, SPECKIT_SESSION_BOOST, SPECKIT_CAUSAL_BOOST, SPECKIT_HYDE_ACTIVE, SPECKIT_ENTITY_LINKING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_CONCEPT_ROUTING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_REFRESH_MODE=write_local. Tier 3 LLM save routing is always on (fail-open to Tier 2 on timeout).'), ('_NOTE_DAEMON_REELECTION', 'Daemon re-election is on by default in the launcher code: on disposal the launcher releases the shared daemon for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. An unadopted released daemon is bounded by SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MIN. Set SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION=0 to restore kill-on-disposal. See ENV_REFERENCE.md.'), ('_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET', 'Shared hf-local model-server socket. Pinned identically for mk-spec-memory AND mk_skill_advisor so both consume ONE resident nomic server (single-owner via the socket-keyed respawn lock). Short /tmp path stays under the macOS sun_path 104-char limit. Do not diverge the two services.'), ('_NOTE_RECOMMENDED_SETUP', 'New users: install Ollama (https://ollama.com) and run `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5`. The cascade auto-detects Ollama and persists nomic-embed-text-v1.5 (768d) as the active embedder — no API keys, all-local.'), ('_NOTE_RETRY_TUNING', 'Bulk re-embed retry tuning: raised pending cap + max-age + faster batch/interval so a large embedding backlog drains instead of being parked as failed (defaults park excess/old pending: cap 1000, 24h age, 5-per-5min).'), ('_NOTE_SOCKET', 'macOS sun_path limit (104 chars): the default bridge socket path under database/daemon-ipc.sock exceeds the limit and the launcher fails with EINVAL. Pin to a short /tmp path so the multi-client bridge can bind.')]\n.mcp.json mk_skill_advisor [('HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL', 'unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock'), ('MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR', '.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database'), ('MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED', '0'), ('MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_TRUST_DEFAULT', 'trusted'), ('SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS', 'true'), ('SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR', '/tmp/mk-skill-advisor'), ('SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS', '64'), ('_NOTE_1_DB', 'Database lives at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite by default; MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR overrides, with SYSTEM_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR as a legacy fallback (both still recognized by the launcher + handlers).'), ('_NOTE_3_THRESHOLDS', 'Advisor confidence/uncertainty thresholds are tunable: SPECKIT_ADVISOR_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD (default 0.8), SPECKIT_ADVISOR_UNCERTAINTY_THRESHOLD (default 0.35). Lane weights tunable via SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_WEIGHTS_JSON + SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_SHADOW_WEIGHTS_JSON (partial-merge JSON, post-022/011/4b).'), ('_NOTE_DOC_TRIGGERS', 'Opt-in doc-frontmatter harvest: skill_graph_scan ingests references/assets trigger_phrases into skill_docs and advisor_recommend returns matchedDocs pointers (dampened derived-lane signal). Default-off in code; enabled for this repo. Unset/false to roll back.'), ('_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET', \"Shared hf-local model-server socket — identical to mk-spec-memory's so both services share ONE resident nomic server. (skill-advisor only spawns it when SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_MODEL_SERVER_ENABLED=1; otherwise it just connects to mk-spec-memory's.)\"), ('_NOTE_TRUST_DEFAULT', \"Daemon-owner trust grant for mutation tools (advisor_rebuild, skill_graph_scan, skill_graph_propagate_enhances). Callers whose _meta omits transport/trust markers default to UNTRUSTED unless this is 'trusted'. Native MCP clients (e.g. /doctor repair flows) send no _meta, so this grant keeps them working; remove it to fail-closed on every transport-absent caller. Explicit _meta trusted:false / callerAuthority:'untrusted' is always rejected.\")]\n.mcp.json mk_code_index [('SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS', 'false'), ('SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS', 'false'), ('SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS', 'false'), ('SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS', 'false'), ('SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS', 'false'), ('SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR', '/tmp/mk-code-index'), ('SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS', '64'), ('_NOTE_1_DB', 'Database lives SKILL-LOCAL at .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/database/code-graph.sqlite by default (shared across runtimes via the .opencode/skills symlink); SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR overrides. Former shared location (.opencode/.spec-kit/code-graph/database/) is migrated back on first launcher startup.'), ('_NOTE_3_INDEX_DEFAULTS', 'INDEX_* committed defaults are false (end-user safe). Maintainer mode: set SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_MAINTAINER_MODE=true in .env.local (gitignored); the launcher will force all 5 INDEX_* to true at startup. Per-call code_graph_scan args (includeSkills, includeAgents, includeCommands, includeSpecs, includePlugins) still override env for fine-grained control.'), ('_NOTE_4_RESCAN_THRESHOLD', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_SELECTIVE_REINDEX_THRESHOLD (default 50) controls when the launcher switches from selective rescan to full scan. Raise to delay full-scans (faster session-boot, more drift tolerance); lower to keep the DB tighter. Post-commit hook (.opencode/scripts/git-hooks/post-commit) also invalidates the SQLite when commits exceed SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_POST_COMMIT_REBUILD_THRESHOLD (default 100).')]\n.mcp.json code_mode [('UTCP_CONFIG_FILE', '.utcp_config.json')]\nparsed .claude/mcp.json\n.claude/mcp.json mk-spec-memory [('EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER', 'auto'), ('HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL', 'unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock'), ('SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR', '/tmp/mk-spec-memory'), ('SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS', '64'), ('SPECKIT_RETRY_BATCH_SIZE', '100'), ('SPECKIT_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS', '5000'), ('SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_AGE_MS', '3153600000000'), ('SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING', '300000'), ('_NOTE_1_DB', 'Default DB (recommended): context-index__ollama__nomic-embed-text-v1.5__768.sqlite (auto-derived from provider+model+dim). Pull `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5` for the local-first new-user setup; hf-local with nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5 is the zero-install Node fallback (no Python).'), ('_NOTE_3_PROVIDERS', 'Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama (local) -> hf-local (pure-Node @huggingface/transformers HTTP model server, zero-install) -> OpenAI API -> Voyage API.'), ('_NOTE_4_EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER', 'Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama -> hf-local -> OpenAI -> Voyage. Set EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=<provider> (ollama|hf-local|openai|voyage) to force a specific tier.'), ('_NOTE_5_CLOUD_PROVIDERS', 'Cloud tiers are explicit opt-in: add VOYAGE_API_KEY or OPENAI_API_KEY only when you want cloud embeddings; otherwise the cascade keeps everything local. Voyage is embeddings-only here; cloud rerankers (voyage/cohere) were removed in 022/013.'), ('_NOTE_6_GET_VOYAGE_KEY', 'Get Voyage key: https://dash.voyageai.com/api-keys'), ('_NOTE_7_GET_OPENAI_KEY', 'Get OpenAI key: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys'), ('_NOTE_8_FEATURE_FLAGS', 'Opt-out flags (default ON): SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION, SPECKIT_SESSION_BOOST, SPECKIT_CAUSAL_BOOST, SPECKIT_HYDE_ACTIVE, SPECKIT_ENTITY_LINKING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_CONCEPT_ROUTING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_REFRESH_MODE=write_local. Tier 3 LLM save routing is always on (fail-open to Tier 2 on timeout).'), ('_NOTE_DAEMON_REELECTION', 'Daemon re-election is on by default in the launcher code: on disposal the launcher releases the shared daemon for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. An unadopted released daemon is bounded by SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MIN. Set SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION=0 to restore kill-on-disposal. See ENV_REFERENCE.md.'), ('_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET', 'Shared hf-local model-server socket. Pinned identically for mk-spec-memory AND mk_skill_advisor so both consume ONE resident nomic server (single-owner via the socket-keyed respawn lock). Short /tmp path stays under the macOS sun_path 104-char limit. Do not diverge the two services.'), ('_NOTE_RECOMMENDED_SETUP', 'New users: install Ollama (https://ollama.com) and run `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5`. The cascade auto-detects Ollama and persists nomic-embed-text-v1.5 (768d) as the active embedder — no API keys, all-local.'), ('_NOTE_RETRY_TUNING', 'Bulk re-embed retry tuning: raised pending cap + max-age + faster batch/interval so a large embedding backlog drains instead of being parked as failed (defaults park excess/old pending: cap 1000, 24h age, 5-per-5min).'), ('_NOTE_SOCKET', 'macOS sun_path limit (104 chars): the default bridge socket path under database/daemon-ipc.sock exceeds the limit and the launcher fails with EINVAL. Pin to a short /tmp path so the multi-client bridge can bind.')]\n.claude/mcp.json mk_skill_advisor [('HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL', 'unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock'), ('MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR', '.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database'), ('MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED', '0'), ('MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_TRUST_DEFAULT', 'trusted'), ('SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS', 'true'), ('SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR', '/tmp/mk-skill-advisor'), ('SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS', '64'), ('_NOTE_1_DB', 'Database lives at .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite by default; MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR overrides, with SYSTEM_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR as a legacy fallback (both still recognized by the launcher + handlers).'), ('_NOTE_3_THRESHOLDS', 'Advisor confidence/uncertainty thresholds are tunable: SPECKIT_ADVISOR_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD (default 0.8), SPECKIT_ADVISOR_UNCERTAINTY_THRESHOLD (default 0.35). Lane weights tunable via SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_WEIGHTS_JSON + SPECKIT_ADVISOR_LANE_SHADOW_WEIGHTS_JSON (partial-merge JSON, post-022/011/4b).'), ('_NOTE_DOC_TRIGGERS', 'Opt-in doc-frontmatter harvest: skill_graph_scan ingests references/assets trigger_phrases into skill_docs and advisor_recommend returns matchedDocs pointers (dampened derived-lane signal). Default-off in code; enabled for this repo. Unset/false to roll back.'), ('_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET', \"Shared hf-local model-server socket — identical to mk-spec-memory's so both services share ONE resident nomic server. (skill-advisor only spawns it when SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_MODEL_SERVER_ENABLED=1; otherwise it just connects to mk-spec-memory's.)\"), ('_NOTE_TRUST_DEFAULT', \"Daemon-owner trust grant for mutation tools (advisor_rebuild, skill_graph_scan, skill_graph_propagate_enhances). Callers whose _meta omits transport/trust markers default to UNTRUSTED unless this is 'trusted'. Native MCP clients (e.g. /doctor repair flows) send no _meta, so this grant keeps them working; remove it to fail-closed on every transport-absent caller. Explicit _meta trusted:false / callerAuthority:'untrusted' is always rejected.\")]\n.claude/mcp.json mk_code_index [('SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS', 'false'), ('SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS', 'false'), ('SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS', 'false'), ('SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS', 'false'), ('SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS', 'false'), ('SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR', '/tmp/mk-code-index'), ('SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS', '64'), ('_NOTE_1_DB', 'Database lives SKILL-LOCAL at .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/database/code-graph.sqlite by default (shared across runtimes via the .opencode/skills symlink); SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR overrides. Former shared location (.opencode/.spec-kit/code-graph/database/) is migrated back on first launcher startup.'), ('_NOTE_3_INDEX_DEFAULTS', 'INDEX_* committed defaults are false (end-user safe). Maintainer mode: set SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_MAINTAINER_MODE=true in .env.local (gitignored); the launcher will force all 5 INDEX_* to true at startup. Per-call code_graph_scan args (includeSkills, includeAgents, includeCommands, includeSpecs, includePlugins) still override env for fine-grained control.'), ('_NOTE_4_RESCAN_THRESHOLD', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_SELECTIVE_REINDEX_THRESHOLD (default 50) controls when the launcher switches from selective rescan to full scan. Raise to delay