, SPECKIT_CAUSAL_BOOST, SPECKIT_HYDE_ACTIVE, SPECKIT_ENTITY_LINKING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_CONCEPT_ROUTING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_REFRESH_MODE=write_local. Tier 3 LLM save routing is always on (fail-open to Tier 2 on timeout).'), ('_NOTE_DAEMON_REELECTION', 'Daemon re-election is on by default in the launcher code: on disposal the launcher releases the shared daemon for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. An unadopted released daemon is bounded by SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MIN. Set SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION=0 to restore kill-on-disposal. See ENV_REFERENCE.md.'), ('_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET', 'Shared hf-local model-server socket. Pinned identically for mk-spec-memory AND mk_skill_advisor so both consume ONE resident nomic server (single-owner via the socket-keyed respawn lock). Short /tmp path stays under the macOS sun_path 104-char limit. Do not diverge the two services.'), ('_NOTE_RECOMMENDED_SETUP', 'New users: install Ollama (https://ollama.com) and run `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5`. The cascade auto-detects Ollama and persists nomic-embed-text-v1.5 (768d) as the active embedder — no API keys, all-local.'), ('_NOTE_RETRY_TUNING', 'Bulk re-embed retry tuning: raised pending cap + max-age + faster batch/interval so a large embedding backlog drains instead of being parked as failed (defaults park excess/old pending: cap 1000, 24h age, 5-per-5min).'), ('_NOTE_SOCKET', 'macOS sun_path limit (104 chars): the default bridge socket path under database/daemon-ipc.sock exceeds the limit and the launcher fails with EINVAL. Pin to a short /tmp path so the multi-client bridge can bind.')]\nopencode.json mk_skill_advisor [('HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL', 'unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock'), ('MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR', '.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database'), ('MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED', '0'), ('MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_TRUST_DEFAULT', 'trusted'), ('SPECKIT_ADVISOR_DOC_TRIGGERS', 'true'), ('SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR', '/