e DB tighter. Post-commit hook (.opencode/scripts/git-hooks/post-commit) also invalidates the SQLite when commits exceed SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_POST_COMMIT_REBUILD_THRESHOLD (default 100).')]\n.codex/config.toml code_mode [('UTCP_CONFIG_FILE', '.utcp_config.json')]\ncompare mk-spec-memory .mcp.json True\ncompare mk-spec-memory .claude/mcp.json True\ncompare mk-spec-memory opencode.json True\ncompare mk-spec-memory .codex/config.toml True\ncompare mk_skill_advisor .mcp.json True\ncompare mk_skill_advisor .claude/mcp.json True\ncompare mk_skill_advisor opencode.json True\ncompare mk_skill_advisor .codex/config.toml True\ncompare mk_code_index .mcp.json True\ncompare mk_code_index .claude/mcp.json True\ncompare mk_code_index opencode.json True\ncompare mk_code_index .codex/config.toml True\ncompare code_mode .mcp.json True\ncompare code_mode .claude/mcp.json True\ncompare code_mode opencode.json True\ncompare code_mode .codex/config.toml True\nindex_defaults .mcp.json {'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS': 'false'}\nindex_defaults .claude/mcp.json {'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS': 'false'}\nindex_defaults opencode.json {'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS': 'false'}\nindex_defaults .codex/config.toml {'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS': 'false', 'SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS': 'false'}\ndoc_trigger .mcp.json true\ndoc_trigger .claude/mcp.json true\ndoc_trigger opencode.json true\ndoc_trigger .codex/config.toml true\nlegacy_hook .mcp.json False mk_hook 0\nlegacy_hook .claude/mcp.json False mk_hook 0\nlegacy_hook opencode.json False mk_hook 0\nlegacy_hook .codex/config.toml False mk_hook 0\nreelection_key .mcp.json False note True\nreelection_key .claude/mcp.json False note True\nreelection_key opencode.json False note True\nreelection_key .codex/config.toml False note True\n","metadata":{"output":"symlink True .claude/mcp.json\nparsed .mcp.json\n.mcp.json mk-spec-memory [('EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER', 'auto'), ('HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL', 'unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock'), ('SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR', '/tmp/mk-spec-memory'), ('SPECKIT_MAX_SECONDARY_CLIENTS', '64'), ('SPECKIT_RETRY_BATCH_SIZE', '100'), ('SPECKIT_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS', '5000'), ('SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_AGE_MS', '3153600000000'), ('SPECKIT_RETRY_QUEUE_MAX_PENDING', '300000'), ('_NOTE_1_DB', 'Default DB (recommended): context-index__ollama__nomic-embed-text-v1.5__768.sqlite (auto-derived from provider+model+dim). Pull `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5` for the local-first new-user setup; hf-local with nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5 is the zero-install Node fallback (no Python).'), ('_NOTE_3_PROVIDERS', 'Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama (local) -> hf-local (pure-Node @huggingface/transformers HTTP model server, zero-install) -> OpenAI API -> Voyage API.'), ('_NOTE_4_EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER', 'Auto cascade (ADR-014, local-first): Ollama -> hf-local -> OpenAI -> Voyage. Set EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=<provider> (ollama|hf-local|openai|voyage) to force a specific tier.'), ('_NOTE_5_CLOUD_PROVIDERS', 'Cloud tiers are explicit opt-in: add VOYAGE_API_KEY or OPENAI_API_KEY only when you want cloud embeddings; otherwise the cascade keeps everything local. Voyage is embeddings-only here; cloud rerankers (voyage/cohere) were removed in 022/013.'), ('_NOTE_6_GET_VOYAGE_KEY', 'Get Voyage key: https://dash.voyageai.com/api-keys'), ('_NOTE_7_GET_OPENAI_KEY', 'Get OpenAI key: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys'), ('_NOTE_8_FEATURE_FLAGS', 'Opt-out flags (default ON): SPECKIT_ADAPTIVE_FUSION, SPECKIT_SESSION_BOOST, SPECKIT_CAUSAL_BOOST, SPECKIT_HYDE_ACTIVE, SPECKIT_ENTITY_LINKING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_CONCEPT_ROUTING, SPECKIT_GRAPH_REFRESH_MODE=write_local. Tier 3 LLM save routing is always on (fail-open to Tier 2 on timeout).'), ('_NOTE_DAEMON_REELECTION', 'Daemon re-election is on by default in the launcher code: on disposal the launcher releases the shared daemon for a live secondary to adopt instead of killing it, so concurrent sessions keep MCP transport. An unadopted released daemon is bounded by SPECKIT_LAUNCHER_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MIN. Set SPECKIT_DAEMON_REELECTION=0 to restore kill-on-disposal. See ENV_REFERENCE.md.'), ('_NOTE_HF_EMBED_SOCKET', 'Shared hf-local model-server socket. Pinned identically for mk-spec-memory AND mk_skill_advisor so both consume ONE resident nomic server (single-owner via the socket-keyed respawn lock). Short /tmp path stays under the macOS sun_path 104-char limit. Do not diverge the two services.'), ('_NOTE_RECOMMENDED_SETUP', 'New users: install Ollama (https://ollama.com) and run `ollama pull nomic-embed-text:v1.5`. The cascade auto-detects Ollama and persists nomic-embed-text-v1.5 (768d) as the active embedder — no API keys, all-local.'), ('_NOTE_RETRY_TUNING', 'Bulk re-embed retry tuning: raised pending cap + max-age + faster batch/interval so a large embedding backlog drains instead of being parked as failed (defaults park excess/old pending: cap 1000, 24h age, 5-per-5min).'), ('_NOTE_SOCKET', 'macOS sun_path limit (104 chars): the default bridge socket path under database/daemon-ipc.sock exceeds the limit and the launcher fails with EINVAL. Pin to a short /tmp path so the multi-client bridge can bind.')]\n.mcp.json mk_skill_advisor [('HF_EMBED_SERVER_URL', 'unix:///tmp/mk-hf-embed/hf-embed.sock'), ('MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR', '.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server