.opencode/specs/system-speckit/028-memory-search-intelligence/scratch/topology-migration-backup/identity-backups/002-spec-data-quality/006-generated-metadata-build/036-metadata-validator-status-enum/spec.md:192:- RESOLVED. The `planned` fallback for a non-enum legacy status sets `status_review_required` in the graph-metadata JSON, mirroring the existing `parent_id_review_required` field, so the dropped status is surfaced in the file rather than only in the validator report.
.opencode/specs/system-speckit/028-memory-search-intelligence/scratch/topology-migration-backup/identity-backups/002-spec-data-quality/006-generated-metadata-build/038-generator-hardening/implementation-summary.md:68:Added one shared `listPhaseChildren` helper in `is-phase-parent.ts` returning each direct spec-leaf-segment child plus a `qualifies` flag (carries spec.md or description.json). Behind the flag both `isPhaseParent` (reads `qualifies`) and `resolveChildrenIds` (maps every entry) resolve through it, so the parent classification and the derived `children_ids` can no longer disagree and a parent-counted child is never absent from `children_ids`. Flag-off keeps the legacy split detection byte-identical.
