.opencode/specs/system-speckit/028-memory-search-intelligence/scratch/topology-migration-backup/identity-backups/001-speckit-memory/009-derived-id-provenance/decision-record.md:267:**We chose**: `legacy-pre-derived-id` as the fixed sentinel `rule_version` for pre-C4-B derived rows, recorded in the migration and reused on any backfill re-run.
.opencode/specs/system-speckit/028-memory-search-intelligence/scratch/topology-migration-backup/identity-backups/001-speckit-memory/009-derived-id-provenance/decision-record.md:269:**How it works**: the backfill computes `derived_id` for legacy rows using the sentinel. New derived writes use the live rule's actual version, so legacy and new artifacts of the same triple are distinct exactly when their rule versions differ.
