    47	## 2. QUALITY GATES
    48	
    49	### Definition of Ready
    50	
    51	- [ ] P3 exposes a stable minter, manifest-location abstraction, freshness predicate, and new-hub runtime discovery.
    52	- [ ] The exact directive block in `spec.md` is approved.
    53	- [ ] Legacy remains the backward-compatible CLI default.
    54	- [ ] Existing create-skill tests pass before implementation changes.
    55	
    56	### Definition of Done
    57	
    58	- [ ] Active and canonical parent templates render matching directive blocks.
    59	- [ ] Legacy and compiled-ready states are explicit and tested.
    60	- [ ] Ready state is reported only after shared freshness verification.
    61	- [ ] Standalone scaffolding and existing parent CLI calls remain compatible.
    62	- [ ] create-skill validation and docs agree with generated behavior.
    63	- [ ] No runtime router, manifest of an existing hub, or frozen scorer file is modified.
