    31	
    32	<!-- ANCHOR:what-built -->
    33	## What Was Built
    34	
    35	The parent-hub generator will gain the same additive compiled-routing directive used by the seven established hubs and an explicit onboarding state. Legacy generation will omit the canonical manifest and remain on the fallback path. Ready generation will invoke the shared minter and report compiled-ready only after the shared predicate confirms freshness.
    36	
    37	### Planned Implementation Surfaces
    38	
    39	| Area | Planned Files | Purpose |
    40	|------|---------------|---------|
    41	| Generator | `create-skill/scripts/init_skill.py` | Parse parent state, render hub name, mint and verify ready manifests |
    42	| Templates | Active hub scaffold and canonical parent-hub template | Keep generated directives identical |
    43	| Workflow | create-skill `SKILL.md`, README, and parent reference | Ask the state explicitly and document the ordered manifest step |
    44	| Validation | `validate_skill_package.py` and create-skill contract tests | Prove both states and fail-closed outcomes |
    45	
    46	No create-skill, runtime, manifest, or scorer file was modified by this planning phase.
    47	<!-- /ANCHOR:what-built -->
    48	
    49	---
    50	
    51	<!-- ANCHOR:how-delivered -->
    52	## How It Was Delivered
    53	
    54	Implementation waits for the P3 minter, freshness predicate, canonical manifest location, and data-driven runtime discovery. After those interfaces stabilize, the two templates move together, the initializer gains the state adapter, and the existing create-skill contract suite expands to cover legacy, ready, and failure outcomes before any adoption claim.
    55	<!-- /ANCHOR:how-delivered -->
    56	
    57	---
    58	
    59	<!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->
    60	## Key Decisions
    61	
    62	| Decision | Rationale |
    63	|----------|-----------|
    64	| Add the directive to every generated parent hub | Legacy and ready hubs should share one durable SKILL.md shape; eligibility is determined by the manifest state. |
    65	| Default existing CLI calls to legacy | Preserves automation compatibility and the safe no-manifest state. |
    66	| Require the authoring workflow to ask explicitly | Human/agent-created hubs should not hide the onboarding decision behind a compatibility default. |
    67	| Delegate minting and freshness to P3 interfaces | Prevents a second eligibility algorithm or hardcoded hub map inside create-skill. |
    68	| Reject ready claims on every mint/freshness error | A safe legacy fallback must not be mislabeled as compiled-ready. |
    69	<!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->
    70	
