    10	# Implementation Plan: Lane C Compiled-Routing Benchmark Alignment
    11	
    12	<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->
    13	<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: plan-core + level2-verify | v2.2 -->
    14	<!--
    15	SELF-CHECK:
    16	- Confirm the plan names the simplest viable approach, affected surfaces, and verification path.
    17	- Match phases to the stated scope; remove setup theater that does not change the outcome.
    18	FAILURE MODES:
    19	- Over-planning, missing rollback, and treating assumptions as dependencies.
    20	-->
    21	
    22	---
    23	
    24	<!-- ANCHOR:summary -->
    25	## 1. SUMMARY
    26	
    27	### Technical Context
    28	
    29	| Aspect | Value |
    30	|--------|-------|
    31	| **Language/Stack** | Node.js/CommonJS harness plus Vitest |
    32	| **Legacy observation** | Frozen `router-replay.cjs` Mode A output |
    33	| **Compiled observation** | Public `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` child process with flag `1` |
    34	| **Gold evaluator** | Frozen `evaluateRouteGold()` export |
    35	| **Report authority** | `report.json`, with Markdown rendered by `build-report.cjs` |
    36	| **Mutation posture** | Read-only diagnostics; no manifest mint or routing-input write |
    37	
    38	### Overview
    39	
    40	Add one new parity module at the orchestrator boundary. It hashes the frozen files, asks the shared eligibility/status interface what compiled outcome is expected, obtains legacy and compiled observations, normalizes them, and evaluates both against the existing route gold. The orchestrator adds structured parity results and a distinct gate; the scorer and scenario loader remain unchanged.
    41	
    42	This design keeps responsibilities clean: existing files continue to define legacy replay and scoring, while the new harness proves the served compiled path matches them.
    43	<!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->
    44	
    45	---
    46	
    47	<!-- ANCHOR:quality-gates -->
    48	## 2. QUALITY GATES
    49	
    50	### Definition of Ready
    51	
    52	- [ ] P0 provides a stable public compiled front door and machine-readable serving-status cause.
    53	- [ ] P3 provides shared eligibility and manifest discovery without a local hub list.
    54	- [ ] Baseline hashes and legacy benchmark reports are captured.
    55	- [ ] Normalized routing fields and order semantics are approved.
    56	
    57	### Definition of Done
    58	
    59	- [ ] Every eligible route-gold row invokes the flag-on compiled front door.
    60	- [ ] Legacy and compiled projections both pass the same gold and compare equal.
    61	- [ ] Drift, no-manifest legacy, and breakage are reported distinctly.
    62	- [ ] D1-D5 legacy results remain unchanged.
    63	- [ ] JSON, Markdown, CLI, and README describe the same gate.
    64	- [ ] Frozen file hashes remain identical.
    65	<!-- /ANCHOR:quality-gates -->
    66	
    67	---
    68	
    69	<!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->
    70	## 3. ARCHITECTURE
    71	
    72	### Pattern
    73	
    74	Dual-observation adapter around an immutable scorer. The parity module converts two executor-specific shapes into one routing projection, while the current scorer continues evaluating the legacy-compatible observed shape.
    75	
    76	### Key Components
    77	
    78	- **Eligibility/status adapter**: decides whether compiled parity is required and why a sentinel occurred.
    79	- **Compiled child-process adapter**: runs the public front door with an isolated flag-on environment.
    80	- **Normalizer**: maps legacy intents and compiled qualified targets through `mode-registry.json` into action/selection/ordered targets.
    81	- **Parity evaluator**: calls frozen route-gold evaluation twice and compares routing projections.
    82	- **Report gate**: aggregates row results without changing D1-D5 values.
    83	
    84	### Data Flow
    85	
    86	```text
    87	authored scenario + gold
    88	          |
    89	          +----> frozen legacy replay ----+
    90	          |                               |
    91	          +----> flag-on compiled CLI ----+--> normalize --> gold x2 + equality
    92	                                                   |
    93	                                                   v
    94	                                          report.compiledRouting
    95	                                                   |
    96	                                      orchestrator verdict/exit gate
    97	```
    98	<!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->
    99	
   100	---
   101	
   102	<!-- ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->
   103	## FIX ADDENDUM: AFFECTED SURFACES
   104	
   105	| Surface | Current Role | Planned Action | Verification |
   106	|---------|--------------|----------------|--------------|
   107	| New parity module | None | Add invocation, normalization, parity, status, and digest logic | Dedicated Vitest suite |
   108	| `run-skill-benchmark.cjs` | Orchestrates Lane C | Call parity module and apply distinct gate | End-to-end temp report test |
   109	| `build-report.cjs` | Renders Markdown from JSON | Render compiled parity without independent scoring | JSON-to-Markdown snapshot |
   110	| Lane C README/CLI | Documents current Mode A/B behavior | Add parity option/resolved mode and report schema | Documentation test/review |
   111	| Frozen replay/scorer/loader | Legacy observation, scoring, gold loading | Import and hash only | Diff plus digest equality |
   112	| Public compiled front door | Flag-gated served decision | Spawn with child-only env | Fresh, drifted, and broken fixtures |
   113	| Shared status/eligibility API | Cause and expectation authority | Consume read-only | State-matrix tests |
   114	
   115	Required inventories:
   116	
   117	- Enumerate every current Lane C exit code and verdict string before adding the gate.
   118	- Enumerate legacy telemetry and compiled target shapes for all seven hub archetypes.
   119	- Capture a baseline report for a representative hub and non-hub skill.
   120	- Pin the frozen file hashes before the first implementation edit.
   121	<!-- /ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->
   122	
