.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md-333-| # | Check | Result | Evidence |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md-334-|---|-------|--------|----------|
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:335:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | The coupling exists at `compiled-route.cjs:16-21` and the repo renumbers spec folders routinely |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md-336-| 2 | **Beyond Local Maxima?** | PASS | The cheaper guard-in-place option is weighed and scored |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md-337-| 3 | **Sufficient?** | PASS | Promotion removes the failure mode; no further mechanism is needed |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md-338-| 4 | **Fits Goal?** | PASS | A default-on fleet cannot rest on a resolver that a spec move can sever |
